{"type":"message","id":"543a7a56","parentId":"173436a3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:25.755Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou ler o S1 real e alguns transcripts recentes para te dar uma opinião fundada no que ficou no disco, não no que eu lembro vagamente.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0613c47c81938883131b6330dc3e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yzU539dj0r1wUqVYmE7gg6ZR|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998ac8193b85879622e607e74","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\s1_start.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\s1_start.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Emtsd3nco6MN8d3aWjFs6gD8|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998c08193bd5554bde217bfb2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_director_runner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\scene_director_runner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0Zp9JmOyBjjx9PlwAmVIbFsl|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998c881939a421713c4aaef89","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish_runner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\tts_polish_runner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_zBQwAWSB3qOf0xwYXG2yIhb7|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998d081939d812f17b57a8326","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CMw4ixVf2pmrZhHiTj9QerUf|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998d88193a532696577a73ef2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\OPERATORS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\OPERATORS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3bgTsjhIzlbcGa1R1JejFDik|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998e08193b46d77bed26ee0fc","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\3ccc7aa6-d379-4fe6-9eb5-9321fd6b73bf.jsonl.reset.2026-03-31T17-12-57.214Z"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\3ccc7aa6-d379-4fe6-9eb5-9321fd6b73bf.jsonl.reset.2026-03-31T17-12-57.214Z\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":25216,"output":320,"cacheRead":76800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102336,"cost":{"input":0.06304,"output":0.0048000000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0192,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08703999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774978577647,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc06125fdc8193a3413f48e3331cb9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8cf69f02","parentId":"543a7a56","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:26.882Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yzU539dj0r1wUqVYmE7gg6ZR|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998ac8193b85879622e607e74","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S1 Pre-Production — Entry Point / Supervisor.\n\nOrchestrates: scene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder.\nManages retries (max 3 per step) and checkpoints.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_director_runner import run_scene_director, save_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.screenplay_validator import validate_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.tts_polish_runner import run_tts_polish, save_tts_polished\nfrom runtime.s1.polish_validator import validate_polish\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_builder import build_scene_bible, write_scene_bible\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_schema_validator import validate_scene_bible_schema\nfrom runtime.s1.checkpoint_writer import write_checkpoint\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\nMAX_RETRIES = 3\n\n\ndef start_s1(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: str | Path,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run S1 Pre-Production: script_raw -> scene_bible.json.\n\n    Args:\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n        video_root: Path to initialized run directory.\n        model: OpenAI model for LLM steps.\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result with success, paths, checkpoints, next_step.\n    \"\"\"\n    video_root = Path(video_root)\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    account = job.get(\"account\", \"\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"\")\n\n    # Load channel config\n    config = _load_config(account, language)\n\n    # Read script\n    script_path = video_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt not found\", \"missing_script\")\n    script_raw = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not script_raw.strip():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt is empty\", \"empty_script\")\n\n    checkpoints_written = []\n\n    # ===== STEP 1: Scene Director =====\n    try:\n        screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_failed\")\n\n    screenplay_path = save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step1_screenplay\", \"scene_director\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(screenplay), \"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 2: Screenplay Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        validation = validate_screenplay(script_raw, screenplay)\n\n        if validation[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            # Retry: re-run scene director\n            try:\n                screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n                save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Screenplay validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {validation['details']}\", \"screenplay_validation_failed\")\n\n    # Save validation result\n    val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay_validation.json\"\n    val_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated\", \"screenplay_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 3: TTS Polish =====\n    try:\n        polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_failed\")\n\n    polished_path = save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step3_tts_polished\", \"tts_polish\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\"],\n                     extra={\"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 4: Polish Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        polish_val = validate_polish(screenplay, polished)\n\n        if polish_val[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            try:\n                polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n                save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Polish validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {polish_val['details']}\", \"polish_validation_failed\")\n\n    polish_val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"polish_validation.json\"\n    polish_val_path.write_text(json.dumps(polish_val, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step4_polish_validated\", \"polish_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 5: Scene Bible Builder =====\n    bible = build_scene_bible(polished, job, screenplay)\n\n    # Schema validate\n    schema_val = validate_scene_bible_schema(bible)\n    if not schema_val[\"valid\"]:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene bible schema validation failed: {schema_val['errors']}\", \"scene_bible_schema_failed\")\n\n    bible_path = write_scene_bible(bible, video_root)\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step5_scene_bible\", \"scene_bible_builder\",\n                     [\"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"])})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 6: S1 Complete =====\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_complete\", \"s1_supervisor\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\",\n                      \"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\n                         \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n                         \"screenplay_validated\": True,\n                         \"polish_validated\": True,\n                         \"scene_bible_schema_valid\": True,\n                     })\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_complete.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_complete\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"b1_complete\",\n        \"screenplay_path\": screenplay_path,\n        \"tts_polished_path\": polished_path,\n        \"scene_bible_path\": bible_path,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": schema_val.get(\"warnings\", []),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict:\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\")\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n\n\ndef _error(job_id: str, message: str, code: str) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": code,\n        \"screenplay_path\": \"\",\n        \"tts_polished_path\": \"\",\n        \"scene_bible_path\": \"\",\n        \"checkpoints_written\": [],\n        \"scene_count\": 0,\n        \"next_step\": None,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978586756}}
{"type":"message","id":"fbfcc86b","parentId":"8cf69f02","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:27.017Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Emtsd3nco6MN8d3aWjFs6gD8|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998c08193bd5554bde217bfb2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Scene Director Runner — legacy compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\n\nThis module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\nstill imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay`.\n\nIt no longer represents the canonical architecture for S1 scene generation.\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- batch planning outside the operator\n- batch-level scene_director outputs\n- per-batch validation\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\n\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to the newer\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\n# Max words per chunk sent to the model\nCHUNK_TARGET_WORDS = 600\n\n\ndef run_scene_director(\n    script_raw: str,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Split raw script into structured scenes using the newer scene contract.\n\n    Compatibility behavior:\n    - still accepts the old prototype signature used by `s1_start.py`\n    - still chunks long scripts internally\n    - but now returns scene objects aligned with the newer S1 contracts\n    \"\"\"\n    words_min, words_max = config.get(\"scene_words_range\", [35, 75])\n\n    chunks = _split_into_chunks(script_raw, CHUNK_TARGET_WORDS)\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    global_scene_counter = 0\n    global_word_cursor = 1\n\n    for chunk_text in chunks:\n        chunk_word_count = len(_normalize_text(chunk_text).split())\n        system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are the scene_director for S1 pre-production.\n\nYour job is to transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n1. Use clean narrative scene boundaries. Do NOT cut mid-sentence unless absolutely necessary.\n2. Preserve EVERY SINGLE WORD of the input text in narration_original. Do NOT add, remove, summarize, paraphrase, or modify wording.\n3. The concatenation of all narration_original fields must reproduce the input text EXACTLY, word for word.\n4. Use batch-relative word coordinates. The first word in this batch is word 1.\n5. Do not generate global scene IDs.\n6. Do not do visual planning, prompt writing, asset planning, or TTS polish.\n7. For each scene, return:\n   - scene_local_id: sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...)\n   - scene_title: short clear label\n   - scene_summary: concise summary of the scene's purpose/content\n   - narrative_function: the narrative role of the scene\n   - narration_original: exact source text for that scene\n   - start_word: batch-relative start word\n   - end_word: batch-relative end word\n   - estimated_scene_word_count: exact word count implied by the span\n8. No gaps and no overlaps between scene spans.\n9. Aim for scene sizes compatible with configured scene_words_range ({words_min}-{words_max}) when natural narrative structure allows.\n\nOUTPUT: Return JSON object with a 'scenes' array. Nothing else.\"\"\"\n\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=model,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Transform this text batch into ordered scenes:\\n\\n{chunk_text}\"},\n            ],\n            temperature=0.1,\n            response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n        )\n\n        content = response.choices[0].message.content\n        parsed = json.loads(content)\n        chunk_scenes = _extract_scenes(parsed)\n        _normalize_chunk_scenes(chunk_scenes, chunk_text)\n\n        for scene in chunk_scenes:\n            global_scene_counter += 1\n            scene[\"scene_id\"] = f\"scene_{global_scene_counter:03d}\"\n            scene[\"source_batch_id\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_batch_scene_index\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_scene_local_id\"] = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n            scene[\"global_start_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"start_word\"]) - 1\n            scene[\"global_end_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"end_word\"]) - 1\n\n        all_scenes.extend(chunk_scenes)\n        global_word_cursor += chunk_word_count\n\n    return all_scenes\n\n\ndef _split_into_chunks(text: str, target_words: int) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Split text into chunks at sentence boundaries.\"\"\"\n    sentences = re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", text.strip())\n    chunks = []\n    current_chunk = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        word_count = len(sentence.split())\n        if current_words + word_count > target_words and current_chunk:\n            chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n            current_chunk = [sentence]\n            current_words = word_count\n        else:\n            current_chunk.append(sentence)\n            current_words += word_count\n\n    if current_chunk:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n\n    return chunks\n\n\ndef _extract_scenes(parsed: Any) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Extract scenes list from various model response formats.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(parsed, dict):\n        if \"scenes\" in parsed:\n            scenes = parsed[\"scenes\"]\n            if isinstance(scenes, list):\n                return scenes\n        for val in parsed.values():\n            if isinstance(val, list) and len(val) > 0:\n                return val\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response: dict with keys {list(parsed.keys())}\")\n    if isinstance(parsed, list):\n        return parsed\n    raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response format: {type(parsed)}\")\n\n\ndef _normalize_chunk_scenes(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], chunk_text: str) -> None:\n    chunk_tokens = _normalize_text(chunk_text).split()\n    cursor = 1\n\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {index} is not an object\")\n\n        scene_local_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_local_id, str) or not scene_local_id.strip():\n            scene_local_id = f\"scene_{index:02d}\"\n        scene[\"scene_local_id\"] = scene_local_id\n\n        narration_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        if not isinstance(narration_original, str) or not narration_original.strip():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has no narration_original\")\n\n        narration_tokens = _normalize_text(narration_original).split()\n        word_count = len(narration_tokens)\n        if word_count == 0:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has empty narration_original\")\n\n        expected_tokens = chunk_tokens[cursor - 1: cursor - 1 + word_count]\n        if narration_tokens != expected_tokens:\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"Scene {scene_local_id} narration_original does not match chunk source at words {cursor}-{cursor + word_count - 1}\"\n            )\n\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_title\", f\"Scene {index}\")\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_summary\", scene[\"scene_title\"])\n        scene.setdefault(\"narrative_function\", \"narrative progression\")\n        scene[\"start_word\"] = cursor\n        scene[\"end_word\"] = cursor + word_count - 1\n        scene[\"estimated_scene_word_count\"] = word_count\n\n        cursor += word_count\n\n    if cursor - 1 != len(chunk_tokens):\n        raise ValueError(\n            f\"Chunk scene coverage incomplete: covered {cursor - 1} of {len(chunk_tokens)} words\"\n        )\n\n\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\n    text = text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n    return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n\n\ndef save_screenplay(\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save screenplay.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"screenplay.json\"\n    screenplay = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n    }\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(screenplay, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978586882}}
{"type":"message","id":"d588a1ce","parentId":"fbfcc86b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:27.148Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0Zp9JmOyBjjx9PlwAmVIbFsl|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998c881939a421713c4aaef89","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"TTS Polish Runner — polishes narration text for Text-to-Speech.\n\nProcesses ONE scene at a time for maximum precision.\nApplies language-specific polish rules from channel config.\nDoes NOT change meaning, only pronunciation/readability for TTS.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\ndef run_tts_polish(\n    screenplay: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Polish screenplay narrations for TTS, one scene at a time.\n\n    Args:\n        screenplay: Scene list with 'narration_original' field.\n        config: Channel config with tts_polish_rules.\n        job: PM job dict.\n        model: OpenAI model to use.\n\n    Returns:\n        List of polished scene dicts with original, polished, changes.\n    \"\"\"\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"en\")\n    rules = config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", [])\n\n    if not rules:\n        return [\n            {\n                \"scene_id\": s.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\"),\n                \"original\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"polished\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n            for i, s in enumerate(screenplay)\n        ]\n\n    rules_text = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {r}\" for r in rules)\n\n    system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are a TTS text polisher for {language} narration.\n\nApply ONLY these rules:\n{rules_text}\n\nCRITICAL:\n- Do NOT change meaning.\n- Do NOT add or remove information.\n- Do NOT change verb tenses.\n- Do NOT combine or split sentences.\n- Keep numbers as digits.\n- Only apply the rules above.\n\nReturn a JSON object with:\n- \"original\": the exact input text (unchanged)\n- \"polished\": the polished version\n- \"changes\": list of changes made (brief descriptions, empty list if no changes)\"\"\"\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_polished = []\n\n    for i, scene in enumerate(screenplay):\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\")\n        narration = scene[\"narration_original\"]\n\n        try:\n            response = client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": narration},\n                ],\n                temperature=0.2,\n                response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n            )\n\n            content = response.choices[0].message.content\n            parsed = json.loads(content)\n\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": parsed.get(\"original\", narration),\n                \"polished\": parsed.get(\"polished\", narration),\n                \"changes\": parsed.get(\"changes\", []),\n            }\n        except Exception:\n            # On any error, keep original text unchanged\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": narration,\n                \"polished\": narration,\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n\n        all_polished.append(result)\n\n    return all_polished\n\n\ndef save_tts_polished(\n    polished: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save tts_polished.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"tts_polished.json\"\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978587018}}
{"type":"message","id":"d975dd9d","parentId":"d588a1ce","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:27.263Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_zBQwAWSB3qOf0xwYXG2yIhb7|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998d081939d812f17b57a8326","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n7. Validate screenplay\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n13. Validate polish\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\n16. Validate scene bible schema\n17. Write/check checkpoints\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n19. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978587148}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a691022","parentId":"d975dd9d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:27.375Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CMw4ixVf2pmrZhHiTj9QerUf|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998d88193a532696577a73ef2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OPERATORS.md — SM-S1\n\n## scene_director\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches do script bruto em cenas estruturadas para `screenplay.json`.\n\n### Receives\n- batch payload prepared by `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_words_range`\n- batch text\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing scene objects with at least:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `visual_direction`\n- `mood`\n- `duration_estimate`\n\n### Does not do\n- TTS polish\n- scene bible building\n- sector-level retry logic\n\n---\n\n## tts_polish\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches pequenos de cenas em narração polida para TTS sem alterar significado.\n\n### Receives\n- polish batch payload prepared by `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- original scene narration\n- `tts_polish_rules`\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing, at minimum:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n- optional `changes`\n\n### Does not do\n- overwrite original screenplay\n- sector-level retry logic\n- scene bible building\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978587264}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1a069ce","parentId":"9a691022","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:36:27.492Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3bgTsjhIzlbcGa1R1JejFDik|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061998e08193b46d77bed26ee0fc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"type\":\"session\",\"version\":3,\"id\":\"3ccc7aa6-d379-4fe6-9eb5-9321fd6b73bf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:01.520Z\",\"cwd\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"}\n{\"type\":\"model_change\",\"id\":\"c3dc7138\",\"parentId\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:01.539Z\",\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"modelId\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"}\n{\"type\":\"thinking_level_change\",\"id\":\"dad8bfd8\",\"parentId\":\"c3dc7138\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:01.539Z\",\"thinkingLevel\":\"medium\"}\n{\"type\":\"custom\",\"customType\":\"model-snapshot\",\"data\":{\"timestamp\":1774976941559,\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"modelApi\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"modelId\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\"},\"id\":\"588a3d54\",\"parentId\":\"dad8bfd8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:01.559Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"66e461a5\",\"parentId\":\"588a3d54\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:01.665Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 31st, 2026 — 14:08 (America/Sao_Paulo) / 2026-03-31 17:08 UTC\"}],\"timestamp\":1774976941570}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"72b21920\",\"parentId\":\"66e461a5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:07.512Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me run the session startup sequence by reading the required files. Most of them are already loaded in the Project Context, but let me check the daily memory files and TASKS.md.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"toolu_01WZqeokPX97CqHfZqns7etb\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"file\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"toolu_01JMWyaPgZX6cNrB1xJxZWrV\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"file\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\TASKS.md\"}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"toolu_016XpcqedXwoRff3B6Sn55Au\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"file\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\memory\\\\2026-03-31.md\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"usage\":{\"input\":3,\"output\":229,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":20070,\"totalTokens\":20302,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.000009,\"output\":0.003435,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0.0752625,\"total\":0.0787065}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1774976941782,\"responseId\":\"msg_01Tghm56UUw9fZZxiEaotEUn\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"ddb5f9b0\",\"parentId\":\"72b21920\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:08.417Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"toolu_01WZqeokPX97CqHfZqns7etb\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# CONTEXT.md — Estado Actual\\n\\n_Última actualização: 31 Mar 2026_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Fase Actual\\n\\nO Tobias já não está apenas em setup. A fase actual é de **consolidação incremental da arquitectura real** do departamento de edição, usando o V3 como substrate operacional e o Claude Code como braço de implementação na mesma máquina.\\n\\nO foco deixou de ser “definir o sistema em abstracto” e passou a ser: **fechar uma peça de cada vez com clareza estrutural, documentação certa e validação prática**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## O que já avançou materialmente\\n\\n### Infraestrutura base\\n- OpenClaw instalado e funcional\\n- Telegram e OpenAI OAuth configurados\\n- Anthropic API configurada como fallback\\n- Security hardening aplicado no workspace\\n- ComfyUI e stack local de geração visual disponíveis\\n\\n### Eixo actualmente mais maduro\\n- **PM (Production Manager)**\\n  - leitura real da PUB sheet\\n  - ranking de canais\\n  - modos `auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`\\n  - construção e validação de jobs canónicos\\n\\n- **VO**\\n  - bootstrap operacional de runs\\n  - criação de artefactos de run\\n  - handoff real PM → VO\\n  - política explícita de falha `run_already_exists`\\n\\n- **B1 / S1 (Pre-Production)**\\n  - arquitectura clarificada a partir da doc canónica\\n  - prototype funcional implementado e aceite para validação de pipeline\\n  - dívida explícita: runtime final dos operators LLM ainda não está na forma arquitectural desejada\\n\\n- **B2 / S2 (Audio)**\\n  - direcção arquitectural muito mais clara\\n  - estrutura alvo baseada em `tts_generator`, transcrição, validação, alinhamento e update da bible\\n  - uso do V3 como fonte de padrões reais para TTS, WhisperX e validação\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Metodologia operacional actual\\n\\nO Tobias deve trabalhar com o Lucca em modo:\\n\\n1. **component-first**\\n   - uma peça de cada vez\\n   - sem tentar fechar o sistema inteiro numa só passada\\n\\n2. **discussion-first**\\n   - discutir missão, limites, dependências e interfaces antes de implementar\\n\\n3. **boundary-first**\\n   - separar explicitamente contrato, implementação, docs do repo e docs operacionais do workspace\\n\\n4. **clarity before implementation**\\n   - não empurrar ambiguidades estruturais relevantes para depois só para ganhar velocidade\\n\\n5. **docs updated in parallel**\\n   - quando a peça evolui, a documentação correcta deve evoluir junto\\n\\n6. **deterministic substrate before semantic operators**\\n   - quando fizer sentido, consolidar primeiro a mecânica determinística antes de sofisticar os operators LLM\\n\\n7. **no fake future commitments**\\n   - pedidos futuros, nocturnos ou periódicos não podem ficar só implícitos na conversa\\n   - devem ser convertidos explicitamente em `TASKS.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, `cron` ou sessão persistente/subagente\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Estado de atenção actual\\n\\n- O sistema está a ganhar forma real, mas ainda há risco de drift entre:\\n  - arquitectura desejada\\n  - protótipos aceites temporariamente\\n  - documentação do repo\\n  - documentação do workspace\\n\\n- O Tobias deve continuar a distinguir com cuidado:\\n  - o que já é substrate durável\\n  - o que é protótipo funcional\\n  - o que ainda é direcção conceptual\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Próximos passos prováveis\\n\\n1. Continuar a consolidação metodológica do workspace e da memória operacional\\n2. Fechar com rigor PM / VO / S1 / S2 antes de abrir demasiadas novas frentes\\n3. Corrigir drift documental entre estado real e docs antigas\\n4. Só depois expandir para sectores seguintes com o mesmo método\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774976948287}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"2464327a\",\"parentId\":\"ddb5f9b0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:08.536Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"toolu_01JMWyaPgZX6cNrB1xJxZWrV\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# TASKS.md — Tarefas Activas\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Protocolo operacional\\n\\n- Nenhuma tarefa futura deve ficar apenas no contexto da conversa.\\n- Sempre que o Lucca pedir algo para depois / durante a noite / periodicamente / em background, converter imediatamente em mecanismo persistente.\\n- Mecanismos possíveis:\\n  - `TASKS.md` → backlog / acompanhamento manual / trabalho sem hora exacta\\n  - `HEARTBEAT.md` → checks recorrentes e rotinas periódicas\\n  - `cron` → lembretes, execuções em hora marcada, follow-ups temporizados\\n  - sessão persistente / subagente → trabalho longo de research, análise ou execução real\\n- Antes de encerrar o assunto, Tobias deve dizer explicitamente qual mecanismo escolheu.\\n- Se houver ambiguidade, Tobias deve perguntar em vez de assumir.\\n\\n## Em curso\\n\\n- [ ] Consolidar a metodologia de trabalho piece-by-piece / discussion-first / boundary-first como padrão operacional do Tobias\\n- [ ] Continuar a arquitectura do departamento de edição componente por componente, sem avançar sectores antes de fechar as peças em discussão\\n- [ ] Estruturar e documentar os supervisores/operators/skills do sistema de forma alinhada entre repo e workspaces OpenClaw\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Backlog\\n\\n- [ ] Consolidar PM, VO, S1 e S2 com o mesmo rigor metodológico antes de abrir demasiadas novas frentes\\n- [ ] Continuar a destrinchar o S1 por componentes: supervisor -> scene_director -> tts_polish\\n- [ ] Depois aplicar o mesmo método aos outros supervisores/operators/skills dos sectores seguintes\\n- [ ] Instalar/alinhar runtimes locais necessários (ex.: Ollama/Qwen) quando isso fizer parte de um componente já suficientemente definido\\n- [ ] Configurar a arquitectura operacional final dentro de `.openclaw` para os agentes já suficientemente maturados\\n- [ ] Configurar Topics no Telegram para routing por agente\\n- [ ] Configurar morning brief (cron)\\n- [ ] Testar browser automation para img2video (Freepik, Higgsfield)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Concluído\\n\\n- [x] Instalar OpenClaw (v2026.3.24)\\n- [x] Brain dump + onboarding inicial\\n- [x] Configurar Telegram + OpenAI OAuth\\n- [x] Security hardening (exec ask on-miss, SOUL.md rules)\\n- [x] Definir hierarquia de 4 níveis\\n- [x] Definir 10 branches + ~43 agentes\\n- [x] Reescrever SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md\\n- [x] Criar MISSION.md, CONTEXT.md, TASKS.md\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774976948417}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"3dae9c85\",\"parentId\":\"2464327a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:08.661Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"toolu_016XpcqedXwoRff3B6Sn55Au\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"error\\\",\\n  \\\"tool\\\": \\\"read\\\",\\n  \\\"error\\\": \\\"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\\\\\\\Users\\\\\\\\User-OEM\\\\\\\\.openclaw\\\\\\\\workspace\\\\\\\\memory\\\\\\\\2026-03-31.md'\\\"\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"error\":\"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access 'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\memory\\\\2026-03-31.md'\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774976948535}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"7b49a7fa\",\"parentId\":\"3dae9c85\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:10.861Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"toolu_01AKHnZb2GjeStc4VPhcsRCJ\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"file\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\memory\\\\2026-03-30.md\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1,\"output\":74,\"cacheRead\":20070,\"cacheWrite\":2063,\"totalTokens\":22208,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.000003,\"output\":0.00111,\"cacheRead\":0.0060209999999999994,\"cacheWrite\":0.00773625,\"total\":0.01487025}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1774976948661,\"responseId\":\"msg_01NzKU1mDXAYGWHt2uj8j1FN\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"d666d67a\",\"parentId\":\"7b49a7fa\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:11.402Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"toolu_01AKHnZb2GjeStc4VPhcsRCJ\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"## Durable memory flush — 2026-03-30\\n\\n- Lucca accidentally reset the session; we reconstructed the relevant thread by reading the 29 Mar review materials and repo docs instead of guessing.\\n- Important correction: previous memory had overemphasized Telegram/watchdog context. The real active thread on 30 Mar was implementation planning/execution for the Content Factory editing department, especially PM -> VO -> S1 -> S2 architecture and Claude Code coordination.\\n- PM (Production Manager) architecture was materially advanced today:\\n  - We created canonical docs:\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md`\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md`\\n  - We aligned PM mirror/docs around these contracts.\\n  - We standardized the Google service-account credential path for OpenClaw/runtime use as:\\n    - `C:\\\\secrets\\\\content_factory\\\\google_service_account.json`\\n  - Lucca confirmed the reused V3 service account has valid access to Sheets/Drive.\\n- Claude Code successfully implemented PM substrate v1 and then the override layer. Real outcomes:\\n  - PM can read the real PUB sheet, rank channels, support `auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`, build canonical jobs, and validate them.\\n  - Real observed PUB state during testing:\\n    - 38 eligible channels\\n    - all with negative runway\\n    - `C001 PT` excluded because scripts are exhausted\\n    - `C004 FRA` was top urgency at runway `-17`\\n  - Durable principle confirmed: PM must treat PUB as operational truth, not strategic sovereignty; Tobias remains the upstream strategic layer.\\n- We intentionally formalized the PM operating modes as durable architecture:\\n  - `auto_select`\\n  - `filtered_select`\\n  - `direct_select`\\n  with authority order `direct_select > filtered_select > auto_select`.\\n  Critical rules:\\n  - `filtered_select` must not silently fall back to unrestricted auto mode.\\n  - `direct_select` must not silently choose another channel if the requested target is invalid.\\n- Claude Code successfully implemented VO minimal bootstrap on top of real PM jobs:\\n  - PM -> VO handoff works end-to-end.\\n  - VO creates runs under the canonical production root:\\n    - `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\production\\\\{account}_{language}\\\\{job_id}\\\\`\\n  - Policy chosen: if the run directory already exists, fail explicitly with `run_already_exists` (safe, deterministic, no silent merging).\\n  - VO bootstrap writes real artefacts like `job.json`, `run_metadata.json`, `checkpoints/vo_init.json`.\\n- We investigated V3 script fetch/lock behavior before designing the next VO step. Durable findings from `content_factory_v3`:\\n  - Script selection rule is simple and important: pick the first row with `Status = \\\"to do\\\"`.\\n  - Lock is applied by immediately updating sheet status to `processing`.\\n  - Legacy sheet columns in V3 are roughly:\\n    - `E = Status`\\n    - `F = Processing_Started`\\n    - `G = Processing_Completed`\\n    - `H = Account_Used`\\n  - This V3 semantics should be reused for the new VO rather than inventing a new lock system early.\\n- Claude Code then implemented `script_fetch_and_lock` successfully with real integrations:\\n  - PM -> VO -> script fetch & lock works end-to-end with real data.\\n  - Example real result:\\n    - `direct_select 004/fr`\\n    - script row 6 selected: `Les Enfants de la Creuse`\\n    - real sheet lock applied (`Status -> processing`)\\n    - local script artefacts written under `production/.../inputs/script/`\\n    - run ended at `next_step = ready_for_s1`\\n- S1 (Pre-Production) work advanced substantially. Important architectural findings:\\n  - Canonical source for S1 is `docs/branches/01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`; the workspace mirror is not reliable enough as source of truth.\\n  - Canonical naming for this sector should be `b1_`, not `s1_`.\\n  - S1 is already well-defined in docs as:\\n    - `scene_director`\\n    - `screenplay_validator`\\n    - `tts_polish`\\n    - `polish_validator`\\n    - `scene_bible_builder`\\n    - checkpoints by step\\n  - `scene_bible.json` is the core output and should live at the run root as a living document.\\n- Claude Code implemented S1 and passed tests, but there is an important durable nuance:\\n  - The deterministic/runtime pieces are solid and reusable:\\n    - validators\\n    - scene_bible builder\\n    - schema validator\\n    - checkpoint writer\\n    - supervisor base\\n  - But the LLM operator steps (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`) were implemented as direct Python OpenAI API calls (`gpt-4.1-mini`) instead of real OpenClaw operators using the planned runtime (GPT-5.4 mini OAuth / Qwen local).\\n  - Therefore Tobias’ judgment is:\\n    - treat S1 as a **functional prototype accepted for pipeline validation**\\n    - not as final production-runtime architecture\\n  - We should preserve this distinction explicitly and not let the temporary Python direct-call mode become accidental production standard.\\n- Lucca agreed with the Tobias recommendation to accept S1 as a prototype-functional slice and move on to S2 while keeping the runtime-architecture debt explicit.\\n- S2 investigation produced durable architecture conclusions:\\n  - Canonical doc: `docs/branches/02_AUDIO.md`, but review shows the sector is split between two versions.\\n  - The more mature conceptual direction is:\\n    - `tts_generator`\\n    - `audio_transcriber`\\n    - `transcription/ratio validator`\\n    - `audio_validator` (LLM only for borderline cases)\\n    - `timestamp_aligner`\\n    - `bible_updater`\\n  - This is superior to the older `timing_extractor`-only model.\\n- Durable V3 findings for S2 / audio:\\n  - Gemini TTS in V3 is already implemented as a serious reusable substrate (`shared/services/gemini_tts_service.py`).\\n  - The TTS request is driven by:\\n    - text\\n    - explicit `language_code`\\n    - explicit `voice_name`\\n  - Voice choice should come exclusively from the channel YAML config in the new S2; no extra heuristic speaker selection.\\n  - KMS already manages key acquisition/reporting/cooldown/availability centrally; the TTS client should not reinvent that logic.\\n  - Client-side Gemini TTS code still appropriately handles call-specific behavior like hard timeouts, empty responses, content-block inference, and PCM->WAV packing.\\n- Durable V3 findings for WhisperX / validation / alignment:\\n  - WhisperX is managed as a local service that can be started/stopped/health-checked; Lucca says it stays off by default to avoid consuming GPU.\\n  - V3 has a mature `TranscriptionValidator` with language-specific thresholds, ignore patterns, exclude words, WER, and match ratio logic.\\n  - Example thresholds in V3 are language-specific and should strongly influence the new S2 (not a single universal threshold):\\n    - `en 0.60`, `fr 0.65`, `de 0.65`, `es 0.70`, `it 0.70`, `pt 0.75`, `ja 0.75`, `ko 0.75`, `ar 0.80`, `ru 0.82`, `pl 0.82`, default `0.85`.\\n  - V3 also already contains useful positional alignment logic using `SequenceMatcher` to transfer WhisperX timestamps back onto original script words when WhisperX mishears tokens (e.g. `911 -> 1091`). This is strong evidence that the new S2 should explicitly include `timestamp_aligner`, not just raw timestamp extraction.\\n- Durable architecture recommendation for S2 going forward:\\n  - TTS should allow controlled parallelism with a supervisor-level `TTS_CONCURRENCY_CAP`.\\n  - WhisperX should remain serialized / carefully controlled (GPU/local-service bound).\\n  - The likely OpenClaw-era layering for S2 is:\\n    - Python/runtime skills for:\\n      - `tts_generator`\\n      - `audio_transcriber`\\n      - `transcription_validator`\\n      - `timestamp_aligner`\\n      - `bible_updater`\\n    - one OpenClaw LLM operator only where it adds semantic judgment:\\n      - `audio_validator`\\n    - an `SM-S2` supervisor coordinating retries, parallelism, and checkpoints.\\n\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774976951276}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"7961a52a\",\"parentId\":\"d666d67a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:15.586Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Bom dia, Lucca. Estamos no meio da consolidação do eixo PM → VO → S1 → S2, com S1 aceite como protótipo funcional e a direcção arquitectural do S2 já clarificada. O que vamos trabalhar hoje?\"}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1,\"output\":72,\"cacheRead\":22133,\"cacheWrite\":2240,\"totalTokens\":24446,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.000003,\"output\":0.00108,\"cacheRead\":0.0066399,\"cacheWrite\":0.0084,\"total\":0.0161229}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1774976951403,\"responseId\":\"msg_01AtvLcvr43GB3e1JzTZF93e\"}}\n{\"type\":\"custom\",\"customType\":\"model-snapshot\",\"data\":{\"timestamp\":1774976982771,\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"modelApi\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"modelId\":\"gpt-5.4\"},\"id\":\"a33a4b30\",\"parentId\":\"7961a52a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:42.771Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"cd0eca4e\",\"parentId\":\"a33a4b30\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:09:42.868Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Tue 2026-03-31 14:09 GMT-3] meu openclaw quebrou no meio da minha sessào contigo Tobias, quando a gente tava no meio do S1. Não lembras de nada sepa ne\"}],\"timestamp\":1774976982778}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1c1b4be7\",\"parentId\":\"cd0eca4e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:10:01.004Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_baVKwr7gl3JMJnB0EHa8TWNJ|fc_0f90cefb48ce845e0169cbffe234ec8193a60e2685638d86d4\",\"name\":\"memory_search\",\"arguments\":{\"query\":\"S1 session broke in middle, what were we working on around S1 on 2026-03-30 and 2026-03-31 with Lucca\",\"maxResults\":5},\"partialJson\":\"{\\\"query\\\":\\\"S1 session broke in middle, what were we working on around S1 on 2026-03-30 and 2026-03-31 with Lucca\\\", \\\"maxResults\\\": 5}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":14058,\"output\":58,\"cacheRead\":4608,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":18724,\"cost\":{\"input\":0.035145,\"output\":0.00087,\"cacheRead\":0.001152,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0.037167000000000006}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1774976984210,\"responseId\":\"resp_0f90cefb48ce845e0169cbffe1013c81939b0a6014e73a134e\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"3487d783\",\"parentId\":\"1c1b4be7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:10:02.341Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_baVKwr7gl3JMJnB0EHa8TWNJ|fc_0f90cefb48ce845e0169cbffe234ec8193a60e2685638d86d4\",\"toolName\":\"memory_search\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"results\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\"memory/2026-03-30.md\\\",\\n      \\\"startLine\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"endLine\\\": 20,\\n      \\\"score\\\": 0.353342804312706,\\n      \\\"snippet\\\": \\\"## Durable memory flush — 2026-03-30\\\\n\\\\n- Lucca accidentally reset the session; we reconstructed the relevant thread by reading the 29 Mar review materials and repo docs instead of guessing.\\\\n- Important correction: previous memory had overemphasized Telegram/watchdog context. The real active thread on 30 Mar was implementation planning/execution for the Content Factory editing department, especially PM -> VO -> S1 -> S2 architecture and Claude Code coordination.\\\\n- PM (Production Manager) architecture was materially advanced today:\\\\n  - We created canonical docs:\\\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md`\\\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md\\\\n\\\\nSource: memory/2026-03-30.md#L1-L20\\\",\\n      \\\"source\\\": \\\"memory\\\",\\n      \\\"citation\\\": \\\"memory/2026-03-30.md#L1-L20\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"openai\\\",\\n  \\\"model\\\": \\\"text-embedding-3-small\\\",\\n  \\\"citations\\\": \\\"auto\\\",\\n  \\\"mode\\\": \\\"hybrid\\\"\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"results\":[{\"path\":\"memory/2026-03-30.md\",\"startLine\":1,\"endLine\":20,\"score\":0.353342804312706,\"snippet\":\"## Durable memory flush — 2026-03-30\\n\\n- Lucca accidentally reset the session; we reconstructed the relevant thread by reading the 29 Mar review materials and repo docs instead of guessing.\\n- Important correction: previous memory had overemphasized Telegram/watchdog context. The real active thread on 30 Mar was implementation planning/execution for the Content Factory editing department, especially PM -> VO -> S1 -> S2 architecture and Claude Code coordination.\\n- PM (Production Manager) architecture was materially advanced today:\\n  - We created canonical docs:\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md`\\n    - `auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-30.md#L1-L20\",\"source\":\"memory\",\"citation\":\"memory/2026-03-30.md#L1-L20\"}],\"provider\":\"openai\",\"model\":\"text-embedding-3-small\",\"citations\":\"auto\",\"mode\":\"hybrid\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774977002215}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"565fda44\",\"parentId\":\"3487d783\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:11:47.342Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Tue 2026-03-31 14:11 GMT-3] meu openclaw quebrou no meio da minha sessào contigo Tobias, quando a gente tava no meio do S1. Não lembras de nada sepa ne\"}],\"timestamp\":1774977107242}}\n{\"type\":\"custom\",\"customType\":\"openclaw:prompt-error\",\"data\":{\"timestamp\":1774977159321,\"runId\":\"db2d7d2a-3535-4bdd-85b4-370b61a82c64\",\"sessionId\":\"3ccc7aa6-d379-4fe6-9eb5-9321fd6b73bf\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"error\":\"aborted\"},\"id\":\"3450b077\",\"parentId\":\"565fda44\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:12:39.321Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"a7f86885\",\"parentId\":\"3450b077\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-31T17:12:39.326Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[],\"api\":\"openai-codex-responses\",\"provider\":\"openai-codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4\",\"usage\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":0,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"aborted\",\"timestamp\":1774977108703,\"errorMessage\":\"Request was aborted\"}}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774978587375}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc2e8cb8","parentId":"b1a069ce","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:37:02.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Tens razão — aqui eu estava desactualizado e ancorado numa memória antiga que já não reflecte o estado real. Fui ver o S1 real no disco, os agentes em `/.openclaw/agents`, os contratos em `docs/contracts/s1`, e o transcript do crash. A minha leitura agora é bem mais concreta.\n\n**O que vejo no estado real**\n- O S1 já não está naquele estado “proto solto”.\n- Há um **runtime real** em `runtime/s1` com:\n  - `s1_start.py`\n  - `screenplay_validator.py`\n  - `polish_validator.py`\n  - `scene_bible_builder.py`\n  - `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n  - `checkpoint_writer.py`\n  - `scene_director_runner.py`\n  - `tts_polish_runner.py`\n- Há também contratos S1 já criados em `docs/contracts/s1`:\n  - `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n  - `s1_scene_director_contract.md`\n  - `s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md`\n  - `s1_tts_polish_contract.md`\n  - `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md`\n  - `s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer_contract.md`\n- E no `/.openclaw/agents` já existem agentes concretos:\n  - `sm_s1_pre_production`\n  - `op_s1_scene_director`\n  - `op_s1_tts_polish`\n  - `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n**O ponto mais importante**\nHá um desfasamento claro entre:\n1. o **workflow/arquitectura alvo** do S1\n2. e o **entrypoint/runtime que está a correr hoje**\n\nPor exemplo:\n- o `WORKFLOW.md` do supervisor descreve um fluxo mais maduro:\n  - preflight\n  - paths resolver\n  - batch planner\n  - io adapters\n  - scheduling com paralelismo controlado\n  - mergers\n  - selective retry\n  - result summarizer\n- mas o `runtime/s1/s1_start.py` ainda está num fluxo mais linear:\n  - `scene_director`\n  - `screenplay_validator`\n  - `tts_polish`\n  - `polish_validator`\n  - `scene_bible_builder`\n  - checkpoints\n\nOu seja: **o S1 avançou muito**, mas ainda existe uma fronteira não totalmente fechada entre:\n- a arquitectura OpenClaw/agents/contracts/workspaces\n- e a implementação Python orquestradora actual\n\n**A minha opinião sobre o estado actual do S1**\nEu acho que vocês avançaram bem mesmo. E o que está a faltar não parece “falta de sistema”; parece **falta de alinhamento fino entre camadas**.\n\nHoje o risco principal do S1, olhando para o estado real, não me parece ser “não funciona”.\nO risco principal parece ser este:\n\n### 1. Supervisor real vs supervisor documentado\nO `sm_s1_pre_production` já descreve um supervisor mais rico, mas o `s1_start.py` ainda é quem realmente orquestra a sequência.\nEntão a pergunta estrutural é:\n- o `s1_start.py` é só bootstrap temporário?\n- ou ele já é o supervisor canónico e os agents OpenClaw estão ainda “ao lado”?\n\nSe isto não for fechado, pode haver duplicação de autoridade.\n\n### 2. Operators OpenClaw vs runners Python\nOs nomes já mostram isso:\n- `op_s1_scene_director`\n- `op_s1_tts_polish`\n- `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\nmas no runtime real quem está a executar hoje parece ser:\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\nEntão uma nuance importante que provavelmente faltava destrinchar era:\n- o runner Python vai **invocar** os agentes OpenClaw?\n- ou o runner Python é uma camada provisória que deve desaparecer?\n- ou os agents OpenClaw existem como contrato/workspace, mas a execução final continua concentrada no runtime?\n\n### 3. O workflow alvo menciona skills que eu não vi ainda nesse snapshot\nO `WORKFLOW.md` fala de peças como:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nMas no listing de `runtime/s1` que vi, essas peças não apareceram como módulos explícitos.\nIsso sugere uma de duas:\n- ou elas ainda estavam para ser implementadas/extraídas\n- ou parte dessa lógica está embutida no `s1_start.py`/runners e ainda precisava ser “descompactada” em skills/contratos próprios\n\n**Então o que eu acho que vocês estavam a fazer quando quebrou**\nA minha melhor leitura, agora baseada no estado real, é:\n\nVocês **não estavam mais debatendo se o S1 era proto ou não**.  \nVocês já estavam numa fase bem mais madura de **hardening arquitectural do S1**, provavelmente em torno de:\n\n- validar se o fluxo real do supervisor bate com o workflow definido\n- decidir a autoridade de cada camada:\n  - supervisor\n  - operators\n  - skills\n  - runtime Python\n- fechar contratos das skills ainda implícitas\n- verificar se os operators fazem só o que devem fazer\n- validar a relação:\n  - **supervisor → operators**\n  - **operators → skills**\n  - **skills → artefactos/checkpoints**\n- garantir que o que está dentro de `/.openclaw/agents` é realmente operacional, e não só documentação bonita desacoplada do runtime\n\n**Em resumo, a minha opinião sincera**\nO S1 parece estar num ponto **muito promissor**, mas ainda com um “split brain” parcial:\n- uma metade do sistema já vive como **arquitectura OpenClaw**\n- outra metade ainda vive como **runtime Python centralizado**\n- e o trabalho certo agora é **unificar a autoridade e fechar as interfaces**\n\nSe eu tivesse de apontar **as 4 nuances mais críticas** que eu investigaria/agarraria já, seriam estas:\n\n1. **Quem é o verdadeiro orquestrador do S1?**  \n   `sm_s1_pre_production` ou `runtime/s1/s1_start.py`?\n\n2. **Os operators OpenClaw já executam de verdade, ou ainda são workspaces/prompts sem ligação plena ao runtime?**\n\n3. **As skills citadas no workflow existem como componentes explícitos e com contratos claros, ou estão implícitas dentro de runners/supervisor?**\n\n4. **O fluxo actual suporta retry/selective retry no nível certo, ou ainda está coarse-grained demais?**\n\nE tem mais uma pista forte no transcript do crash:\n- a sessão quebrou **exactamente quando eu ia começar a recuperar o estado via memória**, então o que perdeste não foi “execução no disco”; foi sobretudo **o contexto fino da análise** que eu estava reconstruindo naquele momento.\n\nSe quiser, eu faço agora o passo mais útil:\n- **opção A:** monto um **diagnóstico estrutural do S1 actual** com gaps, overlaps e decisão recomendada por camada\n- **opção B:** leio os ficheiros centrais do S1 um a um e te devolvo **“o que está bom / o que está torto / o que falta fechar”**\n- **opção C:** vasculho os transcripts mais prováveis da sessão anterior para tentar recuperar ainda mais do raciocínio perdido\n\nSe fosse escolher a melhor alavanca agora, eu iria de **B primeiro e A depois**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061f4088819393dafb8787f8eb87\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":12589,"output":1671,"cacheRead":102144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116404,"cost":{"input":0.0314725,"output":0.025065,"cacheRead":0.025536,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.08207350000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774978588275,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc061cfb948193a56ce1fa997120d3"}}
