{"type":"message","id":"4ad3caf6","parentId":"060de433","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SncqD35NAXcuuo5ScxVyPZTl|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f4c8193b6cc8f544dcfa1b8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"operator_batch_scheduler.py\r\nretry_planner.py\r\ns1_paths_resolver.py\r\ns1_preflight_checker.py\r\ns1_result_summarizer.py\r\nscene_director_io_adapter.py\r\nscene_director_output_validator.py\r\nscreenplay_merger.py\r\nscript_batch_planner.py\r\ntts_polish_batch_planner.py\r\ntts_polish_io_adapter.py\r\ntts_polish_merger.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":450,"aggregated":"operator_batch_scheduler.py\r\nretry_planner.py\r\ns1_paths_resolver.py\r\ns1_preflight_checker.py\r\ns1_result_summarizer.py\r\nscene_director_io_adapter.py\r\nscene_director_output_validator.py\r\nscreenplay_merger.py\r\nscript_batch_planner.py\r\ntts_polish_batch_planner.py\r\ntts_polish_io_adapter.py\r\ntts_polish_merger.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979055905}}
{"type":"message","id":"92206909","parentId":"4ad3caf6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.167Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_E3103szxmnsjjb8ILpN4Ljyj|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f5c81938a27f288cc4c3de2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n\n## Supervisor skills implemented\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n## Existing shared component to reuse\n- `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`\n\n## Operators supervised\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n## Key paths in the system repo\n- Supervisor contract:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- Runtime supervisor skills:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\`\n- Existing checkpoint writer:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\checkpoint_writer.py`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979056032}}
{"type":"message","id":"1469a14a","parentId":"92206909","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_zW42e74EYlPfa5iKjuWGGIZh|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f648193b21fad679e909ddf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\n\n## Input assumptions\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n## Naming convention\nCanonical naming is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*`\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979056168}}
{"type":"message","id":"92ccf0b7","parentId":"1469a14a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.393Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_gFGrPQjmEfC6UXVjquU3YfuZ|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f708193ad63854cabf37a51","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n7. Validate screenplay\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n13. Validate polish\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\n16. Validate scene bible schema\n17. Write/check checkpoints\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n19. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979056286}}
{"type":"message","id":"8d8074c0","parentId":"92ccf0b7","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_oEKwv92GgloXeHcT8iJHfSKg|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f788193afa8dae4af67384b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# STATE.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector state model\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\n- `not_started`\n- `running`\n- `retrying`\n- `blocked`\n- `complete`\n- `failed`\n\n## Retry policy (v1)\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\n- semantic screenplay failures -> retry affected batches when possible\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\n- retry limit -> abort\n\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n## Parallelism rules\n- parallelize only batchable operators\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, and preflight sequential\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\n\n## Escalation rule\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979056394}}
{"type":"message","id":"214e9a1b","parentId":"8d8074c0","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:16.618Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Jfj1oe4ZkH3fLiuMlDrYYOUI|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ee8f808193990b1190b7461786","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Newly required / now being formalized\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer` (already exists in `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`, pending light alignment audit only)\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\nImportant precondition:\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\n- structural patch candidates\n- batch repair candidates\n- full batch regeneration candidates\n\n## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Purpose\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\n\n### Scope\n- receives operator batches\n- applies a concurrency cap\n- groups batches into execution waves\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\n\n### Initial supported operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n### Out of scope\n`operator_batch_scheduler` does **not**:\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself yet\n- decide semantic retry logic\n- merge outputs\n- validate content\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n- `operator_batch_scheduler` is implemented as the controlled parallel scheduling layer for batchable operators\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979056509}}
{"type":"message","id":"6020f886","parentId":"214e9a1b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:31.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou abrir as supervisor_skills para verificar se estão mesmo adequadas ao workflow descrito e onde faltam contratos específicos.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07f5a56881938ac1e40ee063ea7d\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4LOGLuyeHWRwTZSrgZMmdPCA|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2ec8193ab1c0134e75f170c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_preflight_checker.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_preflight_checker.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SYWuqmzm7OK1KhS5PpUm104G|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2f88193b05b1da7f814666e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_paths_resolver.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_paths_resolver.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Jhb1o90ieG2Jy1S1wuK0iHgO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2fc8193bebaf161f1f9a776","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\script_batch_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\script_batch_planner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8tkx33PNXuiUyNMMq8fiVx8e|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3048193b0ef7345451db3d8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_director_io_adapter.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\scene_director_io_adapter.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AVgo7CDwz027b1F9pTu0exoi|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3088193a9c2d0c09f419fe9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_director_output_validator.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\scene_director_output_validator.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_RGXdP7x6UBZI5lFKYZeLeJrp|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31081938d2181d71dfe8f5d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\screenplay_merger.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\screenplay_merger.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_26O0DbhWmF4H4QEtDb4NrOEn|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31481938c89dc69ce96924f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OqaPMtpF9vZ9uVWahs4bMgwh|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31c81939fdd9e35503d4f44","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_KDUEnch9vG5UoN7D3F2PpP6v|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3248193953ae5b05c588d50","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_merger.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_merger.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ASeaM0fKIW5hPnJg4o059ART|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb328819387882bc8001b0632","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\retry_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\retry_planner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rTt8G29dBQ4Xwzf13ZbEdVCe|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb32c8193a71d76140623f218","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\operator_batch_scheduler.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\operator_batch_scheduler.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d3PkUcYeYuuNQR5E6RpXvyg1|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb33081939ef5936027f1a8aa","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_result_summarizer.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_result_summarizer.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":118239,"output":599,"cacheRead":14848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133686,"cost":{"input":0.2955975,"output":0.008985,"cacheRead":0.003712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.3082945}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979057187,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07f23fec819393d84ae510d0ce43"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d310da41","parentId":"6020f886","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:33.631Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4LOGLuyeHWRwTZSrgZMmdPCA|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2ec8193ab1c0134e75f170c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef run_preflight(run_root: str | Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"job\": {},\n        \"paths\": {},\n        \"script_stats\": {},\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n    if not run_root.exists() or not run_root.is_dir():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"missing_run_root\",\n            \"message\": f\"Run root not found or not a directory: {run_root}\",\n        })\n        return result\n\n    job_json = run_root / \"job.json\"\n    run_metadata = run_root / \"run_metadata.json\"\n    script_raw = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    script_metadata = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_metadata.json\"\n    script_lock = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_lock.json\"\n    vo_script_ready = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"vo_script_ready.json\"\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    b1_complete = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"b1_complete.json\"\n\n    result[\"paths\"].update(\n        {\n            \"job_json\": str(job_json),\n            \"run_metadata\": str(run_metadata),\n            \"script_raw\": str(script_raw),\n            \"script_metadata\": str(script_metadata),\n            \"script_lock\": str(script_lock),\n            \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": str(vo_script_ready),\n        }\n    )\n\n    required_files = [\n        (job_json, \"missing_job_json\", \"job.json not found\"),\n        (run_metadata, \"missing_run_metadata\", \"run_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_raw, \"missing_script_raw\", \"inputs/script/script_raw.txt not found\"),\n        (script_metadata, \"missing_script_metadata\", \"inputs/script/script_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_lock, \"missing_script_lock\", \"inputs/script/script_lock.json not found\"),\n        (vo_script_ready, \"missing_vo_script_ready_checkpoint\", \"checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json not found\"),\n    ]\n\n    for path_obj, code, message in required_files:\n        if not path_obj.exists():\n            errors.append({\"code\": code, \"message\": message})\n\n    job_data: dict[str, Any] = {}\n    if job_json.exists():\n        try:\n            job_data = json.loads(job_json.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_job_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read/parse job.json: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    job_id = job_data.get(\"job_id\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    account = job_data.get(\"account\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    language = job_data.get(\"language\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n\n    if not job_id:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_job_id\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'job_id'\"})\n    if not account:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_account\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'account'\"})\n    if not language:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_language\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'language'\"})\n\n    result[\"job\"] = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n    }\n\n    channel_config: Path | None = None\n    if account and language:\n        repo_root = run_root.parent.parent.parent\n        channel_config = repo_root / \"accounts\" / str(account) / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n        result[\"paths\"][\"channel_config\"] = str(channel_config)\n        if not channel_config.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_channel_config\",\n                \"message\": f\"Channel config not found: {channel_config}\",\n            })\n\n    if script_raw.exists():\n        try:\n            script_text = script_raw.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").strip()\n            if not script_text:\n                errors.append({\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"script_raw.txt is empty\"})\n            else:\n                word_count = len(script_text.split())\n                char_count = len(script_text)\n                result[\"script_stats\"] = {\n                    \"char_count\": char_count,\n                    \"word_count\": word_count,\n                }\n                if word_count < 50:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_short\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually short ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n                if word_count > 5000:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_long\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually long ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"script_unreadable\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read script_raw.txt: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    if b1_root.exists() and not b1_complete.exists():\n        warnings.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_outputs_already_present\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_pre_production directory already exists but b1_complete.json does not\",\n        })\n\n    if b1_complete.exists():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_already_complete\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_complete.json already exists; S1 appears to be already completed for this run\",\n        })\n\n    result[\"ok\"] = len(errors) == 0\n    return result\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979073516}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc772651","parentId":"d310da41","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:33.746Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SYWuqmzm7OK1KhS5PpUm104G|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2f88193b05b1da7f814666e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef resolve_paths(run_root: str | Path, create_dirs: bool = True) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    inputs_root = b1_root / \"inputs\"\n    intermediate_root = b1_root / \"intermediate\"\n    scene_director_inputs = inputs_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_inputs = inputs_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    scene_director_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    checkpoints_root = run_root / \"checkpoints\"\n\n    if create_dirs:\n        for path_obj in [\n            b1_root,\n            inputs_root,\n            intermediate_root,\n            scene_director_inputs,\n            tts_polish_inputs,\n            scene_director_intermediate,\n            tts_polish_intermediate,\n            checkpoints_root,\n        ]:\n            path_obj.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    paths = {\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"b1_root\": str(b1_root),\n        \"inputs_root\": str(inputs_root),\n        \"intermediate_root\": str(intermediate_root),\n        \"scene_director_inputs_root\": str(scene_director_inputs),\n        \"tts_polish_inputs_root\": str(tts_polish_inputs),\n        \"scene_director_intermediate_root\": str(scene_director_intermediate),\n        \"tts_polish_intermediate_root\": str(tts_polish_intermediate),\n        \"screenplay_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay.json\"),\n        \"screenplay_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay_validation.json\"),\n        \"tts_polished_path\": str(b1_root / \"tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"polish_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"polish_validation.json\"),\n        \"scene_bible_path\": str(run_root / \"scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"checkpoints_root\": str(checkpoints_root),\n        \"b1_step1_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step1_screenplay.json\"),\n        \"b1_step2_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step3_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"b1_step4_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step5_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_complete.json\"),\n    }\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"created_dirs\": create_dirs,\n        \"paths\": paths,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979073631}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f68d8a6","parentId":"dc772651","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:33.855Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Jhb1o90ieG2Jy1S1wuK0iHgO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb2fc8193bebaf161f1f9a776","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches(\n    script_text: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    if not script_text or not script_text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan batches for empty script text\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_text = script_text.strip()\n    total_words = len(normalized_text.split())\n\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in re.split(r\"\\n\\s*\\n+\", normalized_text) if p.strip()]\n    if not paragraphs:\n        paragraphs = [normalized_text]\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_parts: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    running_word_index = 1\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_parts, current_word_count, running_word_index, batch_number\n        if not current_parts:\n            return\n        batch_text = \"\\n\\n\".join(current_parts).strip()\n        batch_words = len(batch_text.split())\n        start_word = running_word_index\n        end_word = running_word_index + batch_words - 1\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"sd_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"start_word\": start_word,\n                \"end_word\": end_word,\n                \"word_count\": batch_words,\n                \"text\": batch_text,\n            }\n        )\n        running_word_index = end_word + 1\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_parts = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for paragraph in paragraphs:\n        paragraph_words = len(paragraph.split())\n\n        # Oversized single paragraph: split by sentences as fallback\n        if paragraph_words > max_words_per_batch:\n            if current_parts:\n                flush_batch()\n            sentence_chunks = _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n                paragraph,\n                target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n                max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n            )\n            for chunk in sentence_chunks:\n                current_parts = [chunk]\n                current_word_count = len(chunk.split())\n                flush_batch()\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count == 0:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count = paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count + paragraph_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count < min_words_per_batch and current_word_count + paragraph_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_parts.append(paragraph)\n        current_word_count = paragraph_words\n\n    if current_parts:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if not batches:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"no_batches_generated\", \"message\": \"Batch planner failed to produce any batches\"})\n\n    if batches and len(batches[-1][\"text\"].split()) < min_words_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Final batch is smaller than recommended ({batches[-1]['word_count']} words)\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"total_words\": total_words,\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_words_per_batch\": target_words_per_batch,\n        \"min_words_per_batch\": min_words_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches_from_file(\n    script_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_script_file\", \"message\": f\"Script file not found: {script_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    text = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    result = plan_script_batches(\n        text,\n        target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n        min_words_per_batch=min_words_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"script_path\"] = str(script_path)\n    return result\n\n\ndef _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n    paragraph: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int,\n    max_words_per_batch: int,\n) -> list[str]:\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", paragraph) if s.strip()]\n    if not sentences:\n        return [paragraph]\n\n    chunks: list[str] = []\n    current: list[str] = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        sentence_words = len(sentence.split())\n\n        if current_words == 0:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words = sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n        current = [sentence]\n        current_words = sentence_words\n\n    if current:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n\n    return chunks\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979073747}}
{"type":"message","id":"39b044e5","parentId":"9f68d8a6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:33.972Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8tkx33PNXuiUyNMMq8fiVx8e|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3048193b0ef7345451db3d8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    account = job.get(\"account\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\")\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\")\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"start_word\": batch.get(\"start_word\"),\n            \"end_word\": batch.get(\"end_word\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n            \"text\": batch.get(\"text\"),\n        },\n        \"scene_words_range\": channel_config.get(\"scene_words_range\"),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes for screenplay generation.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve narrative meaning and order.\",\n                \"Return scene objects only for this batch.\",\n                \"Each scene must include scene_local_id, scene_title, scene_summary, narrative_function, narration_original, start_word, end_word, estimated_scene_word_count.\",\n                \"Use batch-relative word coordinates: the first word in this batch is word 1.\",\n                \"scene_local_id must be sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...).\",\n                \"Do not generate global scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not rewrite the story beyond what is needed for clean scene segmentation.\",\n                \"Do not do visual planning, asset planning, prompt writing, or shot design in this step.\",\n                \"Do not polish for TTS in this step.\",\n                \"Do not leave gaps or overlaps between scene text spans.\",\n                \"narration_original must match the original source text assigned to each scene.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_scene_director_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979073856}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e253be3","parentId":"39b044e5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_AVgo7CDwz027b1F9pTu0exoi|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3088193a9c2d0c09f419fe9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS = {\n    \"batch_id\",\n    \"operator\",\n    \"scenes\",\n}\n\nREQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_local_id\",\n    \"scene_title\",\n    \"scene_summary\",\n    \"narrative_function\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"start_word\",\n    \"end_word\",\n    \"estimated_scene_word_count\",\n}\n\nERROR_SEVERITY = {\n    \"payload_unreadable\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"output_unreadable\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"invalid_top_level_shape\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"empty_scenes\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"missing_required_field\": \"structural_patch\",\n    \"duplicate_scene_local_id\": \"structural_patch\",\n    \"non_sequential_scene_local_id\": \"structural_patch\",\n    \"invalid_scene_span\": \"batch_repair\",\n    \"scene_overlap_detected\": \"batch_repair\",\n    \"missing_coverage_detected\": \"batch_repair\",\n    \"duplicate_coverage_detected\": \"batch_repair\",\n    \"narration_source_mismatch\": \"batch_repair\",\n    \"estimated_word_count_mismatch\": \"structural_patch\",\n}\n\nCLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY = [\n    \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"batch_regenerate\",\n    \"batch_repair\",\n    \"structural_patch\",\n    \"ok\",\n]\n\n\ndef validate_scene_director_output(\n    *,\n    batch_payload_path: str | Path,\n    batch_output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    payload_result = _load_json(batch_payload_path, error_code=\"payload_unreadable\")\n    if not payload_result[\"ok\"]:\n        return _fatal_result(\n            batch_id=None,\n            errors=payload_result[\"errors\"],\n            warnings=warnings,\n        )\n\n    output_result = _load_json(batch_output_path, error_code=\"output_unreadable\")\n    if not output_result[\"ok\"]:\n        payload = payload_result[\"data\"]\n        batch_id = _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload)\n        return _fatal_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=output_result[\"errors\"],\n            warnings=warnings,\n        )\n\n    payload = payload_result[\"data\"]\n    output = output_result[\"data\"]\n\n    batch_id = _extract_batch_id(output) or _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload)\n\n    source_batch = payload.get(\"batch\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\n    if not isinstance(source_batch, dict):\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            message=\"Batch payload must include a 'batch' object\",\n        ))\n        return _finalize_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=errors,\n            warnings=warnings,\n            scenes=[],\n            source_tokens=[],\n            expected_batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\n        )\n\n    source_text = source_batch.get(\"text\")\n    if not isinstance(source_text, str) or not source_text.strip():\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            message=\"Batch payload must include non-empty batch.text\",\n        ))\n        return _finalize_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=errors,\n            warnings=warnings,\n            scenes=[],\n            source_tokens=[],\n            expected_batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\n        )\n\n    scenes = _validate_top_level_output(output, errors)\n    if not scenes:\n        return _finalize_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=errors,\n            warnings=warnings,\n            scenes=[],\n            source_tokens=_tokenize_text(source_text),\n            expected_batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\n        )\n\n    _validate_batch_id_match(output, payload, errors)\n    _validate_required_scene_fields(scenes, errors)\n    _validate_scene_local_ids(scenes, errors)\n    _validate_scene_spans(scenes, errors)\n\n    source_tokens = _tokenize_text(source_text)\n    _validate_coverage(scenes, len(source_tokens), errors)\n    _validate_narration_fidelity(scenes, source_tokens, errors)\n    _validate_estimated_word_counts(scenes, errors)\n\n    return _finalize_result(\n        batch_id=batch_id,\n        errors=errors,\n        warnings=warnings,\n        scenes=scenes,\n        source_tokens=source_tokens,\n        expected_batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\n    )\n\n\ndef _load_json(path: str | Path, *, error_code: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    path = Path(path)\n    try:\n        data = json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"errors\": [_error(error_code, f\"Failed to read JSON from {path}: {exc}\")],\n        }\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"data\": data,\n    }\n\n\ndef _validate_top_level_output(output: Any, errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    if not isinstance(output, dict):\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            message=\"Scene director output must be a JSON object\",\n        ))\n        return []\n\n    missing_top_level = sorted(REQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS - set(output.keys()))\n    if missing_top_level:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            message=f\"Output is missing top-level fields: {', '.join(missing_top_level)}\",\n        ))\n\n    scenes = output.get(\"scenes\")\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list):\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            message=\"Output 'scenes' must be a list\",\n        ))\n        return []\n\n    if not scenes:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"empty_scenes\",\n            message=\"Output 'scenes' list is empty\",\n        ))\n        return []\n\n    valid_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"missing_required_field\",\n                message=f\"Scene at index {index} must be an object\",\n                scene_ids=[f\"scene_index_{index}\"],\n            ))\n            continue\n        valid_scenes.append(scene)\n\n    return valid_scenes\n\n\ndef _validate_batch_id_match(output: dict[str, Any], payload: dict[str, Any], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    output_batch_id = _extract_batch_id(output)\n    expected_batch_id = _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload)\n    if output_batch_id and expected_batch_id and output_batch_id != expected_batch_id:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"missing_required_field\",\n            message=f\"Output batch_id '{output_batch_id}' does not match expected '{expected_batch_id}'\",\n        ))\n\n\ndef _validate_required_scene_fields(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    for scene in scenes:\n        missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n        if missing_fields:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"missing_required_field\",\n                message=(\n                    f\"Scene {scene.get('scene_local_id', '<unknown>')} is missing required fields: \"\n                    f\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                ),\n                scene_ids=[scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")],\n            ))\n\n\ndef _validate_scene_local_ids(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    seen: set[str] = set()\n    expected_index = 1\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_local_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_local_id, str):\n            continue\n\n        if scene_local_id in seen:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"duplicate_scene_local_id\",\n                message=f\"Duplicate scene_local_id detected: {scene_local_id}\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_local_id],\n            ))\n        else:\n            seen.add(scene_local_id)\n\n        expected_id = f\"scene_{expected_index:02d}\"\n        if scene_local_id != expected_id:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"non_sequential_scene_local_id\",\n                message=f\"Expected {expected_id} but found {scene_local_id}\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_local_id],\n            ))\n        expected_index += 1\n\n\ndef _validate_scene_spans(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    previous_end: int | None = None\n    previous_scene_id: str | None = None\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        start_word = scene.get(\"start_word\")\n        end_word = scene.get(\"end_word\")\n\n        if not isinstance(start_word, int) or not isinstance(end_word, int):\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"invalid_scene_span\",\n                message=f\"Scene {scene_id} must have integer start_word/end_word\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            continue\n\n        if start_word < 1 or end_word < 1 or start_word > end_word:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"invalid_scene_span\",\n                message=f\"Scene {scene_id} has invalid span ({start_word}-{end_word})\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            continue\n\n        if previous_end is not None and start_word <= previous_end:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"scene_overlap_detected\",\n                message=(\n                    f\"Scene {scene_id} overlaps with {previous_scene_id} \"\n                    f\"({start_word} <= previous end {previous_end})\"\n                ),\n                scene_ids=[previous_scene_id, scene_id],\n            ))\n\n        previous_end = end_word\n        previous_scene_id = scene_id\n\n\ndef _validate_coverage(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], source_word_count: int, errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    if source_word_count == 0:\n        return\n\n    coverage = [0] * source_word_count\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        start_word = scene.get(\"start_word\")\n        end_word = scene.get(\"end_word\")\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n\n        if not isinstance(start_word, int) or not isinstance(end_word, int):\n            continue\n        if start_word < 1 or end_word > source_word_count or start_word > end_word:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"invalid_scene_span\",\n                message=(\n                    f\"Scene {scene_id} span ({start_word}-{end_word}) is outside batch-relative range \"\n                    f\"1-{source_word_count}\"\n                ),\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            continue\n\n        for index in range(start_word - 1, end_word):\n            coverage[index] += 1\n\n    missing_ranges = _collect_ranges([i + 1 for i, count in enumerate(coverage) if count == 0])\n    duplicate_ranges = _collect_ranges([i + 1 for i, count in enumerate(coverage) if count > 1])\n\n    for start_word, end_word in missing_ranges:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"missing_coverage_detected\",\n            message=f\"Words {start_word}-{end_word} are not assigned to any scene\",\n        ))\n\n    for start_word, end_word in duplicate_ranges:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            code=\"duplicate_coverage_detected\",\n            message=f\"Words {start_word}-{end_word} are assigned to multiple scenes\",\n        ))\n\n\ndef _validate_narration_fidelity(\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    source_tokens: list[str],\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> None:\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        start_word = scene.get(\"start_word\")\n        end_word = scene.get(\"end_word\")\n        narration_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n\n        if not isinstance(start_word, int) or not isinstance(end_word, int):\n            continue\n        if not isinstance(narration_original, str):\n            continue\n        if start_word < 1 or end_word > len(source_tokens) or start_word > end_word:\n            continue\n\n        source_span_text = \" \".join(source_tokens[start_word - 1:end_word])\n        if _normalize_text(narration_original) != _normalize_text(source_span_text):\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"narration_source_mismatch\",\n                message=f\"Scene {scene_id} narration_original does not match source span {start_word}-{end_word}\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n\n\ndef _validate_estimated_word_counts(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        start_word = scene.get(\"start_word\")\n        end_word = scene.get(\"end_word\")\n        estimated_scene_word_count = scene.get(\"estimated_scene_word_count\")\n\n        if not isinstance(start_word, int) or not isinstance(end_word, int):\n            continue\n        if not isinstance(estimated_scene_word_count, int):\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"estimated_word_count_mismatch\",\n                message=f\"Scene {scene_id} must have integer estimated_scene_word_count\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            continue\n\n        actual_count = end_word - start_word + 1\n        if estimated_scene_word_count != actual_count:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                code=\"estimated_word_count_mismatch\",\n                message=(\n                    f\"Scene {scene_id} estimated_scene_word_count={estimated_scene_word_count} \"\n                    f\"but span implies {actual_count}\"\n                ),\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n\n\ndef _tokenize_text(text: str) -> list[str]:\n    normalized = _normalize_text(text)\n    if not normalized:\n        return []\n    return normalized.split(\" \")\n\n\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\n    text = text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n    text = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n    return text\n\n\ndef _collect_ranges(word_indices: list[int]) -> list[tuple[int, int]]:\n    if not word_indices:\n        return []\n\n    ranges: list[tuple[int, int]] = []\n    start = word_indices[0]\n    previous = word_indices[0]\n\n    for current in word_indices[1:]:\n        if current == previous + 1:\n            previous = current\n            continue\n        ranges.append((start, previous))\n        start = current\n        previous = current\n\n    ranges.append((start, previous))\n    return ranges\n\n\ndef _extract_batch_id(output: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\n    batch_id = output.get(\"batch_id\")\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\n\n\ndef _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\n    batch = payload.get(\"batch\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\n    if not isinstance(batch, dict):\n        return None\n    batch_id = batch.get(\"batch_id\")\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\n\n\ndef _error(\n    code: str,\n    message: str,\n    *,\n    scene_ids: list[str | None] | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    clean_scene_ids = [scene_id for scene_id in (scene_ids or []) if scene_id]\n    payload: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"code\": code,\n        \"message\": message,\n    }\n    if clean_scene_ids:\n        payload[\"scene_ids\"] = clean_scene_ids\n    return payload\n\n\ndef _fatal_result(\n    *,\n    batch_id: str | None,\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"approved_for_merge\": False,\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"classification\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"stats\": {\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"source_word_count\": 0,\n            \"covered_word_count\": 0,\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef _finalize_result(\n    *,\n    batch_id: str | None,\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    source_tokens: list[str],\n    expected_batch_id: str | None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    classification = _classify_errors(errors)\n    covered_word_count = _compute_covered_word_count(scenes, len(source_tokens))\n\n    if batch_id is None:\n        batch_id = expected_batch_id\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": classification == \"ok\",\n        \"approved_for_merge\": classification == \"ok\",\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"classification\": classification,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"stats\": {\n            \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n            \"source_word_count\": len(source_tokens),\n            \"covered_word_count\": covered_word_count,\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef _classify_errors(errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n    if not errors:\n        return \"ok\"\n\n    severities = [ERROR_SEVERITY.get(error.get(\"code\"), \"fatal_contract_error\") for error in errors]\n\n    if \"fatal_contract_error\" in severities:\n        return \"fatal_contract_error\"\n\n    repair_like_count = sum(1 for severity in severities if severity == \"batch_repair\")\n    if repair_like_count >= 3:\n        return \"batch_regenerate\"\n    if repair_like_count >= 1:\n        return \"batch_repair\"\n    if \"structural_patch\" in severities:\n        return \"structural_patch\"\n\n    for classification in CLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY:\n        if classification in severities:\n            return classification\n\n    return \"fatal_contract_error\"\n\n\ndef _compute_covered_word_count(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], source_word_count: int) -> int:\n    if source_word_count <= 0:\n        return 0\n\n    covered: set[int] = set()\n    for scene in scenes:\n        start_word = scene.get(\"start_word\")\n        end_word = scene.get(\"end_word\")\n        if not isinstance(start_word, int) or not isinstance(end_word, int):\n            continue\n        if start_word < 1 or end_word < 1 or start_word > end_word:\n            continue\n        for index in range(max(1, start_word), min(source_word_count, end_word) + 1):\n            covered.add(index)\n\n    return len(covered)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979073973}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e748353","parentId":"0e253be3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.217Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_RGXdP7x6UBZI5lFKYZeLeJrp|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31081938d2181d71dfe8f5d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_local_id\",\n    \"scene_title\",\n    \"scene_summary\",\n    \"narrative_function\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"start_word\",\n    \"end_word\",\n    \"estimated_scene_word_count\",\n}\n\n\ndef merge_screenplay_batches(\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\n    *,\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\n    if not ordered_files:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"screenplay\": {\"scenes\": []},\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"no_batch_files\", \"message\": \"No scene_director batch files provided\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\n        if not file_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_batch_file\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch output file not found: {file_path}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to parse batch file {file_path}: {exc}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        batch_id = payload.get(\"batch_id\")\n        scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if not isinstance(scenes, list):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if not scenes:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\",\n            })\n\n        loaded_batches.append({\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"file_path\": str(file_path),\n            \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        })\n\n        for index_in_batch, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"invalid_scene_payload\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\",\n                })\n                continue\n\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n            if missing_fields:\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"missing_scene_fields\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"Batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene {index_in_batch} \"\n                        f\"is missing required fields: {', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n                continue\n\n            merged_scenes.append(\n                {\n                    \"source_batch_id\": batch_id,\n                    \"source_batch_scene_index\": index_in_batch,\n                    \"source_scene_local_id\": scene.get(\"scene_local_id\"),\n                    **scene,\n                }\n            )\n\n    for global_index, scene in enumerate(merged_scenes, start=1):\n        scene[\"scene_id\"] = f\"scene_{global_index:03d}\"\n\n    screenplay = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"scenes\": merged_scenes,\n    }\n\n    if output_path is not None:\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(screenplay, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(loaded_batches),\n        \"screenplay\": screenplay,\n        \"loaded_batches\": loaded_batches,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074091}}
{"type":"message","id":"3dae5dfc","parentId":"8e748353","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.333Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_26O0DbhWmF4H4QEtDb4NrOEn|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31481938c89dc69ce96924f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches(\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list) or not scenes:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_screenplay\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan polish batches without screenplay scenes\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_scene_ids: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def scene_word_count(scene: dict[str, Any]) -> int:\n        return len(str(scene.get(\"narration_original\", \"\")).split())\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_scene_ids, current_word_count, batch_number\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            return\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"tp_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"scene_ids\": current_scene_ids[:],\n                \"scene_count\": len(current_scene_ids),\n                \"word_count\": current_word_count,\n            }\n        )\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_scene_ids = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n        if not scene_id:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_scene_id\",\n                \"message\": \"Screenplay scene is missing 'scene_id' required for polish batching\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        words = scene_word_count(scene)\n\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = words\n            continue\n\n        next_scene_count = len(current_scene_ids) + 1\n        next_word_count = current_word_count + words\n\n        if next_scene_count <= target_scenes_per_batch and next_word_count <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        if len(current_scene_ids) < min_scenes_per_batch and next_scene_count <= max_scenes_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n        current_word_count = words\n\n    if current_scene_ids:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if batches and batches[-1][\"scene_count\"] < min_scenes_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": (\n                    f\"Final TTS polish batch is smaller than recommended \"\n                    f\"({batches[-1]['scene_count']} scenes)\"\n                ),\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_scenes_per_batch\": target_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"min_scenes_per_batch\": min_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_scenes_per_batch\": max_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches_from_file(\n    screenplay_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    screenplay_path = Path(screenplay_path)\n    if not screenplay_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_screenplay_file\", \"message\": f\"Screenplay file not found: {screenplay_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    screenplay = json.loads(screenplay_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    result = plan_tts_polish_batches(\n        screenplay,\n        target_scenes_per_batch=target_scenes_per_batch,\n        min_scenes_per_batch=min_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_scenes_per_batch=max_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"screenplay_path\"] = str(screenplay_path)\n    return result\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074217}}
{"type":"message","id":"b747646f","parentId":"3dae5dfc","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OqaPMtpF9vZ9uVWahs4bMgwh|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb31c81939fdd9e35503d4f44","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    scene_ids = batch.get(\"scene_ids\", [])\n    scene_map = {\n        scene.get(\"scene_id\"): scene\n        for scene in screenplay.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n    }\n    scenes = [scene_map[scene_id] for scene_id in scene_ids if scene_id in scene_map]\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\"),\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"scene_ids\": scene_ids,\n            \"scene_count\": batch.get(\"scene_count\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n        },\n        \"tts_polish_rules\": channel_config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", []),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Polish the narration text for TTS without changing meaning.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve scene order and scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not remove the original narration layer.\",\n                \"Return narration_tts for each scene.\",\n                \"Keep meaning intact while improving speakability.\",\n                \"Return changes metadata for each scene when possible.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_tts_polish_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074334}}
{"type":"message","id":"3486de4d","parentId":"b747646f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KDUEnch9vG5UoN7D3F2PpP6v|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb3248193953ae5b05c588d50","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_id\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"narration_tts\",\n}\n\n\ndef merge_tts_polish_batches(\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\n    *,\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    ordered_scene_ids = [scene.get(\"scene_id\") for scene in scenes if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")]\n\n    if not ordered_files:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"tts_polished\": {\"scenes\": []},\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"no_batch_files\", \"message\": \"No tts_polish batch files provided\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    polish_map: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {}\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\n        if not file_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_batch_file\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file not found: {file_path}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to parse polish batch file {file_path}: {exc}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        batch_id = payload.get(\"batch_id\")\n        batch_scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if not isinstance(batch_scenes, list):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if not batch_scenes:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\",\n            })\n\n        loaded_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n                \"file_path\": str(file_path),\n                \"scene_count\": len(batch_scenes),\n            }\n        )\n\n        for scene in batch_scenes:\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"invalid_scene_payload\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\",\n                })\n                continue\n\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n            if missing_fields:\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"missing_polish_fields\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene is missing required fields: \"\n                        f\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n                continue\n\n            scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n            if scene_id in polish_map:\n                warnings.append({\n                    \"code\": \"duplicate_scene_polish\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Scene {scene_id} appeared more than once across polish batches; latest entry kept\",\n                })\n            polish_map[scene_id] = scene\n\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for scene_id in ordered_scene_ids:\n        polished_scene = polish_map.get(scene_id)\n        if not polished_scene:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_polish_scene\",\n                \"message\": f\"No polish output found for screenplay scene {scene_id}\",\n            })\n            continue\n        merged_scenes.append(polished_scene)\n\n    tts_polished = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"scenes\": merged_scenes,\n    }\n\n    if output_path is not None:\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(tts_polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(loaded_batches),\n        \"tts_polished\": tts_polished,\n        \"loaded_batches\": loaded_batches,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074446}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc7dbbc3","parentId":"3486de4d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ASeaM0fKIW5hPnJg4o059ART|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb328819387882bc8001b0632","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nMAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT = 3\n\n\nFAIL_FAST_TYPES = {\n    \"preflight_structural_failure\",\n    \"missing_required_input\",\n    \"invalid_job_json\",\n    \"invalid_pipeline_state\",\n    \"empty_script\",\n    \"b1_already_complete\",\n}\n\nOPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"operator_timeout\",\n    \"operator_no_output\",\n    \"operator_output_missing\",\n    \"operator_invalid_json\",\n    \"operator_empty_output\",\n    \"operator_malformed_output\",\n}\n\nMERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES = {\n    \"missing_batch_file\",\n    \"invalid_batch_json\",\n    \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n    \"missing_scene_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_scene\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES = {\n    \"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n    \"coverage_too_low\",\n    \"missing_words_detected\",\n    \"extra_words_detected\",\n    \"duplicate_scene_content\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES = {\n    \"polish_validation_failed\",\n    \"words_eaten\",\n    \"meaning_drift\",\n    \"unauthorized_additions\",\n}\n\nBUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"scene_bible_write_failed\",\n    \"scene_bible_schema_invalid\",\n    \"scene_bible_builder_failed\",\n}\n\nINFRA_FAILURE_TYPES = {\n    \"filesystem_write_error\",\n    \"permission_error\",\n    \"disk_full\",\n}\n\n\ndef plan_retry(\n    *,\n    step_name: str,\n    failure_type: str,\n    retry_count: int,\n    affected_batches: list[str] | None = None,\n    affected_scenes: list[str] | None = None,\n    max_retries: int = MAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    affected_batches = affected_batches or []\n    affected_scenes = affected_scenes or []\n\n    if retry_count >= max_retries:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Retry limit reached for step '{step_name}' ({retry_count}/{max_retries})\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in FAIL_FAST_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Structural failure '{failure_type}' should fail fast\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in OPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected batches\",\n                next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun step\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in MERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Merge issue '{failure_type}' traced to missing/invalid batch outputs\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_affected_batches_then_merge\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Merge failure '{failure_type}' cannot be safely retried without affected batch mapping\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected screenplay batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_director\"],\n            reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun screenplay step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected polish batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"tts_polish\"],\n            reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun TTS polish step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in BUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_bible_builder\"],\n            reason=f\"Scene bible build failure '{failure_type}' — rerun builder step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_bible_builder\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in INFRA_FAILURE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Infrastructure failure '{failure_type}' — allow one more controlled retry\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    return _decision(\n        retry=False,\n        retry_mode=\"abort\",\n        targets=[],\n        reason=f\"Unknown failure type '{failure_type}' — abort by default for safety\",\n        next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n    )\n\n\ndef _decision(\n    *,\n    retry: bool,\n    retry_mode: str,\n    targets: list[str],\n    reason: str,\n    next_action: str,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"retry\": retry,\n        \"retry_mode\": retry_mode,\n        \"targets\": targets,\n        \"reason\": reason,\n        \"next_action\": next_action,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074561}}
{"type":"message","id":"61ae062d","parentId":"cc7dbbc3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.802Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_rTt8G29dBQ4Xwzf13ZbEdVCe|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb32c8193a71d76140623f218","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_batch_schedule(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if concurrency_cap < 1:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"operator\": operator_name,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"invalid_concurrency_cap\", \"message\": \"concurrency_cap must be >= 1\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for batch in batches:\n        normalized_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n                \"input_path\": batch.get(\"input_path\"),\n                \"output_path\": batch.get(\"output_path\"),\n                \"status\": batch.get(\"status\", \"queued\"),\n            }\n        )\n\n    waves: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for i in range(0, len(normalized_batches), concurrency_cap):\n        wave_batches = normalized_batches[i : i + concurrency_cap]\n        waves.append(\n            {\n                \"wave_index\": len(waves) + 1,\n                \"batch_ids\": [b.get(\"batch_id\") for b in wave_batches],\n                \"batch_count\": len(wave_batches),\n                \"batches\": wave_batches,\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(normalized_batches),\n        \"wave_count\": len(waves),\n        \"waves\": waves,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef summarize_batch_execution(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n    execution_results: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    completed_batches: list[str] = []\n    failed_batches: list[str] = []\n    pending_batches: list[str] = []\n    output_files: list[str] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    for result in execution_results:\n        batch_id = result.get(\"batch_id\")\n        status = result.get(\"status\", \"unknown\")\n\n        if status == \"completed\":\n            completed_batches.append(batch_id)\n            if result.get(\"output_path\"):\n                output_files.append(result[\"output_path\"])\n        elif status == \"failed\":\n            failed_batches.append(batch_id)\n        else:\n            pending_batches.append(batch_id)\n\n        for error in result.get(\"errors\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(error, dict):\n                errors.append(error)\n        for warning in result.get(\"warnings\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(warning, dict):\n                warnings.append(warning)\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(failed_batches) == 0,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(execution_results),\n        \"completed_batches\": completed_batches,\n        \"failed_batches\": failed_batches,\n        \"pending_batches\": pending_batches,\n        \"output_files\": output_files,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074671}}
{"type":"message","id":"5282be34","parentId":"61ae062d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:44:34.918Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d3PkUcYeYuuNQR5E6RpXvyg1|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc07ffb33081939ef5936027f1a8aa","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef summarize_s1_result(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    screenplay_result: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n    polish_result: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n    scene_bible_path: str | Path | None = None,\n    checkpoints_written: list[str] | None = None,\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] | None = None,\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    screenplay_result = screenplay_result or {}\n    polish_result = polish_result or {}\n    checkpoints_written = checkpoints_written or []\n    warnings = warnings or []\n    errors = errors or []\n\n    screenplay_scene_count = screenplay_result.get(\"scene_count\", 0)\n    polish_scene_count = polish_result.get(\"scene_count\", 0)\n    effective_scene_count = screenplay_scene_count or polish_scene_count\n\n    success = len(errors) == 0 and bool(scene_bible_path)\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": success,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"status\": \"s1_complete\" if success else \"s1_failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"b1_complete\" if success else \"b1_failed\",\n        \"screenplay_scene_count\": screenplay_scene_count,\n        \"polish_scene_count\": polish_scene_count,\n        \"scene_count\": effective_scene_count,\n        \"screenplay_batch_count\": screenplay_result.get(\"batch_count\", 0),\n        \"polish_batch_count\": polish_result.get(\"batch_count\", 0),\n        \"scene_bible_path\": str(scene_bible_path) if scene_bible_path else None,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\" if success else \"blocked\",\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979074802}}
{"type":"message","id":"7116c516","parentId":"5282be34","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:45:48.704Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. E sim: **a opção 2 é a correcta**. Com o estado que estou a ver agora, faz sentido o `sm_s1_pre_production` virar o runtime canónico e o `s1_start.py` ser tratado como bootstrap/transição — não como cérebro definitivo.\n\nVou te devolver agora o **workflow exacto do supervisor como está configurado hoje**, depois a avaliação das skills, e por fim a resposta sobre **quais precisam de contratos específicos**.\n\n---\n\n# 1. Workflow exacto do supervisor hoje\n\n## Papel do supervisor\nO `sm_s1_pre_production` está muito bem definido em docs/workspace:\n\n- recebe uma run `ready_for_s1`\n- coordena o sector até produzir:\n  - `screenplay.json`\n  - `screenplay_validation.json`\n  - `tts_polished.json`\n  - `polish_validation.json`\n  - `scene_bible.json`\n  - checkpoints `b1_*`\n- **não** gera semanticamente por conta própria\n- **não** absorve lógica determinística que já está em skill\n- **não** avança para S2/S3\n- é explicitamente um **supervisor LLM/OpenClaw**\n\nIsto está sólido.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow canónico actual do supervisor\nHoje, pela combinação de:\n- `WORKFLOW.md`\n- `STATE.md`\n- `TOOLS.md`\n- `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- e as supervisor skills existentes\n\no fluxo exacto é este:\n\n### Fase 0 — Entrada / gate\n### 1. `s1_preflight_checker`\nO supervisor valida se a run está pronta para entrar no S1:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n- channel config `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n\nTambém:\n- lê `job_id/account/language`\n- mede tamanho do script\n- avisa se script está muito curto/muito longo\n- falha se `b1_complete.json` já existir\n\n**Leitura:** este é o gate estrutural do sector. Correcto.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `s1_paths_resolver`\nResolve e cria, se necessário, a estrutura canónica do S1:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- output paths canónicos\n- checkpoint paths `b1_*`\n\n**Leitura:** isto tira path logic do supervisor. Correcto.\n\n---\n\n## Fase 1 — Screenplay\n\n### 3. `script_batch_planner`\nDivide `script_raw` em batches `sd_###`:\n- target ~750 palavras\n- min 450\n- max 950\n- prefere parágrafos\n- cai para split por frases em parágrafos grandes\n- preserva ordem\n- devolve:\n  - `batch_id`\n  - `start_word`\n  - `end_word`\n  - `word_count`\n  - `text`\n\n**Leitura:** muito bom. Isto está bem desenhado.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `scene_director_io_adapter`\nPara cada batch `sd_###`, o supervisor constrói um payload explícito para o operator `scene_director` com:\n- `job_id/account/language`\n- `run_root`\n- batch metadata\n- batch text\n- `scene_words_range` do channel config\n- style context\n- instruções explícitas\n- `output_path`\n\n**Leitura:** esta peça é central e está no sítio certo.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `operator_batch_scheduler`\nO supervisor não deve disparar batches soltos sem controlo.\nO scheduler:\n- recebe batches preparados\n- aplica `scene_director_concurrency_cap`\n- agrupa em waves\n- suporta summary dos resultados\n\nCap inicial documentada:\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n\n**Mas atenção a uma nuance importante:**\no scheduler **não invoca operators por si só ainda**.  \nEle só:\n- planeia waves\n- resume execução\n\nOu seja:\n> ainda falta a camada exacta de “como o supervisor chama o operator OpenClaw batch por batch” dentro desse plano.\n\nIsto não invalida a arquitectura, mas é uma nuance real.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Execução do `scene_director`\nPelo contrato:\n- o supervisor prepara payload\n- o `op_s1_scene_director` lê esse payload\n- produz output batch-level JSON\n- escreve no `output_path`\n\n### 7. `scene_director_output_validator`\nDepois de cada batch, o supervisor valida **antes de qualquer merge**:\n- top-level shape\n- required fields\n- `scene_local_id` sequencing\n- spans\n- overlap\n- missing coverage\n- duplicate coverage\n- `narration_original` fidelity contra o source batch\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\nE ele classifica erros em:\n- `fatal_contract_error`\n- `structural_patch`\n- `batch_repair`\n- `batch_regenerate`\n- `ok`\n\n**Leitura:** esta skill está excelente. É uma das mais importantes do supervisor e está muito alinhada com a arquitectura desejada.\n\n---\n\n### 8. `retry_planner` para failures do scene_director\nSe houver failure:\n- o supervisor não improvisa\n- chama `retry_planner`\n\nO planner hoje decide:\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nCom mapeamentos por tipo de falha:\n- structural/fail-fast\n- operator retryable\n- merge recovery\n- semantic screenplay\n- semantic polish\n- builder retryable\n- infra\n\n**Leitura:** boa base, mas ainda com uma nuance:\nele é mais um **decision mapper por failure_type** do que um planner muito contextual/inteligente.  \nEstá bom como v1, mas ainda pode amadurecer.\n\n---\n\n### 9. `screenplay_merger`\nSó batches aprovados entram aqui.\nEle:\n- lê batch outputs ordenados\n- valida required fields mínimos\n- concatena em ordem\n- adiciona:\n  - `source_batch_id`\n  - `source_batch_scene_index`\n  - `source_scene_local_id`\n- reatribui `scene_id = scene_###`\n- escreve `screenplay.json`\n\n**Leitura:** correcto e muito saudável estruturalmente.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Validate screenplay\nAqui há uma nuance importante:\nno workflow e no contract aparece **“Validate screenplay”**, mas no conjunto de `supervisor_skills` que li **não existe uma skill supervisor-specific para isso**, porque a validação está em:\n- `runtime/s1/screenplay_validator.py`\n\nEntão hoje o supervisor provavelmente depende de um componente shared/outside `supervisor_skills` para esta etapa.\n\n**Isto não é errado.**  \nMas convém ficar explícito no contrato/workspace do supervisor que:\n- `screenplay_validator` é uma **shared deterministic sector component**\n- não uma `supervisor_skill/` local\n\n---\n\n## Fase 2 — TTS Polish\n\n### 11. `tts_polish_batch_planner`\nRecebe `screenplay.json` e agrupa cenas em batches `tp_###`:\n- target 5 cenas\n- min 3\n- max 6\n- max 350 palavras\n- preserva ordem\n\n**Leitura:** bom e coerente.\n\n---\n\n### 12. `tts_polish_io_adapter`\nConstrói payload explícito para `tts_polish` com:\n- contexto da run/job\n- metadata do batch\n- `tts_polish_rules`\n- style context\n- instruções\n- cenas daquele batch\n- `output_path`\n\n**Leitura:** também está no sítio certo.\n\n---\n\n### 13. `operator_batch_scheduler`\nAgora para `tts_polish`, com:\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\nMesmo caveat:\n- scheduler planeia\n- não invoca por si só\n\n---\n\n### 14. Execução do `tts_polish`\nPelo contract:\n- operator recebe batch\n- preserva `scene_id`\n- preserva `narration_original`\n- devolve `narration_tts`\n- opcional `changes`\n\n---\n\n### 15. `tts_polish_merger`\nLê batch outputs, reconstrói `tts_polished.json` em ordem do screenplay:\n- exige:\n  - `scene_id`\n  - `narration_original`\n  - `narration_tts`\n- usa screenplay order como sequência canónica\n- detecta missing scenes\n- avisa duplicações\n\n**Leitura:** correcto.\n\n---\n\n### 16. Validate polish\nOutra nuance importante:\nno workflow aparece “Validate polish”, mas dentro de `supervisor_skills/` não há um `tts_polish_output_validator.py`.\n\nHoje isso parece estar distribuído entre:\n- `runtime/s1/polish_validator.py`\n- e possivelmente o layer/agent de `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n- além dos contracts:\n  - `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md`\n  - `s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer_contract.md`\n\nEntão aqui há um ponto de atenção real:\n> o loop exacto de validação do polish ainda está menos consolidado no código visível do que o loop do scene_director\n\n---\n\n## Fase 3 — Fecho do sector\n\n### 17. `scene_bible_builder`\nEstá fora de `supervisor_skills`, em `runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py`\n- usa outputs anteriores\n- gera `scene_bible.json`\n\n### 18. `scene_bible_schema_validator`\nValida schema da bible.\n\n### 19. `checkpoint_writer`\nEscreve checkpoints `b1_*`.\n\n### 20. `s1_result_summarizer`\nAgrega:\n- scene counts\n- batch counts\n- `scene_bible_path`\n- checkpoints\n- warnings/errors\n- `status`\n- `next_step`\n\nSe success:\n- `status = s1_complete`\n- `current_stage = b1_complete`\n- `next_step = ready_for_s2_and_s3`\n\n---\n\n# 2. As skills do supervisor estão adequadas e disponíveis?\n\n## Resposta curta\n**Sim, no geral estão bastante adequadas e disponíveis.**  \nO supervisor está surpreendentemente bem estruturado.\n\nMas há alguns pontos de ajuste/documentação que eu separaria.\n\n---\n\n## Skills que estão boas e coerentes\nEstas estão fortes:\n\n- `s1_preflight_checker.py`\n- `s1_paths_resolver.py`\n- `script_batch_planner.py`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter.py`\n- `scene_director_output_validator.py`\n- `screenplay_merger.py`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner.py`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter.py`\n- `tts_polish_merger.py`\n- `retry_planner.py`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler.py`\n- `s1_result_summarizer.py`\n\n### As mais fortes estruturalmente\nSe eu destacar as melhores:\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n\nEstas já estão muito alinhadas com o desenho canónico.\n\n---\n\n## Onde vejo nuances/gaps\n\n### A. O scheduler ainda não “fecha a última milha”\n`operator_batch_scheduler`:\n- planeia waves\n- resume resultados\n\nMas explicitamente:\n- **não invoca OpenClaw operators ainda**\n\nEntão hoje ele é mais:\n- scheduler declarativo\ndo que\n- executor supervisorial completo\n\nIsto é aceitável, mas precisa de ficar cristalino na doc.\n\n---\n\n### B. O loop do screenplay está mais fechado que o loop do polish\nPara `scene_director`, tens:\n- contract\n- operator workspace\n- io_adapter\n- output_validator\n- merger\n- retry mapping\n\nPara `tts_polish`, tens:\n- contract\n- workspace\n- io_adapter\n- merger\n- retry mapping\n\nMas não vi equivalente claro a:\n- `tts_polish_output_validator.py`\n\nE isso importa porque hoje a validação do polish parece mais difusa entre:\n- `polish_validator.py`\n- semantic reviewer\n- contracts separados\n\nEntão aqui a arquitectura ainda está menos “clean” do que no fluxo do scene_director.\n\n---\n\n### C. O `retry_planner` está funcional, mas ainda genérico\nEle está bom como v1.\nMas hoje ele depende muito de `failure_type` bem mapeado à mão.\n\nPode ficar melhor depois com:\n- richer failure payload\n- distinction entre `repair` vs `regenerate`\n- scene subset vs batch subset no polish\n- handling do semantic reviewer\n\nNão é bloqueador agora, mas vale notar.\n\n---\n\n### D. Algumas shared pieces importantes ainda não estão claramente “classificadas” na documentação do supervisor\nFora de `supervisor_skills`, o supervisor depende de:\n- `screenplay_validator.py`\n- `polish_validator.py`\n- `scene_bible_builder.py`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n- `checkpoint_writer.py`\n\nEssas peças existem, mas a documentação do supervisor podia separar explicitamente:\n\n### Supervisor-owned skills\n- as de `supervisor_skills/`\n\n### Shared deterministic sector components\n- validators\n- builder\n- schema validator\n- checkpoint writer\n\nHoje isso está implícito demais.\n\n---\n\n# 3. Essas skills precisam de contratos específicos ou não?\n\n## Resposta curta\n**Nem todas precisam do mesmo nível de contrato.**\n\nA regra boa aqui é:\n\n### Precisam de contrato específico formal\nAs skills que fazem **ponte de interface**, **produzem artefactos canónicos**, ou **tomam decisões supervisoriais importantes**.\n\n### Não precisam necessariamente de contrato dedicado extenso\nAs skills mais internas/determinísticas e de utilidade, desde que:\n- estejam simples\n- tenham shape de I/O estável\n- estejam bem referidas no contrato do supervisor\n\n---\n\n## Eu separaria assim\n\n## A. DEVEM ter contrato específico próprio\nEstas eu acho que valem contrato próprio ou mini-contract explícito:\n\n### 1. `scene_director_io_adapter`\nPorque define a ponte supervisor → operator.  \nÉ uma interface crítica.\n\n### 2. `scene_director_output_validator`\nPorque é gate de aceitação antes do merge.  \nMuito importante.\n\n### 3. `screenplay_merger`\nPorque escreve artefacto canónico central (`screenplay.json`).\n\n### 4. `tts_polish_io_adapter`\nPorque define a ponte supervisor → operator de polish.\n\n### 5. `tts_polish_merger`\nPorque escreve artefacto canónico central (`tts_polished.json`).\n\n### 6. `retry_planner`\nPorque influencia lógica de recuperação/escalation.\nMesmo sendo determinístico, ele codifica política.\n\n### 7. `operator_batch_scheduler`\nPorque define semântica operacional de paralelismo controlado.\n\nEssas 7 eu trataria como componentes com contratos explícitos.\n\n---\n\n## B. PODEM viver bem só dentro do contrato do supervisor por enquanto\nEstas podem ficar documentadas como seções do `s1_supervisor_contract.md` sem necessariamente virar um `.md` próprio já:\n\n### 1. `s1_preflight_checker`\nJá está bem documentada no contrato do supervisor.\n\n### 2. `s1_paths_resolver`\nTambém.\n\n### 3. `script_batch_planner`\nTambém.\n\n### 4. `tts_polish_batch_planner`\nTambém.\n\n### 5. `s1_result_summarizer`\nTambém.\n\nEssas têm I/O relativamente simples e baixo risco de ambiguidade.\n\n---\n\n## C. Componentes shared que eu documentaria, mas fora da pasta de supervisor_skills\nEstes deveriam ter contrato/documentação própria, mas como **shared runtime components**, não como supervisor skills:\n\n- `screenplay_validator.py`\n- `polish_validator.py`\n- `scene_bible_builder.py`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n- `checkpoint_writer.py`\n\nEspecialmente:\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\nporque são centrais no fecho do sector.\n\n---\n\n# 4. Minha avaliação do supervisor, objectivamente\n\n## O que está muito bom\n- papel do supervisor está claro\n- workflow está claro\n- naming canónico está claro\n- inputs/outputs do sector estão claros\n- scene_director loop está muito bem desenhado\n- uso de skills determinísticas está no sítio certo\n- paralelismo controlado está pensado do jeito certo\n- o supervisor não está a tentar “ser tudo”\n\n## O que precisa de ajuste / clarificação\n1. deixar explícito que **opção 2 é a canónica**\n   - `sm_s1_pre_production` = runtime canónico\n   - `s1_start.py` = transição/bootstrap\n\n2. documentar melhor a distinção entre:\n   - `supervisor_skills`\n   - shared deterministic sector components\n\n3. fechar o loop do polish com a mesma nitidez do loop do scene_director\n\n4. decidir se certas skills merecem contrato dedicado próprio\n\n---\n\n# 5. Recomendação concreta\nSe formos arrumar isto do jeito ideal, eu faria agora esta sequência:\n\n### Supervisor docs first\n1. ajustar `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n   - tornar explícito que o supervisor OpenClaw é o runtime canónico\n   - rebaixar `s1_start.py` a bootstrap/transição\n   - separar `supervisor_skills` vs `shared sector components`\n\n2. criar contratos dedicados para:\n   - `scene_director_io_adapter`\n   - `scene_director_output_validator`\n   - `screenplay_merger`\n   - `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n   - `tts_polish_merger`\n   - `retry_planner`\n   - `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n3. depois revisar o loop do polish\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu posso já fazer o próximo passo de forma útil e concreta:\n\n**A)** escrever aqui um **mapa de autoridade exacto do supervisor**  \nou  \n**B)** começar a **propor os ajustes específicos no `s1_supervisor_contract.md`** antes de mexer em mais nada\n\nEu recomendo **B agora**, porque fixa a camada-mãe primeiro.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc080651c08193bd0bdd583c850d2e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":74959,"output":3896,"cacheRead":14848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93703,"cost":{"input":0.18739750000000002,"output":0.05844,"cacheRead":0.003712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2495495}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774979075588,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc08043be48193a261cd5f88760e98"}}
{"type":"message","id":"60ae51be","parentId":"7116c516","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:48:09.376Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-31 14:48 GMT-3] ta, e ai o que tu sugere que façamos entào pra garantir que o S1 ta 100% confgiruado perfeitamente com agentes openclaw?"}],"timestamp":1774979289298}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1726912","parentId":"60ae51be","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:48:38.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Eu sugiro um caminho **muito disciplinado e em camadas**, para não repetir o erro de avançar execução sem fixar a topologia do sistema.\n\n## O objectivo real\nNão é só “fazer o S1 funcionar”.\n\nÉ garantir que o S1 fique:\n- **canonicamente OpenClaw-native**\n- com autoridade clara\n- com contratos claros\n- com runtime claro\n- com workspaces alinhados\n- sem drift entre doc, agent e implementação\n\n---\n\n# O plano que eu recomendo\n\n## Fase 1 — Fixar a constituição do S1\nAntes de mexer em mais implementação, fechar por escrito a camada-mãe.\n\n### 1. Tornar explícito que:\n- **`sm_s1_pre_production` é o runtime canónico**\n- `s1_start.py` é apenas:\n  - bootstrap\n  - compat layer\n  - transição temporária\n  - ou eventual entry shim\n\nIsto precisa de ficar inequívoco no contrato do supervisor.\n\n### 2. Separar formalmente 3 classes de componentes\nHoje isso está meio implícito. Eu formalizaria assim:\n\n#### A. Supervisor\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n- decide ordem, retries, escalation, accept/reject, completion\n\n#### B. Operators OpenClaw\n- `op_s1_scene_director`\n- `op_s1_tts_polish`\n- `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n#### C. Deterministic components\nDois subgrupos:\n- **supervisor skills**\n- **shared runtime components**\n\nIsso limpa muita confusão.\n\n---\n\n## Fase 2 — Fechar o mapa de autoridade\nEu faria um documento simples, mas duro, respondendo:\n\n### Para cada responsabilidade:\n- quem decide?\n- quem executa?\n- quem valida?\n- quem escreve?\n- quem retria?\n- quem faz escalate?\n\nExemplo:\n\n- **preflight** → skill\n- **path resolution** → skill\n- **script batching** → skill\n- **scene generation** → operator\n- **scene batch validation** → skill\n- **screenplay merge** → skill\n- **screenplay global validation** → shared deterministic validator\n- **polish generation** → operator\n- **polish semantic review** → operator especializado, só quando necessário\n- **polish global validation** → shared validator\n- **scene bible build** → shared deterministic component\n- **checkpoint writing** → shared deterministic component\n- **retry decision** → supervisor via retry_planner\n- **sector completion/failure** → supervisor\n\nSe isso não estiver cristalino, o S1 nunca vai ficar “100%”.\n\n---\n\n## Fase 3 — Fechar contratos críticos\nNem tudo precisa de contrato próprio, mas o que é interface crítica precisa.\n\n### Eu faria contratos específicos para:\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### E deixaria no contrato do supervisor:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### E documentaria como shared sector components:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\n---\n\n## Fase 4 — Auditar agent-by-agent contra o contrato\nAí sim fazemos a revisão profunda.\n\n### Ordem ideal:\n1. **Supervisor**\n2. `op_s1_scene_director`\n3. `op_s1_tts_polish`\n4. `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\nPara cada um:\n- missão\n- boundaries\n- inputs\n- outputs\n- o que não faz\n- relação com supervisor\n- relação com skills\n- artefactos que lê/escreve\n- se o workspace está alinhado com o contrato real\n\n---\n\n## Fase 5 — Fechar a última milha OpenClaw\nAqui entra a pergunta operacional mais importante:\n\n### Como exactamente o supervisor OpenClaw vai chamar os operators?\nPorque hoje eu já vi:\n- contracts bons\n- skills boas\n- scheduler bom\n\nMas ainda falta garantir a **mecânica canónica de invocação**.\n\nOu seja, definir com precisão:\n- o supervisor escreve payload\n- chama operator X\n- operator lê ficheiro Y\n- escreve output Z\n- supervisor valida\n- retry planner decide\n- wave seguinte avança\n\nIsto precisa sair do “entendido” e virar fluxo explícito.\n\n---\n\n## Fase 6 — Despromover o Python monolítico\nDepois que a topologia estiver fixa:\n\n- `s1_start.py` deixa de conter inteligência estrutural\n- vira só:\n  - compat shim\n  - launcher\n  - ou até candidato a remoção futura\n\nMas **não** devemos começar por matar ele.\nPrimeiro fixamos o sistema canónico, depois rebaixamos o velho.\n\n---\n\n# O que eu faria AGORA, concretamente\nSe o teu objectivo é “garantir que o S1 está 100% configurado perfeitamente com agentes OpenClaw”, eu faria nesta ordem:\n\n## Passo 1 — Supervisor first\n- rever e ajustar `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- deixar explícito:\n  - autoridade\n  - runtime canónico\n  - classes de componentes\n  - relação com `s1_start.py`\n\n## Passo 2 — mapa de autoridade do S1\n- um documento curto e duro\n- sem ambiguidade\n- responsabilidade por responsabilidade\n\n## Passo 3 — contratos das interfaces críticas\n- adapters\n- validator de scene_director\n- mergers\n- retry planner\n- scheduler\n\n## Passo 4 — auditoria do workspace do `sm_s1_pre_production`\n- ver se os docs do agent realmente espelham a arquitectura final\n\n## Passo 5 — depois sim agent-by-agent\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação firme\n**Não ir já para “ajustar tudo do S1” de forma difusa.**  \nIsso vai reintroduzir drift.\n\nA melhor alavanca agora é:\n\n> **fechar o supervisor como constituição do sector**\n> porque quando o supervisor fica certo, o resto encaixa mais facilmente.\n\nSe quiser, eu proponho já o próximo movimento operacional:\n\n### Opção recomendada\nEu começo agora por:\n1. **auditar e reescrever mentalmente o `s1_supervisor_contract.md`**\n2. te devolver:\n   - o que manter\n   - o que mudar\n   - o que acrescentar\n3. depois fazemos os ajustes concretos\n\nSe tu quiser, eu já entro nisso agora.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc08dc2e208193808742c5a607b944\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2149,"output":1448,"cacheRead":91648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95245,"cost":{"input":0.0053725000000000005,"output":0.02172,"cacheRead":0.022912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.05000449999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774979290210,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc08db32dc81939aee62130ae9786d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a48db05b","parentId":"d1726912","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:50:58.449Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-31 14:50 GMT-3] sim vai lá Tobias. Acho que tens conhecimento suficiente sobre o que eu preciso no S1, não preciso ficar mais te dizendo oq ue fazer. Acho que agora já tens condições de entender 100% o que precisamos deste setor e o que eu preciso de ti é que tu configure este setor para funcionar da maniera mais perfeita possivel com openclaw. Pode fazer tudo que precisares pra garantir isso e me avisas quando estiver pronto"}],"timestamp":1774979458370}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b57d7fa","parentId":"a48db05b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:51:05.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou assumir o fechamento estruturado do supervisor do S1 como primeira peça canónica e deixar tudo alinhado para OpenClaw.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0988312c8193bc4a052f64953090\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MfUWvk0XFq63N5BmyMoKugKs|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0988ec48819385b2e62c2f0dea3d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":286,"output":80,"cacheRead":95104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95470,"cost":{"input":0.000715,"output":0.0012000000000000001,"cacheRead":0.023776,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025691}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979459450,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc098499888193898c9c388877b68e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a311f92","parentId":"3b57d7fa","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:51:06.449Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MfUWvk0XFq63N5BmyMoKugKs|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0988ec48819385b2e62c2f0dea3d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Newly required / now being formalized\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer` (already exists in `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`, pending light alignment audit only)\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\nImportant precondition:\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\n- structural patch candidates\n- batch repair candidates\n- full batch regeneration candidates\n\n## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Purpose\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\n\n### Scope\n- receives operator batches\n- applies a concurrency cap\n- groups batches into execution waves\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\n\n### Initial supported operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n### Out of scope\n`operator_batch_scheduler` does **not**:\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself yet\n- decide semantic retry logic\n- merge outputs\n- validate content\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n- `operator_batch_scheduler` is implemented as the controlled parallel scheduling layer for batchable operators\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979466326}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ad596e4","parentId":"2a311f92","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:52:31.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou reescrever o contrato do supervisor para refletir a arquitetura canónica OpenClaw do S1 antes de passar para os restantes componentes.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc098e94288193804d73cd4293906c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yPfT5ztWICCxzUDf7jnrT8Bd|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc098f593081939873994282b72cb7","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","content":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v2 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the canonical runtime brain for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**.\nIt is not:\n- a purely conversational helper\n- a passive documentation artifact\n- a monolithic Python script that absorbs the whole sector itself\n\nThe canonical operating model for S1 is:\n- **`sm_s1_pre_production` = canonical runtime supervisor**\n- **OpenClaw operators = semantic specialists**\n- **deterministic Python components = execution substrate**\n- **persisted run artifacts = operational truth**\n\n---\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\n\nThe canonical runtime authority for S1 belongs to:\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n\nThis means the supervisor is the authoritative owner of:\n- sector sequencing\n- operator invocation decisions\n- validation interpretation\n- retry / fail / continue / escalate decisions\n- sector completion decisions\n\n### Important non-canonical component\n`runtime/s1/s1_start.py` must be treated as:\n- bootstrap layer\n- compatibility shim\n- transition helper\n- temporary orchestration bridge where still needed\n\nIt must **not** be treated as the long-term canonical brain of the sector.\n\nThe direction of travel is:\n- more authority in the OpenClaw supervisor\n- less sector intelligence embedded in `s1_start.py`\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n### Persisted artifacts = truth\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic component\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue / escalate\n- decide when outputs are accepted into canonical artifacts\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n- determine final sector completion\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n- scene bible construction internals\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators\n- supervisor deterministic skills\n- shared deterministic sector components\n\n---\n\n## Component classes inside S1\n\nThe S1 sector is composed of four distinct component classes.\n\n### 1. Canonical supervisor\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n\n### 2. OpenClaw semantic operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### 3. Supervisor deterministic skills\nThese are deterministic components directly used by the supervisor to plan, bridge, validate, merge, schedule, and summarize the sector flow.\n\nImplemented now:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### 4. Shared deterministic sector components\nThese are deterministic runtime components used by the sector, but they are not supervisor-local planning/bridging skills.\n\nShared components currently used by S1:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\nThis distinction is important:\n- supervisor skills shape supervision flow\n- shared deterministic components perform reusable sector mechanics\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\n### Minimum expected inputs before S1 begins\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n### Minimum expected outputs after S1 completes\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\nThe supervisor should reason over persisted artifacts rather than hidden in-memory assumptions.\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\n\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical and should not be expanded further.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical authority map\n\n### Supervisor owns\n- sector order of operations\n- operator invocation decisions\n- acceptance/rejection of batch outputs\n- retry decisions\n- escalation decisions\n- final sector status\n\n### Operators own\n- semantic scene structuring (`scene_director`)\n- semantic TTS-oriented oral normalization (`tts_polish`)\n- semantic borderline review for polish when needed (`tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`)\n\n### Supervisor skills own\n- preflight\n- path resolution\n- batching\n- operator payload bridge construction\n- per-batch structural validation where defined\n- merge preparation/composition\n- controlled scheduling plans\n- retry recommendation logic\n- final result summarization\n\n### Shared deterministic components own\n- whole-screenplay validation\n- whole-polish validation\n- scene bible build\n- scene bible schema validation\n- checkpoint writing\n\n---\n\n## Canonical sector workflow\n\nThe canonical S1 flow is:\n\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\n7. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\n8. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\n9. Merge approved batch outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n10. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\n11. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\n16. If needed, route borderline cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n17. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n18. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\n19. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n20. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\n21. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n22. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\n23. Summarize the final result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n24. Complete or fail the sector\n\n---\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, schema validation, checkpointing, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible\n\n### Important current limitation\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently provides:\n- wave planning\n- concurrency capping\n- execution summary structure\n\nIt does **not** by itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\nThe supervisor still owns the actual invocation/control loop.\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` -> OpenClaw operator used only where semantic review is needed\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\nThe supervisor must not delegate its authority away.\nOperators are specialists, not sector owners.\n\n---\n\n## Supervisor deterministic skills\n\n## `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n---\n\n## `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n---\n\n## `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n---\n\n## `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Contract note\nThis component is an interface-critical bridge and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Contract note\nThis component is an acceptance gate and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json`.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Contract note\nThis component writes a canonical sector artifact and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n---\n\n## `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Contract note\nThis component is an interface-critical bridge and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Contract note\nThis component writes a canonical sector artifact and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `retry_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\n### Contract note\nThis component encodes sector recovery policy and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Purpose\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\n\n### Scope\n- receives operator batches\n- applies a concurrency cap\n- groups batches into execution waves\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\n\n### Initial supported operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n### Out of scope\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself\n- decide semantic retry logic\n- merge outputs\n- validate content\n\n### Contract note\nThis component defines operational scheduling semantics and should have its own dedicated contract.\n\n---\n\n## `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n---\n\n## Shared deterministic sector components\n\nThese components are used by S1 but are not classified as supervisor-local skills:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\nThese should remain documented as shared sector components and not be confused with semantic operators or with the supervisor brain itself.\n\n---\n\n## Contract coverage guidance\n\n### Components that should have dedicated contracts\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Components that may remain documented primarily inside this supervisor contract for now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Components that should be documented as shared deterministic sector components\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\n---\n\n## Current status summary\n\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as the canonical OpenClaw runtime brain for the sector\n- the component classes inside S1 are now explicitly separated\n- the intended authority of the supervisor vs operators vs deterministic components is explicit\n- `scene_director` flow is structurally well-defined from batch planning through validation and merge\n- `tts_polish` flow is structurally defined, including the existence of a semantic reviewer lane for borderline cases\n- controlled operator parallelism is defined at the planning/supervisory level\n- `s1_start.py` is explicitly demoted from canonical sector brain to bootstrap/transition role\n\nThe remaining work is no longer to invent the S1 architecture, but to ensure every agent, contract, workspace, and deterministic component is fully aligned with this canonical model.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Supervisor Contract\\n\\n_Status: v2 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is the canonical runtime brain for Pre-Production.\\n\\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\\n- `screenplay.json`\\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `tts_polished.json`\\n- `polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\\n\\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**.\\nIt is not:\\n- a purely conversational helper\\n- a passive documentation artifact\\n- a monolithic Python script that absorbs the whole sector itself\\n\\nThe canonical operating model for S1 is:\\n- **`sm_s1_pre_production` = canonical runtime supervisor**\\n- **OpenClaw operators = semantic specialists**\\n- **deterministic Python components = execution substrate**\\n- **persisted run artifacts = operational truth**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical runtime rule\\n\\nThe canonical runtime authority for S1 belongs to:\\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\\n\\nThis means the supervisor is the authoritative owner of:\\n- sector sequencing\\n- operator invocation decisions\\n- validation interpretation\\n- retry / fail / continue / escalate decisions\\n- sector completion decisions\\n\\n### Important non-canonical component\\n`runtime/s1/s1_start.py` must be treated as:\\n- bootstrap layer\\n- compatibility shim\\n- transition helper\\n- temporary orchestration bridge where still needed\\n\\nIt must **not** be treated as the long-term canonical brain of the sector.\\n\\nThe direction of travel is:\\n- more authority in the OpenClaw supervisor\\n- less sector intelligence embedded in `s1_start.py`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Core principle\\n\\n### Supervisor = brain\\n### Skills = hands\\n### Operators = specialists\\n### Persisted artifacts = truth\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\\n- decide the order of operations\\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic component\\n- interpret validation results\\n- decide retry / fail / continue / escalate\\n- decide when outputs are accepted into canonical artifacts\\n- write or trigger checkpoints\\n- determine final sector completion\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\\n- semantic scene generation\\n- TTS polish generation\\n- low-level file/path mechanics\\n- deterministic validation logic\\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\\n- scene bible construction internals\\n\\nThose belong to:\\n- S1 operators\\n- supervisor deterministic skills\\n- shared deterministic sector components\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component classes inside S1\\n\\nThe S1 sector is composed of four distinct component classes.\\n\\n### 1. Canonical supervisor\\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\\n\\n### 2. OpenClaw semantic operators\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\\n\\n### 3. Supervisor deterministic skills\\nThese are deterministic components directly used by the supervisor to plan, bridge, validate, merge, schedule, and summarize the sector flow.\\n\\nImplemented now:\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### 4. Shared deterministic sector components\\nThese are deterministic runtime components used by the sector, but they are not supervisor-local planning/bridging skills.\\n\\nShared components currently used by S1:\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\\nThis distinction is important:\\n- supervisor skills shape supervision flow\\n- shared deterministic components perform reusable sector mechanics\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File contract principle\\n\\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\\n\\n### Minimum expected inputs before S1 begins\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n### Minimum expected outputs after S1 completes\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\\n\\nThe supervisor should reason over persisted artifacts rather than hidden in-memory assumptions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Naming convention\\n\\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\\n\\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical and should not be expanded further.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical authority map\\n\\n### Supervisor owns\\n- sector order of operations\\n- operator invocation decisions\\n- acceptance/rejection of batch outputs\\n- retry decisions\\n- escalation decisions\\n- final sector status\\n\\n### Operators own\\n- semantic scene structuring (`scene_director`)\\n- semantic TTS-oriented oral normalization (`tts_polish`)\\n- semantic borderline review for polish when needed (`tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`)\\n\\n### Supervisor skills own\\n- preflight\\n- path resolution\\n- batching\\n- operator payload bridge construction\\n- per-batch structural validation where defined\\n- merge preparation/composition\\n- controlled scheduling plans\\n- retry recommendation logic\\n- final result summarization\\n\\n### Shared deterministic components own\\n- whole-screenplay validation\\n- whole-polish validation\\n- scene bible build\\n- scene bible schema validation\\n- checkpoint writing\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical sector workflow\\n\\nThe canonical S1 flow is:\\n\\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches via `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\\n7. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\\n8. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\\n9. Merge approved batch outputs via `screenplay_merger`\\n10. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\\n11. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches via `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\\n16. If needed, route borderline cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\\n17. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\\n18. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\\n19. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n20. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\\n21. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n22. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\\n23. Summarize the final result via `s1_result_summarizer`\\n24. Complete or fail the sector\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Controlled parallelism policy\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\\n\\n### Initial concurrency caps\\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\\n\\n### Parallelism rules\\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\\n- validators, mergers, builders, schema validation, checkpointing, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible\\n\\n### Important current limitation\\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently provides:\\n- wave planning\\n- concurrency capping\\n- execution summary structure\\n\\nIt does **not** by itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\\nThe supervisor still owns the actual invocation/control loop.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current operator model\\n\\nThe intended operator structure for S1 is:\\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` -> OpenClaw operator used only where semantic review is needed\\n\\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\\n- operator reads input\\n- operator writes output file\\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\\n\\nThe supervisor must not delegate its authority away.\\nOperators are specialists, not sector owners.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Supervisor deterministic skills\\n\\n## `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\\n\\n### Scope\\nChecks:\\n- run root exists\\n- required input files exist\\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- create sector outputs\\n- call operators\\n- validate screenplay semantics\\n- decide batching\\n- modify the run\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `s1_paths_resolver`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\\n\\n### Scope\\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\\n- canonical output file paths\\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- validate semantic readiness\\n- call operators\\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\\n- perform batching\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `script_batch_planner`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives raw script text or script file path\\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- divide the script into final scenes\\n- call `scene_director`\\n- perform semantic validation\\n- merge operator outputs\\n\\n### Recommended v1 defaults\\n- target words per batch: `750`\\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives run/job context\\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- run the operator\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge batch outputs\\n- choose retry policy\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component is an interface-critical bridge and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- validate output shape for one batch result\\n- validate required scene fields\\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- merge batches\\n- decide final retry policy by itself\\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component is an acceptance gate and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `screenplay_merger`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json`.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- loads ordered batch output files\\n- validates minimum required scene fields\\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\\n- writes `screenplay.json`\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- perform semantic validation\\n- decide retry policy\\n- invoke operators\\n- polish TTS text\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component writes a canonical sector artifact and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives `screenplay.json`\\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\\n- preserves scene order\\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\\n\\n### Recommended v1 defaults\\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- perform TTS polish\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge polish outputs\\n- decide retry policy\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives run/job context\\n- receives merged screenplay\\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- run the operator\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge polish outputs\\n- choose retry policy\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component is an interface-critical bridge and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `tts_polish_merger`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- loads ordered polish batch files\\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\\n- decide retry policy\\n- invoke operators\\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component writes a canonical sector artifact and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `retry_planner`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\\n- enforces retry limits\\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- run retries itself\\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\\n- invoke operators or validators\\n- write checkpoints\\n\\n### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component encodes sector recovery policy and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives operator batches\\n- applies a concurrency cap\\n- groups batches into execution waves\\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\\n\\n### Initial supported operators\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself\\n- decide semantic retry logic\\n- merge outputs\\n- validate content\\n\\n### Contract note\\nThis component defines operational scheduling semantics and should have its own dedicated contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- aggregates scene counts\\n- aggregates batch counts\\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\\n- exposes checkpoint list\\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n- run the sector\\n- write checkpoints\\n- validate semantic correctness\\n- call operators or skills\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Shared deterministic sector components\\n\\nThese components are used by S1 but are not classified as supervisor-local skills:\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\\nThese should remain documented as shared sector components and not be confused with semantic operators or with the supervisor brain itself.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Contract coverage guidance\\n\\n### Components that should have dedicated contracts\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n### Components that may remain documented primarily inside this supervisor contract for now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### Components that should be documented as shared deterministic sector components\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current status summary\\n\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as the canonical OpenClaw runtime brain for the sector\\n- the component classes inside S1 are now explicitly separated\\n- the intended authority of the supervisor vs operators vs deterministic components is explicit\\n- `scene_director` flow is structurally well-defined from batch planning through validation and merge\\n- `tts_polish` flow is structurally defined, including the existence of a semantic reviewer lane for borderline cases\\n- controlled operator parallelism is defined at the planning/supervisory level\\n- `s1_start.py` is explicitly demoted from canonical sector brain to bootstrap/transition role\\n\\nThe remaining work is no longer to invent the S1 architecture, but to ensure every agent, contract, workspace, and deterministic component is fully aligned with this canonical model.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":4105,"output":4488,"cacheRead":95360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103953,"cost":{"input":0.0102625,"output":0.06732,"cacheRead":0.02384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1014225}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979467344,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc098c1b448193a9f63d16bddaf6b4"}}
