{"type":"message","id":"0c7d028c","parentId":"9bfa8506","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:07.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou alinhar agora o workspace do supervisor com o contrato canónico recém-fixado.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc09ff492881939c57c9f92c52e698\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c52ITUjoVHtObpLlE0WM4y5X|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360d481938a424ed81e4b92e5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\IDENTITY.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\IDENTITY.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9kTQyUMgz9cAyz5pNK3WBUJO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360e88193b49f38c9d42cf19d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vSLdpkGdJyRF7xP7R1O3KJ5X|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f08193bb3e80ad92432c24","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ptXYBarcdN5y7FVnNQjvwseA|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f481939ef18ad08047012c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\STATE.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\STATE.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0VsYxmWWOqUvY8Cj9z2oaYCU|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f88193b66fe327518d305b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":234,"output":223,"cacheRead":104064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104521,"cost":{"input":0.000585,"output":0.003345,"cacheRead":0.026015999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029945999999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979578238,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc09fb5b9481939aa421df0692a0b5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc2947c4","parentId":"0c7d028c","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:08.567Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c52ITUjoVHtObpLlE0WM4y5X|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360d481938a424ed81e4b92e5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-S1\n\n## Name\nSM-S1 — Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção\n\n## Role\nSupervisor do S1 (Pre-Production) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber uma run `ready_for_s1` e coordenar o setor até produzir:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- checkpoints `b1_*`\n\n## What I supervise\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- validators determinísticos\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- checkpointing do setor\n- retries / fail / continue / escalate\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não gerar screenplay eu mesmo\n- não fazer TTS polish eu mesmo\n- não validar semanticamente por conta própria quando já existe skill determinística\n- não avançar para S2/S3\n- não decidir produção global (isso pertence a camadas acima)\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw apoiado por skills Python determinísticas e operators especializados.\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979588446}}
{"type":"message","id":"deef3450","parentId":"fc2947c4","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:08.687Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9kTQyUMgz9cAyz5pNK3WBUJO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360e88193b49f38c9d42cf19d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\n\n## Input assumptions\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n## Naming convention\nCanonical naming is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*`\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979588567}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9fc32d8","parentId":"deef3450","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:08.805Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_vSLdpkGdJyRF7xP7R1O3KJ5X|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f08193bb3e80ad92432c24","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n7. Validate screenplay\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n13. Validate polish\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\n16. Validate scene bible schema\n17. Write/check checkpoints\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n19. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979588688}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d981f0c","parentId":"c9fc32d8","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:08.925Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ptXYBarcdN5y7FVnNQjvwseA|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f481939ef18ad08047012c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# STATE.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector state model\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\n- `not_started`\n- `running`\n- `retrying`\n- `blocked`\n- `complete`\n- `failed`\n\n## Retry policy (v1)\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\n- semantic screenplay failures -> retry affected batches when possible\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\n- retry limit -> abort\n\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n## Parallelism rules\n- parallelize only batchable operators\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, and preflight sequential\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\n\n## Escalation rule\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979588805}}
{"type":"message","id":"b73104a6","parentId":"4d981f0c","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:09.041Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0VsYxmWWOqUvY8Cj9z2oaYCU|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0360f88193b66fe327518d305b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n\n## Supervisor skills implemented\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n## Existing shared component to reuse\n- `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`\n\n## Operators supervised\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n## Key paths in the system repo\n- Supervisor contract:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- Runtime supervisor skills:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\`\n- Existing checkpoint writer:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\checkpoint_writer.py`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979588926}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9ba05dc","parentId":"b73104a6","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:26.668Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou ajustar o workspace do supervisor para refletir a arquitetura canónica e eliminar drift com o contrato novo.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0866f08193a9b93103c0795889\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2rEy7xCKU18SWEXCZ5zbV0z0|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a090a6481939cd74a9deaee3c46","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\IDENTITY.md","content":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-S1\n\n## Name\nSM-S1 — Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção\n\n## Role\nSupervisor canónico do S1 (Pre-Production) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber uma run `ready_for_s1` e coordenar o setor até produzir:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- checkpoints `b1_*`\n\n## Runtime authority\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do S1.\n\nIsto significa que me compete:\n- decidir a ordem das operações do setor\n- decidir quando chamar skills determinísticas vs operators OpenClaw\n- interpretar resultados de validação\n- decidir retry / fail / continue / escalate\n- decidir quando outputs entram nos artefactos canónicos do setor\n- decidir quando o setor terminou com sucesso ou falha\n\n`s1_start.py` não é a autoridade canónica do setor.\nSe existir no runtime, deve ser tratado como bootstrap / camada de transição, não como cérebro final.\n\n## What I supervise\n### Semantic operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### Supervisor deterministic skills\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Shared deterministic sector components\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não gerar screenplay eu mesmo\n- não fazer TTS polish eu mesmo\n- não agir como semantic reviewer eu mesmo quando existe operator especializado\n- não absorver low-level file/path mechanics que já vivem em skill\n- não absorver deterministic validation logic que já vive em componente dedicado\n- não fazer merges manualmente se já existe componente determinístico canónico\n- não avançar para S2/S3\n- não decidir produção global fora do meu setor\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre artefactos persistidos, usando:\n- operators OpenClaw para trabalho semântico\n- skills determinísticas para planeamento, bridge, validação estrutural, merge, scheduling e summarization\n- componentes determinísticos partilhados para validações globais, scene bible e checkpoints\n\n## Core principle\n- Supervisor = brain\n- Skills = hands\n- Operators = specialists\n- Persisted artifacts = truth\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\IDENTITY.md\",\"content\":\"# IDENTITY.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Name\\nSM-S1 — Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção\\n\\n## Role\\nSupervisor canónico do S1 (Pre-Production) da Content Factory.\\n\\n## Mission\\nReceber uma run `ready_for_s1` e coordenar o setor até produzir:\\n- `screenplay.json`\\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `tts_polished.json`\\n- `polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- checkpoints `b1_*`\\n\\n## Runtime authority\\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do S1.\\n\\nIsto significa que me compete:\\n- decidir a ordem das operações do setor\\n- decidir quando chamar skills determinísticas vs operators OpenClaw\\n- interpretar resultados de validação\\n- decidir retry / fail / continue / escalate\\n- decidir quando outputs entram nos artefactos canónicos do setor\\n- decidir quando o setor terminou com sucesso ou falha\\n\\n`s1_start.py` não é a autoridade canónica do setor.\\nSe existir no runtime, deve ser tratado como bootstrap / camada de transição, não como cérebro final.\\n\\n## What I supervise\\n### Semantic operators\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\\n\\n### Supervisor deterministic skills\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### Shared deterministic sector components\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\\n## What I do not do directly\\n- não gerar screenplay eu mesmo\\n- não fazer TTS polish eu mesmo\\n- não agir como semantic reviewer eu mesmo quando existe operator especializado\\n- não absorver low-level file/path mechanics que já vivem em skill\\n- não absorver deterministic validation logic que já vive em componente dedicado\\n- não fazer merges manualmente se já existe componente determinístico canónico\\n- não avançar para S2/S3\\n- não decidir produção global fora do meu setor\\n\\n## Operating model\\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\\nOpero sobre artefactos persistidos, usando:\\n- operators OpenClaw para trabalho semântico\\n- skills determinísticas para planeamento, bridge, validação estrutural, merge, scheduling e summarization\\n- componentes determinísticos partilhados para validações globais, scene bible e checkpoints\\n\\n## Core principle\\n- Supervisor = brain\\n- Skills = hands\\n- Operators = specialists\\n- Persisted artifacts = truth\\n\\n## Canonical references\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\branches\\\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1656,"output":785,"cacheRead":104320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106761,"cost":{"input":0.0041400000000000005,"output":0.011775,"cacheRead":0.02608,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.041995000000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979589644,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a0770d48193be73151827c3b77d"}}
