{"type":"message","id":"dc1aba78","parentId":"1c74ac3f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:40.633Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kwSaMzxHj77KD8UYN3ubeCp7|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a197eb881938696d5b3d71b1f43","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\CONTEXT.md","content":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do setor é o próprio `sm_s1_pre_production`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do S1 para:\n- sequencing\n- invocation decisions\n- validation interpretation\n- retry / fail / continue / escalate\n- sector completion\n\nQualquer camada Python auxiliar deve ser tratada como bootstrap/transição, não como soberania do setor.\n\n## Input assumptions\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n\n### Semantic operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### Supervisor deterministic skills\n- preflight\n- paths resolution\n- batching\n- operator I/O bridge\n- per-batch structural validation\n- merge\n- retry planning\n- controlled scheduling\n- result summarization\n\n### Shared deterministic components\n- whole-screenplay validation\n- whole-polish validation\n- scene bible build\n- scene bible schema validation\n- checkpoint writing\n\n## Naming convention\nCanonical naming is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*`\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\CONTEXT.md\",\"content\":\"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Sector\\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\\n\\n## Sector purpose\\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\\n\\n## Canonical runtime rule\\nO runtime canónico do setor é o próprio `sm_s1_pre_production`.\\n\\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do S1 para:\\n- sequencing\\n- invocation decisions\\n- validation interpretation\\n- retry / fail / continue / escalate\\n- sector completion\\n\\nQualquer camada Python auxiliar deve ser tratada como bootstrap/transição, não como soberania do setor.\\n\\n## Input assumptions\\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n## Output expectations\\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\\n\\n## Component classes in the sector\\n### Supervisor\\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\\n\\n### Semantic operators\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\\n\\n### Supervisor deterministic skills\\n- preflight\\n- paths resolution\\n- batching\\n- operator I/O bridge\\n- per-batch structural validation\\n- merge\\n- retry planning\\n- controlled scheduling\\n- result summarization\\n\\n### Shared deterministic components\\n- whole-screenplay validation\\n- whole-polish validation\\n- scene bible build\\n- scene bible schema validation\\n- checkpoint writing\\n\\n## Naming convention\\nCanonical naming is:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_*`\\n\\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\\n\\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":177,"output":618,"cacheRead":106624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107419,"cost":{"input":0.0004425,"output":0.00927,"cacheRead":0.026656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0363685}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979607795,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a187ab8819394a70e15217f269f"}}
