{"type":"message","id":"5d5cabd3","parentId":"dcde69ee","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:53:54.079Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_egODB6pexDgPK2e1NN0uZjER|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a281df881938c6466616a73fa60","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md","content":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\n7. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\n8. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\n9. Merge approved scene batches via `screenplay_merger`\n10. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\n11. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\n16. If needed, route borderline cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n17. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n18. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\n19. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n20. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\n21. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n22. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\n23. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n24. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n- Do not allow unvalidated batch outputs into canonical merge artifacts\n- The supervisor remains the owner of sequencing and acceptance decisions\n\n## Important current implementation note\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently plans waves and summarizes execution.\nIt does **not** itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\nThe supervisor must still own the actual operator invocation/control loop.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"content\":\"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Canonical sector flow\\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\\n7. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\\n8. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\\n9. Merge approved scene batches via `screenplay_merger`\\n10. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\\n11. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\\n16. If needed, route borderline cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\\n17. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\\n18. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\\n19. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n20. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\\n21. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n22. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\\n23. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\\n24. Complete or fail the sector\\n\\n## Important workflow rules\\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\\n- Use selective retry when possible\\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\\n- Do not allow unvalidated batch outputs into canonical merge artifacts\\n- The supervisor remains the owner of sequencing and acceptance decisions\\n\\n## Important current implementation note\\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently plans waves and summarizes execution.\\nIt does **not** itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\\nThe supervisor must still own the actual operator invocation/control loop.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":195,"output":521,"cacheRead":107264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107980,"cost":{"input":0.00048750000000000003,"output":0.007815,"cacheRead":0.026816,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0351185}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979621751,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a26ee6c81939b23edf3010a50db"}}
