{"type":"message","id":"a496b52b","parentId":"174c9311","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:54:06.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_km2oEooYDH9pNi6ZAxbyoapd|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a3557f88193bdd611f9ba553c20","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\STATE.md","content":"# STATE.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector state model\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\n- `not_started`\n- `running`\n- `retrying`\n- `blocked`\n- `complete`\n- `failed`\n\n## Authority rule\nState transitions belong to the supervisor.\nOperators and deterministic components may emit results, but they do not own sector state sovereignty.\n\n## Retry policy (v1)\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\n- scene_director batch structural/fidelity failures -> retry via `retry_planner`\n- screenplay global validation failures -> retry affected batches when possible\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\n- retry limit -> abort\n\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n## Parallelism rules\n- parallelize only batchable operators\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, schema validation, checkpointing, and preflight sequential\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\n\n## Escalation rule\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\n\n## Acceptance rule\nCanonical artifacts should only be advanced when the supervisor has enough validation basis to accept them.\nRejected or unvalidated operator outputs must not be treated as sector truth.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\STATE.md\",\"content\":\"# STATE.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Sector state model\\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\\n- `not_started`\\n- `running`\\n- `retrying`\\n- `blocked`\\n- `complete`\\n- `failed`\\n\\n## Authority rule\\nState transitions belong to the supervisor.\\nOperators and deterministic components may emit results, but they do not own sector state sovereignty.\\n\\n## Retry policy (v1)\\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\\n- scene_director batch structural/fidelity failures -> retry via `retry_planner`\\n- screenplay global validation failures -> retry affected batches when possible\\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\\n- retry limit -> abort\\n\\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\\n\\n## Parallelism rules\\n- parallelize only batchable operators\\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, schema validation, checkpointing, and preflight sequential\\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\\n\\n## Escalation rule\\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\\n\\n## Acceptance rule\\nCanonical artifacts should only be advanced when the supervisor has enough validation basis to accept them.\\nRejected or unvalidated operator outputs must not be treated as sector truth.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":116,"output":378,"cacheRead":107904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108398,"cost":{"input":0.00029,"output":0.0056700000000000006,"cacheRead":0.026976,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.032936}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979635263,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a33fc148193ae03a2cb07325c67"}}
