{"type":"message","id":"f61d0fdf","parentId":"7dc5c6db","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:55:11.545Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — **ajustei no workspace real dos agents em**:\n\n`C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production`\n\nNão foi no mirror.\n\nTambém actualizei o contrato canónico no repo em:\n`C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n\nPosso seguir tranquilo com essa mesma lógica:  \n- **workspace real** para o comportamento/config dos agents  \n- **repo docs/contracts** para a camada canónica do sistema","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a7d25c88193ba3e9750caa44bfd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":246,"output":125,"cacheRead":109184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109555,"cost":{"input":0.0006150000000000001,"output":0.0018750000000000001,"cacheRead":0.027295999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029785999999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774979707419,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a7c3a2c8193953102f697116787"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b29d407","parentId":"f61d0fdf","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:55:39.604Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-31 14:55 GMT-3] Próximo passo que vou fazer\nAgora vou para a próxima peça crítica:\ncriar/fechar os contratos dedicados do supervisor que ainda faltam, começando por:\n\nscene_director_io_adapter\nscene_director_output_validator\nscreenplay_merger\nDepois disso seguimos para o loop do polish. Show. Vai la"}],"timestamp":1774979739526}}
{"type":"message","id":"07661ef4","parentId":"9b29d407","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:56:09.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou fechar agora os contratos dedicados críticos do loop de screenplay do supervisor.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0aa3a2488193b21bafef75034c5e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kgLj2rN2yex1ws66iXfek8AM|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0aa42c508193b887e0585cb7bee1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_io_adapter_contract.md","content":"# S1 Scene Director IO Adapter Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic bridge contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `scene_director_io_adapter` is the deterministic bridge that prepares the explicit file contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator.\n\nIts role is not to generate scenes and not to supervise the sector.\nIts role is to transform supervisor-side batch planning into a stable, explicit, operator-ready payload.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits between:\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director`\n\nIt exists so that:\n- the supervisor does not manually assemble operator payloads ad hoc\n- the operator receives a stable and explicit contract\n- downstream validation and retries can reference stable input/output paths\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\n\n### Not owned by\n- the `scene_director` operator\n- `s1_start.py` as sector brain\n- downstream merge/validation components\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe adapter should receive, at minimum:\n- `run_root`\n- `job`\n- one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- `channel_config`\n- `input_path`\n- `output_path`\n\n### Required job fields\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n\n### Required batch fields\n- `batch_id`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `word_count`\n- `text`\n\n### Relevant channel config field\n- `scene_words_range`\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe adapter should:\n- preserve run/job identity\n- preserve the exact batch boundaries decided upstream\n- inject `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- include explicit instructions relevant to `scene_director`\n- write a deterministic payload file\n- declare the exact output path expected from the operator\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe adapter must **not**:\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic generation\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- decide retry policy\n- infer new batch boundaries\n- rewrite batch text\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nThe adapter writes one deterministic payload file per `scene_director` batch.\n\n### Minimum payload shape\n```json\n{\n  \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"account\": \"004\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"batch\": {\n    \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n    \"start_word\": 1,\n    \"end_word\": 742,\n    \"word_count\": 742,\n    \"text\": \"...\"\n  },\n  \"scene_words_range\": [35, 75],\n  \"style_context\": {\n    \"channel_name\": \"...\",\n    \"reason\": \"...\"\n  },\n  \"instructions\": {\n    \"task\": \"...\",\n    \"requirements\": [\"...\"]\n  },\n  \"output_path\": \"C:/.../b1_pre_production/intermediate/scene_director/sd_001_output.json\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Output principles\n\nThe payload must make explicit:\n- who the job/run is\n- what batch is being processed\n- what the source text is\n- what structural rules apply\n- where the operator must write the result\n\nThe payload should be deterministic and re-creatable.\nThe same valid inputs should produce the same payload structure.\n\n---\n\n## File-system expectations\n\n### Input payload path\nShould live under the S1 canonical inputs area for `scene_director`, for example:\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/scene_director/sd_001_input.json`\n\n### Output path declared inside payload\nShould point to the canonical intermediate area for `scene_director` results, for example:\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/scene_director/sd_001_output.json`\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with downstream components\n\n### Consumed by\n- `scene_director`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- supervisor retry loop\n\n### Must remain compatible with\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n\n---\n\n## Error policy\n\nIf required inputs are missing or malformed, the adapter should fail clearly and deterministically.\n\nExamples:\n- missing `batch_id`\n- missing `text`\n- missing `output_path`\n- invalid `job` identity fields\n\nIt should not silently invent values for critical fields.\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_director_io_adapter.py`\n\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_scene_director_io_adapter_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Scene Director IO Adapter Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic bridge contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `scene_director_io_adapter` is the deterministic bridge that prepares the explicit file contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator.\\n\\nIts role is not to generate scenes and not to supervise the sector.\\nIts role is to transform supervisor-side batch planning into a stable, explicit, operator-ready payload.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits between:\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director`\\n\\nIt exists so that:\\n- the supervisor does not manually assemble operator payloads ad hoc\\n- the operator receives a stable and explicit contract\\n- downstream validation and retries can reference stable input/output paths\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- the `scene_director` operator\\n- `s1_start.py` as sector brain\\n- downstream merge/validation components\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe adapter should receive, at minimum:\\n- `run_root`\\n- `job`\\n- one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\\n- `channel_config`\\n- `input_path`\\n- `output_path`\\n\\n### Required job fields\\n- `job_id`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n\\n### Required batch fields\\n- `batch_id`\\n- `start_word`\\n- `end_word`\\n- `word_count`\\n- `text`\\n\\n### Relevant channel config field\\n- `scene_words_range`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe adapter should:\\n- preserve run/job identity\\n- preserve the exact batch boundaries decided upstream\\n- inject `scene_words_range` from channel config\\n- include explicit instructions relevant to `scene_director`\\n- write a deterministic payload file\\n- declare the exact output path expected from the operator\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe adapter must **not**:\\n- call `scene_director`\\n- perform semantic generation\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge batch outputs\\n- decide retry policy\\n- infer new batch boundaries\\n- rewrite batch text\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\\nThe adapter writes one deterministic payload file per `scene_director` batch.\\n\\n### Minimum payload shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"account\\\": \\\"004\\\",\\n  \\\"language\\\": \\\"fr\\\",\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"batch\\\": {\\n    \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"sd_001\\\",\\n    \\\"start_word\\\": 1,\\n    \\\"end_word\\\": 742,\\n    \\\"word_count\\\": 742,\\n    \\\"text\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"scene_words_range\\\": [35, 75],\\n  \\\"style_context\\\": {\\n    \\\"channel_name\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"instructions\\\": {\\n    \\\"task\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"requirements\\\": [\\\"...\\\"]\\n  },\\n  \\\"output_path\\\": \\\"C:/.../b1_pre_production/intermediate/scene_director/sd_001_output.json\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output principles\\n\\nThe payload must make explicit:\\n- who the job/run is\\n- what batch is being processed\\n- what the source text is\\n- what structural rules apply\\n- where the operator must write the result\\n\\nThe payload should be deterministic and re-creatable.\\nThe same valid inputs should produce the same payload structure.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File-system expectations\\n\\n### Input payload path\\nShould live under the S1 canonical inputs area for `scene_director`, for example:\\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/scene_director/sd_001_input.json`\\n\\n### Output path declared inside payload\\nShould point to the canonical intermediate area for `scene_director` results, for example:\\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/scene_director/sd_001_output.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship with downstream components\\n\\n### Consumed by\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- supervisor retry loop\\n\\n### Must remain compatible with\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error policy\\n\\nIf required inputs are missing or malformed, the adapter should fail clearly and deterministically.\\n\\nExamples:\\n- missing `batch_id`\\n- missing `text`\\n- missing `output_path`\\n- invalid `job` identity fields\\n\\nIt should not silently invent values for critical fields.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_director_io_adapter.py`\\n\\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":238,"output":1223,"cacheRead":109440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110901,"cost":{"input":0.000595,"output":0.018345,"cacheRead":0.02736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.046299999999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979740589,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0a9d82648193a8643030d9d2fd15"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef8c26c1","parentId":"07661ef4","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:56:10.410Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kgLj2rN2yex1ws66iXfek8AM|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0aa42c508193b887e0585cb7bee1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 4193 bytes to C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_io_adapter_contract.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979770293}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc8ddbdb","parentId":"ef8c26c1","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:56:40.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZCiEzLkuYY431lVkX7ANNtMQ|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0abcc8c88193a1eb047e4e57f050","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md","content":"# S1 Scene Director Output Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic batch-acceptance gate for `scene_director` outputs inside S1._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `scene_director_output_validator` validates each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\nIts role is to ensure that only structurally valid, source-faithful, batch-compatible outputs are accepted into the canonical screenplay merge path.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits between:\n- `scene_director`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n\nIt is the deterministic acceptance gate for scene batch outputs.\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\n\n### Not owned by\n- the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- the retry planner\n\nThe validator classifies the batch outcome.\nThe supervisor still decides what to do with that classification.\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe validator should receive, at minimum:\n- `batch_payload_path`\n- `batch_output_path`\n\n### Why both are required\nThe validator must compare the operator output against the exact supervisor-prepared batch payload, because validation depends on:\n- expected batch identity\n- expected source text\n- expected batch-relative span semantics\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe validator should:\n- validate output readability/parsing\n- validate top-level output shape\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` sequencing\n- validate scene spans\n- validate non-overlap\n- validate full source coverage for the intended batch\n- validate `narration_original` fidelity against source text\n- validate `estimated_scene_word_count`\n- classify failures into retry-relevant categories\n- decide whether the batch is approved for merge\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe validator must **not**:\n- merge batches\n- regenerate scenes\n- repair outputs in place\n- decide final retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- judge broad creative quality beyond structural/fidelity checks\n\n---\n\n## Required operator output structure\n\n### Minimum top-level shape\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n  \"operator\": \"scene_director\",\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_01\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"...\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"...\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"...\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"...\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 52,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 52\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation rules\n\n### Top-level rules\n- payload must be valid JSON\n- output must be valid JSON\n- output must be a JSON object\n- output must include:\n  - `batch_id`\n  - `operator`\n  - `scenes`\n- `scenes` must be a non-empty list\n\n### Scene-level rules\nEach scene must include:\n- `scene_local_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\n### Sequencing rules\n- `scene_local_id` must be sequential within the batch\n- expected format is `scene_01`, `scene_02`, ...\n- duplicates are invalid\n\n### Span rules\n- `start_word` and `end_word` must be integers\n- spans must be batch-relative\n- spans must be ordered\n- spans must not overlap\n- spans must stay within the source batch range\n\n### Coverage rules\n- the batch source text must be fully covered\n- missing coverage is invalid\n- duplicate coverage is invalid\n\n### Fidelity rules\n- `narration_original` must match the source text assigned to that scene\n- `estimated_scene_word_count` must match the span-implied count\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nThe validator should return a structured result containing at minimum:\n- `ok`\n- `approved_for_merge`\n- `batch_id`\n- `classification`\n- `errors`\n- `warnings`\n- `stats`\n\n### Example shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": false,\n  \"approved_for_merge\": false,\n  \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n  \"classification\": \"batch_repair\",\n  \"errors\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"narration_source_mismatch\",\n      \"message\": \"Scene scene_02 narration_original does not match source span 53-104\",\n      \"scene_ids\": [\"scene_02\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"scene_count\": 7,\n    \"source_word_count\": 742,\n    \"covered_word_count\": 701\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Classification semantics\n\nCurrent classification space:\n- `ok`\n- `structural_patch`\n- `batch_repair`\n- `batch_regenerate`\n- `fatal_contract_error`\n\n### Meaning\n- `ok` -> approved for merge\n- `structural_patch` -> structurally incomplete but locally patch-like\n- `batch_repair` -> batch should be repaired/regenerated under supervisor control\n- `batch_regenerate` -> batch quality/structure is too broken for targeted repair\n- `fatal_contract_error` -> contract-level failure, do not proceed\n\nThe validator provides classification.\nThe supervisor decides the next action.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with retry handling\n\nThe validator does not run retries.\nIt provides structured evidence for the supervisor and `retry_planner`.\n\nThe supervisor should:\n- validate each batch independently\n- keep approved batches isolated from failed ones\n- avoid disturbing already-approved batches when only a subset fails\n\n---\n\n## Merge acceptance rule\n\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that are already approved for merge.\nUnvalidated or rejected batches must not be merged into canonical `screenplay.json`.\n\n---\n\n## Error policy\n\nThe validator should fail clearly and deterministically.\nIt should not silently downgrade contract failures into accepted outputs.\n\nExamples of fatal situations:\n- unreadable payload file\n- unreadable output file\n- invalid top-level output shape\n- empty scenes list\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_director_output_validator.py`\n\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Scene Director Output Validator Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic batch-acceptance gate for `scene_director` outputs inside S1._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `scene_director_output_validator` validates each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\\n\\nIts role is to ensure that only structurally valid, source-faithful, batch-compatible outputs are accepted into the canonical screenplay merge path.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits between:\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n\\nIt is the deterministic acceptance gate for scene batch outputs.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- the retry planner\\n\\nThe validator classifies the batch outcome.\\nThe supervisor still decides what to do with that classification.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe validator should receive, at minimum:\\n- `batch_payload_path`\\n- `batch_output_path`\\n\\n### Why both are required\\nThe validator must compare the operator output against the exact supervisor-prepared batch payload, because validation depends on:\\n- expected batch identity\\n- expected source text\\n- expected batch-relative span semantics\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe validator should:\\n- validate output readability/parsing\\n- validate top-level output shape\\n- validate required scene fields\\n- validate `scene_local_id` sequencing\\n- validate scene spans\\n- validate non-overlap\\n- validate full source coverage for the intended batch\\n- validate `narration_original` fidelity against source text\\n- validate `estimated_scene_word_count`\\n- classify failures into retry-relevant categories\\n- decide whether the batch is approved for merge\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe validator must **not**:\\n- merge batches\\n- regenerate scenes\\n- repair outputs in place\\n- decide final retry policy\\n- invoke operators\\n- judge broad creative quality beyond structural/fidelity checks\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required operator output structure\\n\\n### Minimum top-level shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"sd_001\\\",\\n  \\\"operator\\\": \\\"scene_director\\\",\\n  \\\"scenes\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"scene_local_id\\\": \\\"scene_01\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_title\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_summary\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"narrative_function\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"narration_original\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"start_word\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"end_word\\\": 52,\\n      \\\"estimated_scene_word_count\\\": 52\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation rules\\n\\n### Top-level rules\\n- payload must be valid JSON\\n- output must be valid JSON\\n- output must be a JSON object\\n- output must include:\\n  - `batch_id`\\n  - `operator`\\n  - `scenes`\\n- `scenes` must be a non-empty list\\n\\n### Scene-level rules\\nEach scene must include:\\n- `scene_local_id`\\n- `scene_title`\\n- `scene_summary`\\n- `narrative_function`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `start_word`\\n- `end_word`\\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\\n\\n### Sequencing rules\\n- `scene_local_id` must be sequential within the batch\\n- expected format is `scene_01`, `scene_02`, ...\\n- duplicates are invalid\\n\\n### Span rules\\n- `start_word` and `end_word` must be integers\\n- spans must be batch-relative\\n- spans must be ordered\\n- spans must not overlap\\n- spans must stay within the source batch range\\n\\n### Coverage rules\\n- the batch source text must be fully covered\\n- missing coverage is invalid\\n- duplicate coverage is invalid\\n\\n### Fidelity rules\\n- `narration_original` must match the source text assigned to that scene\\n- `estimated_scene_word_count` must match the span-implied count\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\\nThe validator should return a structured result containing at minimum:\\n- `ok`\\n- `approved_for_merge`\\n- `batch_id`\\n- `classification`\\n- `errors`\\n- `warnings`\\n- `stats`\\n\\n### Example shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": false,\\n  \\\"approved_for_merge\\\": false,\\n  \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"sd_001\\\",\\n  \\\"classification\\\": \\\"batch_repair\\\",\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"code\\\": \\\"narration_source_mismatch\\\",\\n      \\\"message\\\": \\\"Scene scene_02 narration_original does not match source span 53-104\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_ids\\\": [\\\"scene_02\\\"]\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n  \\\"stats\\\": {\\n    \\\"scene_count\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"source_word_count\\\": 742,\\n    \\\"covered_word_count\\\": 701\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Classification semantics\\n\\nCurrent classification space:\\n- `ok`\\n- `structural_patch`\\n- `batch_repair`\\n- `batch_regenerate`\\n- `fatal_contract_error`\\n\\n### Meaning\\n- `ok` -> approved for merge\\n- `structural_patch` -> structurally incomplete but locally patch-like\\n- `batch_repair` -> batch should be repaired/regenerated under supervisor control\\n- `batch_regenerate` -> batch quality/structure is too broken for targeted repair\\n- `fatal_contract_error` -> contract-level failure, do not proceed\\n\\nThe validator provides classification.\\nThe supervisor decides the next action.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship with retry handling\\n\\nThe validator does not run retries.\\nIt provides structured evidence for the supervisor and `retry_planner`.\\n\\nThe supervisor should:\\n- validate each batch independently\\n- keep approved batches isolated from failed ones\\n- avoid disturbing already-approved batches when only a subset fails\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Merge acceptance rule\\n\\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that are already approved for merge.\\nUnvalidated or rejected batches must not be merged into canonical `screenplay.json`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error policy\\n\\nThe validator should fail clearly and deterministically.\\nIt should not silently downgrade contract failures into accepted outputs.\\n\\nExamples of fatal situations:\\n- unreadable payload file\\n- unreadable output file\\n- invalid top-level output shape\\n- empty scenes list\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_director_output_validator.py`\\n\\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":229,"output":1562,"cacheRead":110720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112511,"cost":{"input":0.0005725000000000001,"output":0.02343,"cacheRead":0.02768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0516825}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979771242,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0abbc808819387c34a5f6e1207fe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"16cdee02","parentId":"fc8ddbdb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:56:41.511Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ZCiEzLkuYY431lVkX7ANNtMQ|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0abcc8c88193a1eb047e4e57f050","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 5795 bytes to C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774979801373}}
{"type":"message","id":"26dd8bfc","parentId":"16cdee02","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:57:05.336Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_I97Ez96y1GyJetHJRibIzF7r|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0adc39088193a49d059d1228eb9b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_screenplay_merger_contract.md","content":"# S1 Screenplay Merger Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic merge contract that produces canonical `screenplay.json` from approved `scene_director` batch outputs._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `screenplay_merger` merges approved `scene_director` batch outputs into one canonical `screenplay.json`.\n\nIts role is to:\n- preserve approved batch order\n- normalize scene identity into one canonical sequence\n- preserve traceability back to batch-level origins\n- produce the stable screenplay artifact for the rest of S1\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits after:\n- `scene_director`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\nAnd before:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- downstream S1 components that depend on canonical scene IDs\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\n\n### Not owned by\n- `scene_director`\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe merger should receive:\n- ordered batch output files\n- optional canonical `output_path`\n\n### Critical precondition\nThe merger should only receive batch output files that were already approved by `scene_director_output_validator`.\n\nThe merger must not be used as a hidden validation gate for unapproved batches.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe merger should:\n- load ordered batch output files\n- validate minimum required scene fields for merge compatibility\n- concatenate scenes in batch order\n- preserve source-batch traceability metadata\n- assign canonical global `scene_id` values\n- write canonical `screenplay.json`\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe merger must **not**:\n- perform semantic quality validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- repair malformed batches\n- overwrite source batch outputs\n- rewrite narration content\n\n---\n\n## Required input assumptions\n\nEach approved batch file should contain:\n- `batch_id`\n- `scenes`\n\nEach scene should contain at minimum:\n- `scene_local_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output structure\n\nThe merger should produce:\n```json\n{\n  \"scene_count\": 24,\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"source_batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"source_batch_scene_index\": 1,\n      \"source_scene_local_id\": \"scene_01\",\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_01\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"...\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"...\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"...\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"...\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 52,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 52,\n      \"scene_id\": \"scene_001\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Merge principles\n\n### Ordering\n- batch order must be preserved\n- scene order inside each batch must be preserved\n\n### Canonical scene identity\n- canonical global `scene_id` values are assigned here\n- expected format: `scene_001`, `scene_002`, ...\n\n### Traceability\nThe merger should preserve enough metadata to trace each merged scene back to:\n- source batch\n- source batch position\n- source local scene ID\n\n### Content preservation\nThe merger must not rewrite `narration_original` or other semantic fields.\nIts role is compositional, not generative.\n\n---\n\n## Error policy\n\nThe merger should fail clearly when merge prerequisites are not met.\n\nExamples:\n- no batch files provided\n- missing batch file\n- invalid batch JSON\n- invalid `scenes` payload\n- missing required scene fields\n\nWarnings may be emitted for soft anomalies such as:\n- empty batch scenes in an otherwise parseable file\n\n---\n\n## Output path expectation\n\nThe canonical merged artifact should normally be written to:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n\nThe merger may also return the in-memory screenplay structure to the supervisor.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with downstream validation\n\nThe merger is not the final quality gate.\nAfter merge, the supervisor should pass the resulting canonical screenplay to:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n\nThis separation is important:\n- `scene_director_output_validator` = per-batch acceptance gate\n- `screenplay_merger` = deterministic composition layer\n- `screenplay_validator` = whole-screenplay validation layer\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/screenplay_merger.py`\n\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_screenplay_merger_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Screenplay Merger Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic merge contract that produces canonical `screenplay.json` from approved `scene_director` batch outputs._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `screenplay_merger` merges approved `scene_director` batch outputs into one canonical `screenplay.json`.\\n\\nIts role is to:\\n- preserve approved batch order\\n- normalize scene identity into one canonical sequence\\n- preserve traceability back to batch-level origins\\n- produce the stable screenplay artifact for the rest of S1\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits after:\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\\nAnd before:\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- downstream S1 components that depend on canonical scene IDs\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe merger should receive:\\n- ordered batch output files\\n- optional canonical `output_path`\\n\\n### Critical precondition\\nThe merger should only receive batch output files that were already approved by `scene_director_output_validator`.\\n\\nThe merger must not be used as a hidden validation gate for unapproved batches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe merger should:\\n- load ordered batch output files\\n- validate minimum required scene fields for merge compatibility\\n- concatenate scenes in batch order\\n- preserve source-batch traceability metadata\\n- assign canonical global `scene_id` values\\n- write canonical `screenplay.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe merger must **not**:\\n- perform semantic quality validation\\n- decide retry policy\\n- invoke operators\\n- repair malformed batches\\n- overwrite source batch outputs\\n- rewrite narration content\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required input assumptions\\n\\nEach approved batch file should contain:\\n- `batch_id`\\n- `scenes`\\n\\nEach scene should contain at minimum:\\n- `scene_local_id`\\n- `scene_title`\\n- `scene_summary`\\n- `narrative_function`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `start_word`\\n- `end_word`\\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical output structure\\n\\nThe merger should produce:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"scene_count\\\": 24,\\n  \\\"scenes\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"source_batch_id\\\": \\\"sd_001\\\",\\n      \\\"source_batch_scene_index\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"source_scene_local_id\\\": \\\"scene_01\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_local_id\\\": \\\"scene_01\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_title\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"scene_summary\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"narrative_function\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"narration_original\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n      \\\"start_word\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"end_word\\\": 52,\\n      \\\"estimated_scene_word_count\\\": 52,\\n      \\\"scene_id\\\": \\\"scene_001\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Merge principles\\n\\n### Ordering\\n- batch order must be preserved\\n- scene order inside each batch must be preserved\\n\\n### Canonical scene identity\\n- canonical global `scene_id` values are assigned here\\n- expected format: `scene_001`, `scene_002`, ...\\n\\n### Traceability\\nThe merger should preserve enough metadata to trace each merged scene back to:\\n- source batch\\n- source batch position\\n- source local scene ID\\n\\n### Content preservation\\nThe merger must not rewrite `narration_original` or other semantic fields.\\nIts role is compositional, not generative.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error policy\\n\\nThe merger should fail clearly when merge prerequisites are not met.\\n\\nExamples:\\n- no batch files provided\\n- missing batch file\\n- invalid batch JSON\\n- invalid `scenes` payload\\n- missing required scene fields\\n\\nWarnings may be emitted for soft anomalies such as:\\n- empty batch scenes in an otherwise parseable file\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output path expectation\\n\\nThe canonical merged artifact should normally be written to:\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\\n\\nThe merger may also return the in-memory screenplay structure to the supervisor.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship with downstream validation\\n\\nThe merger is not the final quality gate.\\nAfter merge, the supervisor should pass the resulting canonical screenplay to:\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n\\nThis separation is important:\\n- `scene_director_output_validator` = per-batch acceptance gate\\n- `screenplay_merger` = deterministic composition layer\\n- `screenplay_validator` = whole-screenplay validation layer\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/screenplay_merger.py`\\n\\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":175,"output":1177,"cacheRead":112384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113736,"cost":{"input":0.0004375,"output":0.017655,"cacheRead":0.028096,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0461885}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979802254,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0adb1e00819391e6aa5050879bbc"}}
