{"type":"message","id":"59b77ecd","parentId":"fd509c0c","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:58:23.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou fechar agora o loop do polish e as peças de política/scheduling do supervisor.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0b2811e88193be00f00980d157a0\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9eddpTiLxRZoiZgth7U6ttYc|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0b28ce5c8193bebd0deff5236a05","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_tts_polish_io_adapter_contract.md","content":"# S1 TTS Polish IO Adapter Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic bridge contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `tts_polish_io_adapter` is the deterministic bridge that prepares the explicit file contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator.\n\nIts job is to convert canonical screenplay context plus one polish batch plan into a stable operator-ready payload.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits between:\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish`\n\nIt exists so that:\n- the supervisor does not manually assemble polish payloads ad hoc\n- `tts_polish` receives a stable contract\n- batch-level polish outputs can be validated/merged deterministically afterward\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\n\n### Not owned by\n- the `tts_polish` operator\n- the screenplay merger\n- the retry planner\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe adapter should receive, at minimum:\n- `run_root`\n- `job`\n- `screenplay`\n- one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `channel_config`\n- `input_path`\n- `output_path`\n\n### Required job fields\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n\n### Required batch fields\n- `batch_id`\n- `scene_ids`\n- `scene_count`\n- `word_count`\n\n### Required screenplay property\n- ordered canonical `scenes` with stable `scene_id`\n\n### Relevant channel config field\n- `tts_polish_rules`\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe adapter should:\n- preserve run/job identity\n- preserve batch identity\n- preserve canonical scene order inside the selected batch\n- preserve `scene_id`\n- preserve `narration_original`\n- inject `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- include explicit instructions relevant to TTS polish behavior\n- write a deterministic payload file\n- declare the expected output path for the operator\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe adapter must **not**:\n- call `tts_polish`\n- perform polish itself\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n- rewrite screenplay content\n- decide whether semantic review is needed\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nThe adapter writes one deterministic payload file per polish batch.\n\n### Minimum payload shape\n```json\n{\n  \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"account\": \"004\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"batch\": {\n    \"batch_id\": \"tp_001\",\n    \"scene_ids\": [\"scene_001\", \"scene_002\"],\n    \"scene_count\": 2,\n    \"word_count\": 148\n  },\n  \"tts_polish_rules\": [\"...\"],\n  \"style_context\": {\n    \"channel_name\": \"...\",\n    \"reason\": \"...\"\n  },\n  \"instructions\": {\n    \"task\": \"Polish the narration text for TTS without changing meaning.\",\n    \"requirements\": [\"...\"]\n  },\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_id\": \"scene_001\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"output_path\": \"C:/.../b1_pre_production/intermediate/tts_polish/tp_001_output.json\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Output principles\n\nThe payload must make explicit:\n- who the job/run is\n- what polish batch is being processed\n- which canonical scenes belong to the batch\n- what original narration is being polished\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where the operator must write the result\n\nThe payload should be deterministic and re-creatable.\n\n---\n\n## File-system expectations\n\n### Input payload path\nShould live under the S1 canonical inputs area for `tts_polish`, for example:\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/tts_polish/tp_001_input.json`\n\n### Output path declared inside payload\nShould point to the canonical intermediate area for `tts_polish` results, for example:\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/tts_polish/tp_001_output.json`\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with downstream components\n\n### Consumed by\n- `tts_polish`\n- supervisor retry loop\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- optional semantic review routing logic\n\n### Must remain compatible with\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `polish_validator`\n\n---\n\n## Error policy\n\nIf required inputs are missing or malformed, the adapter should fail clearly and deterministically.\nIt should not silently invent critical fields.\n\nExamples:\n- missing `batch_id`\n- missing `scene_ids`\n- missing `output_path`\n- missing canonical `scene_id` mapping in screenplay\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/tts_polish_io_adapter.py`\n\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_tts_polish_io_adapter_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 TTS Polish IO Adapter Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic bridge contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `tts_polish_io_adapter` is the deterministic bridge that prepares the explicit file contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator.\\n\\nIts job is to convert canonical screenplay context plus one polish batch plan into a stable operator-ready payload.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits between:\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n\\nIt exists so that:\\n- the supervisor does not manually assemble polish payloads ad hoc\\n- `tts_polish` receives a stable contract\\n- batch-level polish outputs can be validated/merged deterministically afterward\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 Supervisor as a deterministic supervisor skill\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- the `tts_polish` operator\\n- the screenplay merger\\n- the retry planner\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe adapter should receive, at minimum:\\n- `run_root`\\n- `job`\\n- `screenplay`\\n- one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `channel_config`\\n- `input_path`\\n- `output_path`\\n\\n### Required job fields\\n- `job_id`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n\\n### Required batch fields\\n- `batch_id`\\n- `scene_ids`\\n- `scene_count`\\n- `word_count`\\n\\n### Required screenplay property\\n- ordered canonical `scenes` with stable `scene_id`\\n\\n### Relevant channel config field\\n- `tts_polish_rules`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe adapter should:\\n- preserve run/job identity\\n- preserve batch identity\\n- preserve canonical scene order inside the selected batch\\n- preserve `scene_id`\\n- preserve `narration_original`\\n- inject `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\\n- include explicit instructions relevant to TTS polish behavior\\n- write a deterministic payload file\\n- declare the expected output path for the operator\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe adapter must **not**:\\n- call `tts_polish`\\n- perform polish itself\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge polish outputs\\n- decide retry policy\\n- rewrite screenplay content\\n- decide whether semantic review is needed\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\\nThe adapter writes one deterministic payload file per polish batch.\\n\\n### Minimum payload shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"account\\\": \\\"004\\\",\\n  \\\"language\\\": \\\"fr\\\",\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"batch\\\": {\\n    \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"tp_001\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_ids\\\": [\\\"scene_001\\\", \\\"scene_002\\\"],\\n    \\\"scene_count\\\": 2,\\n    \\\"word_count\\\": 148\\n  },\\n  \\\"tts_polish_rules\\\": [\\\"...\\\"],\\n  \\\"style_context\\\": {\\n    \\\"channel_name\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"reason\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"instructions\\\": {\\n    \\\"task\\\": \\\"Polish the narration text for TTS without changing meaning.\\\",\\n    \\\"requirements\\\": [\\\"...\\\"]\\n  },\\n  \\\"scenes\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"scene_id\\\": \\\"scene_001\\\",\\n      \\\"narration_original\\\": \\\"...\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"output_path\\\": \\\"C:/.../b1_pre_production/intermediate/tts_polish/tp_001_output.json\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output principles\\n\\nThe payload must make explicit:\\n- who the job/run is\\n- what polish batch is being processed\\n- which canonical scenes belong to the batch\\n- what original narration is being polished\\n- what rules govern polish behavior\\n- where the operator must write the result\\n\\nThe payload should be deterministic and re-creatable.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File-system expectations\\n\\n### Input payload path\\nShould live under the S1 canonical inputs area for `tts_polish`, for example:\\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/tts_polish/tp_001_input.json`\\n\\n### Output path declared inside payload\\nShould point to the canonical intermediate area for `tts_polish` results, for example:\\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/tts_polish/tp_001_output.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship with downstream components\\n\\n### Consumed by\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- supervisor retry loop\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- optional semantic review routing logic\\n\\n### Must remain compatible with\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error policy\\n\\nIf required inputs are missing or malformed, the adapter should fail clearly and deterministically.\\nIt should not silently invent critical fields.\\n\\nExamples:\\n- missing `batch_id`\\n- missing `scene_ids`\\n- missing `output_path`\\n- missing canonical `scene_id` mapping in screenplay\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/tts_polish_io_adapter.py`\\n\\nThis contract is the canonical behavioral layer for that implementation.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":221,"output":1315,"cacheRead":113920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115456,"cost":{"input":0.0005525,"output":0.019725,"cacheRead":0.02848,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.048757499999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774979875527,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0b2454488193811a114ab37e9643"}}
