rration\n 32 - Use selective retry when possible\n 33 - Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n 34 - Do not allow unvalidated batch outputs into canonical merge artifacts\n 35 - The supervisor remains the owner of sequencing and acceptance decisions\n+37 - Semantic review is a narrow escalation lane, not a default second pass for all polish batches\n 36 \n 37 ## Important current implementation note\n 38 `operator_batch_scheduler` currently plans waves and summarizes execution.\n 39 It does **not** itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":19},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980278332}}
{"type":"message","id":"20c94720","parentId":"f3aeb7bb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:04:48.152Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mgb1q5udefuOr6IAKsbGuz6X|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0cb9a7c0819399768b65ad8ead22","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\TOOLS.md","oldText":"## Supervisor deterministic skills implemented\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n","newText":"## Supervisor deterministic skills implemented\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n## Intended runtime validation lane for polish\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` is part of the canonical runtime architecture\n- deterministic validation should happen before merge\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` is a narrow escalation lane for ambiguous cases only\n- semantic review should not be treated as a default second pass for every polish batch\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\TOOLS.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Supervisor deterministic skills implemented\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Supervisor deterministic skills implemented\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n## Intended runtime validation lane for polish\\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` is part of the canonical runtime architecture\\n- deterministic validation should happen before merge\\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` is a narrow escalation lane for ambiguous cases only\\n- semantic review should not be treated as a default second pass for every polish batch\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":189,"output":337,"cacheRead":127872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128398,"cost":{"input":0.00047250000000000005,"output":0.0050550000000000005,"cacheRead":0.031967999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.037495499999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774980279194,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0cb805348193b7b6e1fd7af33da0"}}
