{"type":"message","id":"e667db5e","parentId":"8cef2bef","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:14.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou fazer um refinamento fino no scene_director e seguir directo para os operators de polish.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d4c2ce08193b886f88698f8ad71\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fpGEDXfLidT24tHzBaWIjgoX|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef3081939f206509d1e452e8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\EXAMPLES.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\EXAMPLES.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Vw1pTKwCuHrPZUSNwMo6qhWo|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef44819382d46c8fd5c3b405","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lHH9Mhd367hlalldF35ESkWG|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef508193b3bb78bb96a756ec","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish\\AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish\\\\AGENTS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_BnpM6UlnAuGyAR83Brt1KjQX|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef588193a0912474c51934f4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_NT20Ky3WsjIrpPihr4lY63jy|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef608193af96bfafe2952906","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ennSW3owm5JQdzWjdU1wcacO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef6c81938e2d745b688420d7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\\\AGENTS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9WMy85i9gk5l1tJuZNU2CgTt|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef748193bda45bde19ad5f55","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":186,"output":314,"cacheRead":133248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133748,"cost":{"input":0.000465,"output":0.00471,"cacheRead":0.033312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.038487}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774980424460,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d497d008193b76b9ffac28c8aab"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c4e9dc53","parentId":"e667db5e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:15.504Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_fpGEDXfLidT24tHzBaWIjgoX|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef3081939f206509d1e452e8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# EXAMPLES.md\n\n## Example Shape (Illustrative)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"sd_003\",\n  \"operator\": \"scene_director\",\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_01\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"The first signal of danger\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"Introduces the first concrete sign that the situation is shifting and creates tension.\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"setup and tension seed\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"The first warnings came long before anyone understood what they meant.\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 12,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 12\n    },\n    {\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_02\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"The pattern becomes visible\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"Shows that the earlier signal was not isolated and starts building narrative momentum.\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"escalation\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"Soon, the same pattern appeared again, this time impossible to ignore.\",\n      \"start_word\": 13,\n      \"end_word\": 24,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 12\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Good Characteristics\n\n- `scene_local_id` is sequential\n- scene boundaries are clean\n- `narration_original` preserves source text exactly\n- titles are clear\n- summaries are concise but meaningful\n- narrative functions are explicit\n- spans are batch-relative and non-overlapping\n\n## Bad Characteristics\n\n- rewriting the source text\n- adding visual suggestions instead of scene structure\n- vague scene titles like \"Scene 1\"\n- summaries that repeat the title without adding value\n- narrative functions that are too generic to help downstream work\n- gaps or overlaps in word spans\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435384}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ecfa154","parentId":"c4e9dc53","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:15.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Vw1pTKwCuHrPZUSNwMo6qhWo|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef44819382d46c8fd5c3b405","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md\n\n## Where This Operator Sits\n\n`op_s1_tts_polish` operates after canonical `screenplay.json` has already been created and before the final scene bible layer is built.\n\nIt acts after the supervisor has:\n- prepared ordered polish batches from the screenplay\n- selected the scenes for one `tp_###` batch\n- injected relevant polish rules/context\n\nIt acts before:\n- deterministic polish validation\n- optional semantic review of borderline changes\n- targeted scene-subset repair decisions\n- deterministic merge into canonical `tts_polished.json`\n- downstream audio generation\n\n## What It Receives\n\nThis operator receives a small ordered batch of scenes, not the full screenplay.\n\nThe input is expected to provide:\n- run/job context\n- batch identity\n- ordered batch scenes\n- each scene's original narration\n- language/channel-specific polish rules\n- explicit output expectations\n\n## What It Must Produce\n\nFor one polish batch, this operator must produce an ordered set of polished scene narrations that:\n- preserve original meaning and information\n- preserve scene identity and order\n- improve TTS readability/orality only where necessary\n- remain structurally valid for downstream validation and merge\n\n## Why This Output Matters\n\nThe output of `op_s1_tts_polish` becomes the narration layer that downstream TTS/audio generation will actually speak.\n\nIf it drifts semantically, the video says the wrong thing.\nIf it remains awkward, the voice sounds worse than necessary.\nSo this operator must optimize narrowly and safely.\n\n## Relationship to the Supervisor\n\nThe supervisor owns:\n- polish batching\n- scheduling\n- validation\n- semantic review escalation\n- retry policy\n- merge decisions\n\nThis operator owns:\n- oral normalization of the assigned batch\n- preserving semantic fidelity scene by scene\n- keeping polish adjustments narrow and controlled\n\n## Relationship to Downstream Work\n\nThis operator does not perform:\n- scene restructuring\n- validation\n- audio synthesis\n- timestamps/alignment\n- downstream visual or composition work\n\nHowever, its output directly affects the spoken narration, so precision here is critical.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435508}}
{"type":"message","id":"05ae8e7a","parentId":"2ecfa154","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:15.740Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_lHH9Mhd367hlalldF35ESkWG|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef508193b3bb78bb96a756ec","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - op_s1_tts_polish\n\n## Purpose of This Workspace\n\nThis workspace exists to give `op_s1_tts_polish` the minimum operational context needed to perform safe, controlled TTS polish on small ordered scene batches.\n\n## What This Agent Should Read\n\nAt minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n\n## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Do not change meaning.\n- Do not add/remove information.\n- Do not absorb downstream audio or upstream narrative-structure responsibilities.\n- Do not improvise around broken contracts; surface the conflict through the proper supervisory loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435626}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4c61c34","parentId":"05ae8e7a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:15.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_BnpM6UlnAuGyAR83Brt1KjQX|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef588193a0912474c51934f4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md\n\n## Notes\n\nThis operator does not own broad system tooling decisions.\nIts operational contract is mostly defined by:\n- the supervisor-prepared payload\n- S1 contracts\n- workspace rules/prompt/examples\n\n## Important Structural Notes\n\n- Dispatch unit: small ordered scene batches\n- Comparison sensitivity: scene-by-scene inside the batch\n- Validation is supervisor-owned\n- Semantic review is optional and only for ambiguous cases\n- Preferred correction mode: affected scene subset when possible\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435740}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2f8c2d5","parentId":"b4c61c34","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:15.971Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NT20Ky3WsjIrpPihr4lY63jy|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef608193af96bfafe2952906","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md\n\n## Where This Reviewer Sits\n\n`op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` sits inside the `tts_polish` supervisory loop as an auxiliary semantic-arbitration layer.\n\nIt is not part of the normal happy path for every batch.\nIt is invoked only when deterministic validation detects meaningful changes but cannot safely classify them as acceptable vs unsafe without interpretation.\n\n## What Happens Before It\n\nBefore this reviewer is called:\n- the supervisor dispatches a `tts_polish` batch\n- `tts_polish` returns a batch output\n- deterministic validation checks structure, mapping, and obvious drift\n- the validator flags some scene subset as semantically ambiguous\n\n## What It Receives\n\nThis reviewer should receive only the material needed to judge the ambiguity:\n- affected scene subset\n- original narration\n- TTS-polished narration\n- validator flags/reasons\n- relevant language/polish rules if needed\n\n## What It Must Produce\n\nIt must produce a narrow semantic judgment per affected scene that helps the supervisor decide whether to:\n- approve\n- repair a scene subset\n- regenerate a batch if needed\n\n## Why It Matters\n\nWithout this reviewer, the supervisor would either:\n- over-trust deterministic heuristics in ambiguous language cases, or\n- over-escalate repair unnecessarily\n\nThis reviewer exists to keep the loop precise without becoming bloated.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435740}}
{"type":"message","id":"c56884a2","parentId":"d2f8c2d5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:16.089Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ennSW3owm5JQdzWjdU1wcacO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef6c81938e2d745b688420d7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer\n\n## Purpose of This Workspace\n\nThis workspace exists to give the semantic reviewer the minimum operational context needed to arbitrate ambiguous `tts_polish` cases safely and consistently.\n\n## What This Agent Should Read\n\nAt minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n\n## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, semantic, and action-oriented.\nIt should not behave like a main pipeline operator, structural validator, or freeform editor.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Do not rewrite scenes instead of judging them.\n- Do not widen review scope unnecessarily.\n- Do not replace supervisor authority.\n- Do not treat stylistic preference as semantic truth.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980435973}}
{"type":"message","id":"9324a616","parentId":"c56884a2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:16.235Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9WMy85i9gk5l1tJuZNU2CgTt|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d51ef748193bda45bde19ad5f55","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md\n\n## Notes\n\nThis reviewer exists only for ambiguous `tts_polish` cases that deterministic validation cannot safely classify.\n\n## Important Structural Notes\n\n- Preferred review scope: affected scene subset only\n- Preferred focus: semantic preservation vs unsafe drift\n- Output should be directly actionable by the supervisor\n- This reviewer is not the policy owner; the supervisor remains the policy owner\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774980436089}}
{"type":"message","id":"84e82a8a","parentId":"9324a616","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:07:36.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou fazer um refinamento curto no scene_director e alinhar explicitamente os operators de polish com o lane canónico que fixámos.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d583abc8193b340fea57ed62566\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_zQ3bkw6lf72EXoVOqrIP5emf|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc0d59080881939151e54e19e83d0f","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\CONTEXT.md","oldText":"## Relationship to the Supervisor\n\nThe supervisor owns:\n- batching\n- scheduling\n- validation\n- retry policy\n- merge decisions\n\nThis operator owns:\n- scene-level interpretation of the assigned batch\n- clean narrative division\n- faithful scene-by-scene text preservation\n","newText":"## Relationship to the Supervisor\n\nThe supervisor owns:\n- batching\n- scheduling\n- validation\n- retry policy\n- merge decisions\n- approval / reject / repair routing\n\nThis operator owns:\n- scene-level interpretation of the assigned batch\n- clean narrative division\n- faithful scene-by-scene text preservation\n\n## Repair mode\n\nWhen reinvoked in repair mode, this operator should:\n- treat the task as batch-local\n- obey the supervisor's structured correction focus\n- avoid redesigning unaffected scenes unless correction logically requires it\n- preserve already-sound parts of the batch when possible\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\CONTEXT.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Relationship to the Supervisor\\n\\nThe supervisor owns:\\n- batching\\n- scheduling\\n- validation\\n- retry policy\\n- merge decisions\\n\\nThis operator owns:\\n- scene-level interpretation of the assigned batch\\n- clean narrative division\\n- faithful scene-by-scene text preservation\\n\",\"newText\":\"## R