{"type":"message","id":"295c3e8b","parentId":"becb0143","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:31:03.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_uItATNvE4A2d8oKyBHv3id5Q|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc12da7244819386f04d0ded9bcdf2","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_bible_builder_contract.md","content":"# S1 Scene Bible Builder Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic builder that produces the initial `scene_bible.json` at the end of S1._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `scene_bible_builder` compiles the initial canonical `scene_bible.json` from:\n- canonical screenplay structure\n- canonical TTS-polished narration layer\n- job metadata\n\nIt creates the S1-owned living document that downstream sectors will enrich rather than replace.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits after:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- successful completion of the main screenplay + polish loops\n\nAnd before:\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- final checkpointing / sector completion\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 as a shared deterministic sector component\n\n### Not owned by\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- the supervisor as freeform author\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe builder should:\n- preserve canonical `scene_id`\n- carry forward scene-level structure from screenplay\n- carry forward TTS narration from canonical polish output\n- preserve the original narration reference\n- initialize reserved downstream fields explicitly\n- mark S1 as the contributing sector\n- write a stable initial scene bible artifact\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe builder must **not**:\n- perform semantic generation\n- validate schema by itself\n- overwrite downstream sector contributions\n- collapse distinct narration layers into ambiguous naming\n\n---\n\n## Canonical field rule\n\nAt S1 stage, the scene bible should preserve both:\n- original narration reference\n- TTS-ready narration layer\n\nPreferred semantic model:\n- `narration_original` = original source text for the scene\n- `narration_tts` = TTS-optimized narration layer\n\nIf a compatibility field like `narration` exists, its meaning must remain explicit and not obscure the distinction between original and TTS-ready narration.\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe builder should receive:\n- canonical screenplay scenes\n- canonical merged polish scenes\n- job metadata\n\nThe builder should align screenplay/polish primarily by:\n- `scene_id`\n\nnot by fragile positional assumptions alone.\n\n---\n\n## Output expectations\n\nThe builder should produce a bible with at minimum:\n- top-level run/job metadata\n- stable `scene_count`\n- ordered `scenes`\n\nEach scene should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts` (preferred canonical naming)\n- reserved downstream fields\n- sector contribution metadata\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py`\n\nAt the time of this contract, the implementation is a good base but still reflects older `polished` naming assumptions and should be aligned to the canonical narration-field model.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_scene_bible_builder_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Scene Bible Builder Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic builder that produces the initial `scene_bible.json` at the end of S1._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `scene_bible_builder` compiles the initial canonical `scene_bible.json` from:\\n- canonical screenplay structure\\n- canonical TTS-polished narration layer\\n- job metadata\\n\\nIt creates the S1-owned living document that downstream sectors will enrich rather than replace.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits after:\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- successful completion of the main screenplay + polish loops\\n\\nAnd before:\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- final checkpointing / sector completion\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 as a shared deterministic sector component\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- the supervisor as freeform author\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe builder should:\\n- preserve canonical `scene_id`\\n- carry forward scene-level structure from screenplay\\n- carry forward TTS narration from canonical polish output\\n- preserve the original narration reference\\n- initialize reserved downstream fields explicitly\\n- mark S1 as the contributing sector\\n- write a stable initial scene bible artifact\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe builder must **not**:\\n- perform semantic generation\\n- validate schema by itself\\n- overwrite downstream sector contributions\\n- collapse distinct narration layers into ambiguous naming\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical field rule\\n\\nAt S1 stage, the scene bible should preserve both:\\n- original narration reference\\n- TTS-ready narration layer\\n\\nPreferred semantic model:\\n- `narration_original` = original source text for the scene\\n- `narration_tts` = TTS-optimized narration layer\\n\\nIf a compatibility field like `narration` exists, its meaning must remain explicit and not obscure the distinction between original and TTS-ready narration.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe builder should receive:\\n- canonical screenplay scenes\\n- canonical merged polish scenes\\n- job metadata\\n\\nThe builder should align screenplay/polish primarily by:\\n- `scene_id`\\n\\nnot by fragile positional assumptions alone.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output expectations\\n\\nThe builder should produce a bible with at minimum:\\n- top-level run/job metadata\\n- stable `scene_count`\\n- ordered `scenes`\\n\\nEach scene should preserve:\\n- `scene_id`\\n- `scene_title`\\n- `scene_summary`\\n- `narrative_function`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `narration_tts` (preferred canonical naming)\\n- reserved downstream fields\\n- sector contribution metadata\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py`\\n\\nAt the time of this contract, the implementation is a good base but still reflects older `polished` naming assumptions and should be aligned to the canonical narration-field model.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":129,"output":743,"cacheRead":145024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145896,"cost":{"input":0.00032250000000000003,"output":0.011145,"cacheRead":0.036256,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047723499999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774981848583,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc12d9604081938ac7738827aa9ff8"}}
