{"type":"message","id":"953a0898","parentId":"229e999a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:31:17.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_KP526oVtM7HbymjbzkW42x4n|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc12ecd4548193811ffb41b88d0842","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_bible_schema_validator_contract.md","content":"# S1 Scene Bible Schema Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic schema-validation layer for `scene_bible.json` at the end of S1._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `scene_bible_schema_validator` validates that the produced `scene_bible.json` is structurally acceptable for handoff to downstream sectors.\n\nIts role is to validate schema/staging readiness, not to regenerate content.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits after:\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n\nAnd before:\n- final checkpointing\n- final sector completion\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 as a shared deterministic sector component\n\n### Not owned by\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- downstream sectors\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe validator should:\n- validate top-level bible structure\n- validate `scene_count`\n- validate ordered scene objects exist\n- validate duplicate `scene_id` problems\n- validate required-at-S1 fields\n- validate reserved-for-later fields are present when expected by schema policy\n- distinguish hard schema errors from softer staging warnings\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe validator must **not**:\n- rewrite the bible\n- invent missing content\n- act as a semantic-quality judge of scene content\n\n---\n\n## Staging rule\n\nThe scene bible schema should distinguish clearly between:\n- fields required at S1 completion\n- fields reserved for later sectors\n\nA field may be required to exist at S1 stage while still being allowed to be `null` until later sectors fill it.\nThat distinction should remain explicit in the schema policy.\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation note\n\nThe current implementation lives in:\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n\nAt the time of this contract, the implementation is functional but the required-vs-reserved staging semantics should be kept especially clear, since some downstream-owned fields may intentionally remain null at S1 completion.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_scene_bible_schema_validator_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Scene Bible Schema Validator Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic schema-validation layer for `scene_bible.json` at the end of S1._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe `scene_bible_schema_validator` validates that the produced `scene_bible.json` is structurally acceptable for handoff to downstream sectors.\\n\\nIts role is to validate schema/staging readiness, not to regenerate content.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Position inside S1\\n\\nThis component sits after:\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n\\nAnd before:\\n- final checkpointing\\n- final sector completion\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Ownership\\n\\n### Owned by\\n- S1 as a shared deterministic sector component\\n\\n### Not owned by\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- downstream sectors\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe validator should:\\n- validate top-level bible structure\\n- validate `scene_count`\\n- validate ordered scene objects exist\\n- validate duplicate `scene_id` problems\\n- validate required-at-S1 fields\\n- validate reserved-for-later fields are present when expected by schema policy\\n- distinguish hard schema errors from softer staging warnings\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\nThe validator must **not**:\\n- rewrite the bible\\n- invent missing content\\n- act as a semantic-quality judge of scene content\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Staging rule\\n\\nThe scene bible schema should distinguish clearly between:\\n- fields required at S1 completion\\n- fields reserved for later sectors\\n\\nA field may be required to exist at S1 stage while still being allowed to be `null` until later sectors fill it.\\nThat distinction should remain explicit in the schema policy.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation note\\n\\nThe current implementation lives in:\\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\\n\\nAt the time of this contract, the implementation is functional but the required-vs-reserved staging semantics should be kept especially clear, since some downstream-owned fields may intentionally remain null at S1 completion.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":151,"output":508,"cacheRead":145792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":146451,"cost":{"input":0.0003775,"output":0.00762,"cacheRead":0.036448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0444455}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774981865006,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc12e9e5008193823072b71433fbd2"}}
