{"type":"message","id":"fe1d1152","parentId":"ef4c3ee8","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:36:39.078Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qNJ5XLmQtGuv5T2V4OSyVLnd|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc143569108193ab9a062073a366a5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S1 Pre-Production — Entry Point / Supervisor.\n\nOrchestrates: scene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder.\nManages retries (max 3 per step) and checkpoints.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_director_runner import run_scene_director, save_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.screenplay_validator import validate_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.tts_polish_runner import run_tts_polish, save_tts_polished\nfrom runtime.s1.polish_validator import validate_polish\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_builder import build_scene_bible, write_scene_bible\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_schema_validator import validate_scene_bible_schema\nfrom runtime.s1.checkpoint_writer import write_checkpoint\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\nMAX_RETRIES = 3\n\n\ndef start_s1(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: str | Path,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run S1 Pre-Production: script_raw -> scene_bible.json.\n\n    Args:\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n        video_root: Path to initialized run directory.\n        model: OpenAI model for LLM steps.\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result with success, paths, checkpoints, next_step.\n    \"\"\"\n    video_root = Path(video_root)\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    account = job.get(\"account\", \"\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"\")\n\n    # Load channel config\n    config = _load_config(account, language)\n\n    # Read script\n    script_path = video_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt not found\", \"missing_script\")\n    script_raw = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not script_raw.strip():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt is empty\", \"empty_script\")\n\n    checkpoints_written = []\n\n    # ===== STEP 1: Scene Director =====\n    try:\n        screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_failed\")\n\n    screenplay_path = save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step1_screenplay\", \"scene_director\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(screenplay), \"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 2: Screenplay Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        validation = validate_screenplay(script_raw, screenplay)\n\n        if validation[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            # Retry: re-run scene director\n            try:\n                screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n                save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Screenplay validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {validation['details']}\", \"screenplay_validation_failed\")\n\n    # Save validation result\n    val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay_validation.json\"\n    val_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated\", \"screenplay_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 3: TTS Polish =====\n    try:\n        polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_failed\")\n\n    polished_path = save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step3_tts_polished\", \"tts_polish\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\"],\n                     extra={\"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 4: Polish Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        polish_val = validate_polish(screenplay, polished)\n\n        if polish_val[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            try:\n                polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n                save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Polish validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {polish_val['details']}\", \"polish_validation_failed\")\n\n    polish_val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"polish_validation.json\"\n    polish_val_path.write_text(json.dumps(polish_val, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step4_polish_validated\", \"polish_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 5: Scene Bible Builder =====\n    bible = build_scene_bible(polished, job, screenplay)\n\n    # Schema validate\n    schema_val = validate_scene_bible_schema(bible)\n    if not schema_val[\"valid\"]:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene bible schema validation failed: {schema_val['errors']}\", \"scene_bible_schema_failed\")\n\n    bible_path = write_scene_bible(bible, video_root)\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step5_scene_bible\", \"scene_bible_builder\",\n                     [\"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"])})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 6: S1 Complete =====\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_complete\", \"s1_supervisor\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\",\n                      \"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\n                         \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n                         \"screenplay_validated\": True,\n                         \"polish_validated\": True,\n                         \"scene_bible_schema_valid\": True,\n                     })\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_complete.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_complete\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"b1_complete\",\n        \"screenplay_path\": screenplay_path,\n        \"tts_polished_path\": polished_path,\n        \"scene_bible_path\": bible_path,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": schema_val.get(\"warnings\", []),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict:\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\")\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n\n\ndef _error(job_id: str, message: str, code: str) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": code,\n        \"screenplay_path\": \"\",\n        \"tts_polished_path\": \"\",\n        \"scene_bible_path\": \"\",\n        \"checkpoints_written\": [],\n        \"scene_count\": 0,\n        \"next_step\": None,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982198957}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f76d40e","parentId":"fe1d1152","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:37:11.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — há poluição legada real, e agora já dá para separar isso com bastante clareza.\n\n## Leitura objectiva: o que está canónico vs legado\n\n### Runtime `runtime/s1`\n## Canónico / alinhado com a arquitectura nova\n### `supervisor_skills/`\n- `s1_preflight_checker.py`\n- `s1_paths_resolver.py`\n- `script_batch_planner.py`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter.py`\n- `scene_director_output_validator.py`\n- `screenplay_merger.py`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner.py`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter.py`\n- `tts_polish_merger.py`\n- `retry_planner.py`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler.py`\n- `s1_result_summarizer.py`\n\n### Shared deterministic components úteis\n- `screenplay_validator.py`\n- `polish_validator.py`\n- `scene_bible_builder.py`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n- `checkpoint_writer.py`\n\nEsses fazem sentido manter.\n\n---\n\n## Legado / transitório / candidato forte a remoção ou isolamento\n### 1. `s1_start.py`\nHoje ele é claramente:\n- **runtime antigo linear**\n- chama directo:\n  - `scene_director_runner`\n  - `tts_polish_runner`\n- bypassa boa parte da arquitectura nova:\n  - supervisor skills\n  - operators OpenClaw reais\n  - lane batch-level canónico\n  - semantic reviewer lane\n  - scheduler canónico\n\nEntão o status dele, na minha leitura, é:\n\n> **transitional legacy bootstrap**\n> e não runtime canónico\n\n### 2. `scene_director_runner.py`\nTambém está com cara forte de legado/transição porque:\n- usa direct OpenAI call\n- faz chunking interno próprio\n- absorve lógica que hoje deveria estar repartida entre:\n  - planner\n  - io_adapter\n  - operator OpenClaw\n  - output validator\n  - merger\n\nStatus:\n> **legacy compatibility wrapper**\ne deveria ser tratado como tal explicitamente\n\n### 3. `tts_polish_runner.py`\nMesmo problema:\n- direct OpenAI call\n- shape antigo\n- não representa a topologia OpenClaw canónica\n\nStatus:\n> **legacy compatibility wrapper**\n\n### 4. `__pycache__/`\nIsto é lixo operacional para cleanup.\nNão é parte arquitectural.\n\n---\n\n# Docs `docs/contracts/s1`\n## Canónico / útil\nTodos estes fazem sentido agora:\n- `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `s1_scene_director_contract.md`\n- `s1_scene_director_io_adapter_contract.md`\n- `s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md`\n- `s1_screenplay_merger_contract.md`\n- `s1_screenplay_validator_contract.md`\n- `s1_tts_polish_contract.md`\n- `s1_tts_polish_io_adapter_contract.md`\n- `s1_tts_polish_merger_contract.md`\n- `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md`\n- `s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer_contract.md`\n- `s1_retry_planner_contract.md`\n- `s1_operator_batch_scheduler_contract.md`\n- `s1_polish_validator_contract.md`\n- `s1_scene_bible_builder_contract.md`\n- `s1_scene_bible_schema_validator_contract.md`\n\n## Único que eu marcaria como redundante / potencialmente temporário\n### `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md`\nEu criei esse para explicitar a lacuna de runtime na altura em que a peça ainda estava mais “conceitualmente presente” do que claramente aterrada.\n\nAgora, olhando a pasta:\n- já existe `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md`\n- o `_runtime_` pode acabar ficando redundante e gerar confusão\n\nEntão este é um forte candidato a:\n- **absorver conteúdo útil no contract principal**\n- e depois **remover o runtime-specific duplicate**\n\n---\n\n# Diagnóstico de limpeza\n## Se quisermos deixar isto realmente limpo, eu recomendaria esta classificação:\n\n### Manter\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/*`\n- `runtime/s1/screenplay_validator.py`\n- `runtime/s1/polish_validator.py`\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py`\n- `runtime/s1/scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n- `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`\n- contratos canónicos actuais\n- workspaces dos agents em `/.openclaw/agents`\n\n### Marcar como legado explícito\n- `runtime/s1/s1_start.py`\n- `runtime/s1/scene_director_runner.py`\n- `runtime/s1/tts_polish_runner.py`\n\n### Remover com segurança\n- `runtime/s1/__pycache__/`\n- possivelmente `docs/contracts/s1/s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md` depois de consolidar\n\n---\n\n# O que eu NÃO faria ainda\nEu **não apagaria já**:\n- `s1_start.py`\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\nPorque ainda precisamos confirmar se algum ponto do runtime ou testes está a depender deles.\n\nMas eu faria uma destas duas coisas:\n## opção segura\n- mover para uma pasta tipo:\n  - `runtime/s1/legacy/`\n- e deixar doc clara de que são transitional compatibility components\n\n## opção ainda mais conservadora\n- manter no sítio por agora\n- mas marcar claramente no topo dos ficheiros e na doc:\n  - `LEGACY`\n  - `NON-CANONICAL`\n  - `TRANSITIONAL ONLY`\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação prática\n## Fase 1 — limpeza sem risco\nEu faria já:\n1. remover `__pycache__/`\n2. consolidar/remover o contract redundante:\n   - `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md`\n3. marcar explicitamente estes 3 ficheiros como legacy:\n   - `s1_start.py`\n   - `scene_director_runner.py`\n   - `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\n## Fase 2 — limpeza estrutural melhor\nDepois disso:\n4. criar talvez uma pasta:\n   - `runtime/s1/legacy/`\n5. mover os 3 para lá\n6. actualizar imports/referências se necessário\n\nMas isso eu faria com mais cuidado.\n\n---\n\n# Conclusão curta\nSim — **há poluição legada real**, mas agora ela está bem identificável.\n\n## Candidatos mais claros\n### Runtime legado\n- `s1_start.py`\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\n### Lixo operacional\n- `__pycache__/`\n\n### Contract possivelmente redundante\n- `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md`\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu posso fazer **agora a Fase 1 segura**:\n- apagar `__pycache__`\n- consolidar o contract redundante\n- marcar os 3 ficheiros legacy com headers/documentação clara\n\nE depois te mostro o estado limpo antes de qualquer move mais agressivo.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc143c5dd8819393f91e04f06bc9cf\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3561,"output":1495,"cacheRead":134016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139072,"cost":{"input":0.0089025,"output":0.022425,"cacheRead":0.033504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0648315}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774982199680,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14394e9881938e0a4c5a0ca5f3bd"}}
