{"type":"message","id":"26b432aa","parentId":"0e01d8c3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:38:45.622Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DNTN3EemmEkdfvL7oIwbPUi7|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b56270819396f50db76f7d7655","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\tests\\test_s1_start.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\tests\\\\test_s1_start.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_WQJ51psgwkeUVASTVVksT01A|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b5628081939610e7a34670fbb9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_director_runner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\scene_director_runner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cBuIsFXJnF4DMPX2kL4P9FuD|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b562888193a796f9c5788a53b4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish_runner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\tts_polish_runner.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":122558,"output":139,"cacheRead":16896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139593,"cost":{"input":0.30639500000000003,"output":0.002085,"cacheRead":0.0042239999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.31270400000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774982319644,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b0827c8193b7d5eee89666cd12"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aafe248b","parentId":"26b432aa","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:38:50.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_DNTN3EemmEkdfvL7oIwbPUi7|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b56270819396f50db76f7d7655","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Tests for S1 start / supervisor.\n\nLLM-dependent steps are mocked.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport pytest\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\n\nfrom runtime.s1.s1_start import start_s1\n\nFIXTURES = Path(__file__).parent / \"fixtures\" / \"s1\"\n\nSAMPLE_JOB = {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\",\n    \"channel_name\": \"C004 FRA\",\n    \"sheet_scripts_id\": \"test\",\n    \"sheet_tracking_id\": \"test\",\n    \"drive_folder_id\": \"test\",\n    \"v3_config\": \"test\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T15:00:00Z\",\n    \"pub_row\": 25,\n}\n\n\ndef _load(name):\n    with open(FIXTURES / name, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        if name.endswith(\".json\"):\n            return json.load(f)\n        return f.read()\n\n\ndef _setup_run(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Create minimal run structure with script.\"\"\"\n    script_dir = tmp_path / \"inputs\" / \"script\"\n    script_dir.mkdir(parents=True)\n    script_text = _load(\"sample_script_raw.txt\")\n    (script_dir / \"script_raw.txt\").write_text(script_text, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    (tmp_path / \"checkpoints\").mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    return script_text\n\n\nclass TestS1HappyPath:\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_tts_polish\")\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director\")\n    def test_success(self, mock_director, mock_polish, tmp_path):\n        _setup_run(tmp_path)\n        screenplay = _load(\"sample_screenplay_valid.json\")\n        polished = _load(\"sample_tts_polished_valid.json\")\n        # Extend polished to match screenplay length\n        while len(polished) < len(screenplay):\n            polished.append({\n                \"scene_id\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"scene_id\"],\n                \"original\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"],\n                \"polished\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"],\n                \"changes\": [],\n            })\n\n        mock_director.return_value = screenplay\n        mock_polish.return_value = polished\n\n        result = start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n\n        assert result[\"success\"] is True\n        assert result[\"status\"] == \"s1_complete\"\n        assert result[\"next_step\"] == \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\"\n        assert result[\"scene_count\"] == len(screenplay)\n\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_tts_polish\")\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director\")\n    def test_all_artifacts_written(self, mock_director, mock_polish, tmp_path):\n        _setup_run(tmp_path)\n        screenplay = _load(\"sample_screenplay_valid.json\")\n        polished = _load(\"sample_tts_polished_valid.json\")\n        while len(polished) < len(screenplay):\n            polished.append({\"scene_id\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"scene_id\"], \"original\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"polished\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"changes\": []})\n\n        mock_director.return_value = screenplay\n        mock_polish.return_value = polished\n\n        start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n\n        assert (tmp_path / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay.json\").exists()\n        assert (tmp_path / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay_validation.json\").exists()\n        assert (tmp_path / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"tts_polished.json\").exists()\n        assert (tmp_path / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"polish_validation.json\").exists()\n        assert (tmp_path / \"scene_bible.json\").exists()\n\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_tts_polish\")\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director\")\n    def test_all_checkpoints_written(self, mock_director, mock_polish, tmp_path):\n        _setup_run(tmp_path)\n        screenplay = _load(\"sample_screenplay_valid.json\")\n        polished = _load(\"sample_tts_polished_valid.json\")\n        while len(polished) < len(screenplay):\n            polished.append({\"scene_id\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"scene_id\"], \"original\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"polished\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"changes\": []})\n\n        mock_director.return_value = screenplay\n        mock_polish.return_value = polished\n\n        result = start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n\n        expected = [\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\", \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\",\n                    \"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\", \"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\",\n                    \"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\", \"b1_complete.json\"]\n        assert result[\"checkpoints_written\"] == expected\n        for cp in expected:\n            assert (tmp_path / \"checkpoints\" / cp).exists()\n\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_tts_polish\")\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director\")\n    def test_scene_bible_at_root(self, mock_director, mock_polish, tmp_path):\n        _setup_run(tmp_path)\n        screenplay = _load(\"sample_screenplay_valid.json\")\n        polished = _load(\"sample_tts_polished_valid.json\")\n        while len(polished) < len(screenplay):\n            polished.append({\"scene_id\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"scene_id\"], \"original\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"polished\": screenplay[len(polished)][\"narration\"], \"changes\": []})\n\n        mock_director.return_value = screenplay\n        mock_polish.return_value = polished\n\n        result = start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n\n        # scene_bible.json must be at ROOT, not inside b1_pre_production\n        assert (tmp_path / \"scene_bible.json\").exists()\n        assert not (tmp_path / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"scene_bible.json\").exists()\n\n\nclass TestS1Failures:\n    def test_missing_script(self, tmp_path):\n        (tmp_path / \"checkpoints\").mkdir(parents=True)\n        result = start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n        assert result[\"success\"] is False\n        assert \"missing_script\" in result[\"errors\"][0][\"code\"]\n\n    @patch(\"runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director\")\n    def test_scene_director_failure(self, mock_director, tmp_path):\n        _setup_run(tmp_path)\n        mock_director.side_effect = Exception(\"API error\")\n\n        result = start_s1(SAMPLE_JOB, tmp_path)\n        assert result[\"success\"] is False\n        assert \"scene_director\" in result[\"errors\"][0][\"code\"]\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982330373}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c2ad4be","parentId":"aafe248b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:38:50.623Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_WQJ51psgwkeUVASTVVksT01A|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b5628081939610e7a34670fbb9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Scene Director Runner — legacy compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\n\nThis module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\nstill imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay`.\n\nIt no longer represents the canonical architecture for S1 scene generation.\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- batch planning outside the operator\n- batch-level scene_director outputs\n- per-batch validation\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\n\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to the newer\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\n# Max words per chunk sent to the model\nCHUNK_TARGET_WORDS = 600\n\n\ndef run_scene_director(\n    script_raw: str,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Split raw script into structured scenes using the newer scene contract.\n\n    Compatibility behavior:\n    - still accepts the old prototype signature used by `s1_start.py`\n    - still chunks long scripts internally\n    - but now returns scene objects aligned with the newer S1 contracts\n    \"\"\"\n    words_min, words_max = config.get(\"scene_words_range\", [35, 75])\n\n    chunks = _split_into_chunks(script_raw, CHUNK_TARGET_WORDS)\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    global_scene_counter = 0\n    global_word_cursor = 1\n\n    for chunk_text in chunks:\n        chunk_word_count = len(_normalize_text(chunk_text).split())\n        system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are the scene_director for S1 pre-production.\n\nYour job is to transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes.\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n1. Use clean narrative scene boundaries. Do NOT cut mid-sentence unless absolutely necessary.\n2. Preserve EVERY SINGLE WORD of the input text in narration_original. Do NOT add, remove, summarize, paraphrase, or modify wording.\n3. The concatenation of all narration_original fields must reproduce the input text EXACTLY, word for word.\n4. Use batch-relative word coordinates. The first word in this batch is word 1.\n5. Do not generate global scene IDs.\n6. Do not do visual planning, prompt writing, asset planning, or TTS polish.\n7. For each scene, return:\n   - scene_local_id: sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...)\n   - scene_title: short clear label\n   - scene_summary: concise summary of the scene's purpose/content\n   - narrative_function: the narrative role of the scene\n   - narration_original: exact source text for that scene\n   - start_word: batch-relative start word\n   - end_word: batch-relative end word\n   - estimated_scene_word_count: exact word count implied by the span\n8. No gaps and no overlaps between scene spans.\n9. Aim for scene sizes compatible with configured scene_words_range ({words_min}-{words_max}) when natural narrative structure allows.\n\nOUTPUT: Return JSON object with a 'scenes' array. Nothing else.\"\"\"\n\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=model,\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Transform this text batch into ordered scenes:\\n\\n{chunk_text}\"},\n            ],\n            temperature=0.1,\n            response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n        )\n\n        content = response.choices[0].message.content\n        parsed = json.loads(content)\n        chunk_scenes = _extract_scenes(parsed)\n        _normalize_chunk_scenes(chunk_scenes, chunk_text)\n\n        for scene in chunk_scenes:\n            global_scene_counter += 1\n            scene[\"scene_id\"] = f\"scene_{global_scene_counter:03d}\"\n            scene[\"source_batch_id\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_batch_scene_index\"] = None\n            scene[\"source_scene_local_id\"] = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n            scene[\"global_start_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"start_word\"]) - 1\n            scene[\"global_end_word\"] = global_word_cursor + int(scene[\"end_word\"]) - 1\n\n        all_scenes.extend(chunk_scenes)\n        global_word_cursor += chunk_word_count\n\n    return all_scenes\n\n\ndef _split_into_chunks(text: str, target_words: int) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Split text into chunks at sentence boundaries.\"\"\"\n    sentences = re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", text.strip())\n    chunks = []\n    current_chunk = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        word_count = len(sentence.split())\n        if current_words + word_count > target_words and current_chunk:\n            chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n            current_chunk = [sentence]\n            current_words = word_count\n        else:\n            current_chunk.append(sentence)\n            current_words += word_count\n\n    if current_chunk:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk))\n\n    return chunks\n\n\ndef _extract_scenes(parsed: Any) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Extract scenes list from various model response formats.\"\"\"\n    if isinstance(parsed, dict):\n        if \"scenes\" in parsed:\n            scenes = parsed[\"scenes\"]\n            if isinstance(scenes, list):\n                return scenes\n        for val in parsed.values():\n            if isinstance(val, list) and len(val) > 0:\n                return val\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response: dict with keys {list(parsed.keys())}\")\n    if isinstance(parsed, list):\n        return parsed\n    raise ValueError(f\"Unexpected response format: {type(parsed)}\")\n\n\ndef _normalize_chunk_scenes(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], chunk_text: str) -> None:\n    chunk_tokens = _normalize_text(chunk_text).split()\n    cursor = 1\n\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {index} is not an object\")\n\n        scene_local_id = scene.get(\"scene_local_id\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_local_id, str) or not scene_local_id.strip():\n            scene_local_id = f\"scene_{index:02d}\"\n        scene[\"scene_local_id\"] = scene_local_id\n\n        narration_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        if not isinstance(narration_original, str) or not narration_original.strip():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has no narration_original\")\n\n        narration_tokens = _normalize_text(narration_original).split()\n        word_count = len(narration_tokens)\n        if word_count == 0:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Scene {scene_local_id} has empty narration_original\")\n\n        expected_tokens = chunk_tokens[cursor - 1: cursor - 1 + word_count]\n        if narration_tokens != expected_tokens:\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"Scene {scene_local_id} narration_original does not match chunk source at words {cursor}-{cursor + word_count - 1}\"\n            )\n\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_title\", f\"Scene {index}\")\n        scene.setdefault(\"scene_summary\", scene[\"scene_title\"])\n        scene.setdefault(\"narrative_function\", \"narrative progression\")\n        scene[\"start_word\"] = cursor\n        scene[\"end_word\"] = cursor + word_count - 1\n        scene[\"estimated_scene_word_count\"] = word_count\n\n        cursor += word_count\n\n    if cursor - 1 != len(chunk_tokens):\n        raise ValueError(\n            f\"Chunk scene coverage incomplete: covered {cursor - 1} of {len(chunk_tokens)} words\"\n        )\n\n\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\n    text = text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n    return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n\n\ndef save_screenplay(\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save screenplay.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"screenplay.json\"\n    screenplay = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n    }\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(screenplay, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982330508}}
{"type":"message","id":"3da51f3d","parentId":"2c2ad4be","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:38:50.745Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cBuIsFXJnF4DMPX2kL4P9FuD|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14b562888193a796f9c5788a53b4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"TTS Polish Runner — polishes narration text for Text-to-Speech.\n\nProcesses ONE scene at a time for maximum precision.\nApplies language-specific polish rules from channel config.\nDoes NOT change meaning, only pronunciation/readability for TTS.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\ndef run_tts_polish(\n    screenplay: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Polish screenplay narrations for TTS, one scene at a time.\n\n    Args:\n        screenplay: Scene list with 'narration_original' field.\n        config: Channel config with tts_polish_rules.\n        job: PM job dict.\n        model: OpenAI model to use.\n\n    Returns:\n        List of polished scene dicts with original, polished, changes.\n    \"\"\"\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"en\")\n    rules = config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", [])\n\n    if not rules:\n        return [\n            {\n                \"scene_id\": s.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\"),\n                \"original\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"polished\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n            for i, s in enumerate(screenplay)\n        ]\n\n    rules_text = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {r}\" for r in rules)\n\n    system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are a TTS text polisher for {language} narration.\n\nApply ONLY these rules:\n{rules_text}\n\nCRITICAL:\n- Do NOT change meaning.\n- Do NOT add or remove information.\n- Do NOT change verb tenses.\n- Do NOT combine or split sentences.\n- Keep numbers as digits.\n- Only apply the rules above.\n\nReturn a JSON object with:\n- \"original\": the exact input text (unchanged)\n- \"polished\": the polished version\n- \"changes\": list of changes made (brief descriptions, empty list if no changes)\"\"\"\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_polished = []\n\n    for i, scene in enumerate(screenplay):\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\")\n        narration = scene[\"narration_original\"]\n\n        try:\n            response = client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": narration},\n                ],\n                temperature=0.2,\n                response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n            )\n\n            content = response.choices[0].message.content\n            parsed = json.loads(content)\n\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": parsed.get(\"original\", narration),\n                \"polished\": parsed.get(\"polished\", narration),\n                \"changes\": parsed.get(\"changes\", []),\n            }\n        except Exception:\n            # On any error, keep original text unchanged\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": narration,\n                \"polished\": narration,\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n\n        all_polished.append(result)\n\n    return all_polished\n\n\ndef save_tts_polished(\n    polished: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save tts_polished.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"tts_polished.json\"\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982330623}}
{"type":"message","id":"a295ebba","parentId":"3da51f3d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:39:08.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. Confirmei antes de limpar — e fizemos bem em não apagar no escuro.\n\n# Resultado da confirmação\n## Sim, esses ficheiros legados **ainda estão em uso**\nPelo menos por:\n- `runtime/tests/test_s1_start.py`\n- o próprio `runtime/s1/s1_start.py`\n\n### Dependências encontradas\n## `s1_start.py`\nImporta directamente:\n- `runtime.s1.scene_director_runner`\n- `runtime.s1.tts_polish_runner`\n\n## Testes\n`runtime/tests/test_s1_start.py` importa:\n- `from runtime.s1.s1_start import start_s1`\n\nE mocka:\n- `runtime.s1.s1_start.run_scene_director`\n- `runtime.s1.s1_start.run_tts_polish`\n\nEntão:\n> **não é seguro apagar agora**\nporque vais quebrar pelo menos essa via de teste/prototipagem.\n\n---\n\n# Leitura correcta\nTemos 3 estados diferentes aqui:\n\n## 1. Canónico\nA arquitectura nova OpenClaw que estamos a consolidar:\n- supervisor\n- operators\n- supervisor_skills\n- deterministic shared components\n\n## 2. Legacy ainda activo\nA via:\n- `s1_start.py`\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\nAinda não é canónica, mas continua:\n- importável\n- testada\n- funcional como prototype path\n\n## 3. Lixo puro\n- `__pycache__/`\n\nIsso sim pode sair sem drama.\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação agora\n## Limpeza segura, sem quebrar nada\n### Podemos fazer já:\n1. remover `__pycache__/`\n2. marcar explicitamente como **legacy / transitional**:\n   - `s1_start.py`\n   - `scene_director_runner.py`\n   - `tts_polish_runner.py`\n3. adicionar uma nota no topo ou doc local explicando:\n   - continuam por compatibilidade/testes\n   - não são o runtime canónico alvo\n\n### Não faria ainda:\n- mover os 3 de pasta\n- apagar os 3\n- renomear os 3\n\nPorque isso pode quebrar imports/tests e criar fricção desnecessária agora.\n\n---\n\n# Sobre os contracts\n## `s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md`\nEste continua o único documento que eu vejo como **mais redundante**.\n\nMas mesmo ele eu também não apagaria já às cegas sem antes:\n- ler se tem algum conteúdo único que não esteja no principal\n- ou fundir esse conteúdo no contract principal primeiro\n\nEntão a abordagem segura também é:\n- primeiro consolidar\n- depois remover\n\n---\n\n# Decisão recomendada\nEu sugiro a seguinte sequência:\n\n## Fase segura imediata\n- apagar `__pycache__/`\n- marcar os 3 ficheiros runtime antigos como legacy/transitional\n- talvez criar um `README.md` em `runtime/s1/` explicando:\n  - canonical path\n  - legacy compatibility path\n  - o que é para manter vs o que está em transição\n\n## Fase seguinte\n- alinhar `test_s1_start.py` com essa realidade\n- e depois decidir:\n  - manter como compatibility path\n  - ou migrar os testes para o fluxo canónico novo\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu faço **agora essa limpeza segura**:\n- remover `__pycache__/`\n- marcar `s1_start.py`, `scene_director_runner.py`, `tts_polish_runner.py` como legacy explícito\n- criar um `runtime/s1/README.md` curto para deixar a pasta limpa conceptualmente\n\nEssa agora é a melhor limpeza possível sem quebrar nada.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14bf1e808193bf9d416ef0255936\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":124228,"output":776,"cacheRead":16896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141900,"cost":{"input":0.31057,"output":0.011640000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0042239999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.326434}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774982331272,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc14bbf5688193b44558910e13370a"}}
