validator -> scene_bible_builder\n\nUse this only as a compatibility/transitional path while the canonical OpenClaw\nruntime path is being finalized.\n\"\"\""},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\s1_start.py\",\"oldText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"S1 Pre-Production — Entry Point / Supervisor.\\n\\nOrchestrates: scene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder.\\nManages retries (max 3 per step) and checkpoints.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\"newText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"S1 Pre-Production — LEGACY transitional entrypoint.\\n\\nLEGACY STATUS:\\n- This module remains active for compatibility and legacy tests.\\n- It is NOT the canonical runtime brain for S1.\\n- Canonical architecture now expects the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`)\\n  to own sector orchestration, with supervisor skills, operators, and deterministic\\n  sector components separated explicitly.\\n\\nThis module still provides a prototype linear path:\\nscene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder\\n\\nUse this only as a compatibility/transitional path while the canonical OpenClaw\\nruntime path is being finalized.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_feXt9zYmBuVvxxir7uIV0wTF|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1571b91481939cb47c699a506249","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_director_runner.py","oldText":"\"\"\"Scene Director Runner — legacy compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\n\nThis module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\nstill imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay`.\n\nIt no longer represents the canonical architecture for S1 scene generation.\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- batch planning outside the operator\n- batch-level scene_director outputs\n- per-batch validation\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\n\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to the newer\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\n\"\"\"","newText":"\"\"\"Scene Director Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\n\nLEGACY STATUS:\n- This module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\n  still imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay` and legacy tests still depend on it.\n- It does NOT represent the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for S1.\n\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- supervisor-owned batch planning\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\n- OpenClaw `scene_director` operator execution\n- per-batch validation\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\n\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to a newer\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\n\"\"\""},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\scene_director_runner.py\",\"oldText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Scene Director Runner — legacy compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\\n\\nThis module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\\nstill imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay`.\\n\\nIt no longer represents the canonical architecture for S1 scene generation.\\nCanonical architecture now expects:\\n- batch planning outside the operator\\n- batch-level scene_director outputs\\n- per-batch validation\\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\\n\\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to the newer\\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\"newText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"Scene Director Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper around the newer S1 batch flow.\\n\\nLEGACY STATUS:\\n- This module remains only because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\\n  still imports `run_scene_director` / `save_screenplay` and legacy tests still depend on it.\\n- It does NOT represent the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for S1.\\n\\nCanonical architecture now expects:\\n- supervisor-owned batch planning\\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\\n- OpenClaw `scene_director` operator execution\\n- per-batch validation\\n- deterministic merge into canonical screenplay.json\\n\\nThis wrapper keeps older call sites functional while adapting them to a newer\\nscene object shape expected by the supervisor skills/contracts.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3QIttUUWtLRHX8l1Svdfze1Y|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1571b91881939d38a972999f483a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish_runner.py","oldText":"\"\"\"TTS Polish Runner — polishes narration text for Text-to-Speech.\n\nProcesses ONE scene at a time for maximum precision.\nApplies language-specific polish rules from channel config.\nDoes NOT change meaning, only pronunciation/readability for TTS.\n\"\"\"","newText":"\"\"\"TTS Polish Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper for TTS-oriented polish.\n\nLEGACY STATUS:\n- This module remains active because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\n  and related legacy tests still depend on it.\n- It is NOT the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for the S1 polish lane.\n\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- supervisor-owned polish batch planning\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\n- OpenClaw `tts_polish` operator execution\n- per-batch validation\n- optional semantic-review escalation for ambiguous cases\n- deterministic merge into canonical `tts_polished.json`\n\nThis module remains only as a transitional compatibility path.\n\"\"\""},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\tts_polish_runner.py\",\"oldText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"TTS Polish Runner — polishes narration text for Text-to-Speech.\\n\\nProcesses ONE scene at a time for maximum precision.\\nApplies language-specific polish rules from channel config.\\nDoes NOT change meaning, only pronunciation/readability for TTS.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\"newText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"TTS Polish Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper for TTS-oriented polish.\\n\\nLEGACY STATUS:\\n- This module remains active because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\\n  and related legacy tests still depend on it.\\n- It is NOT the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for the S1 polish lane.\\n\\nCanonical architecture now expects:\\n- supervisor-owned polish batch planning\\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\\n- OpenClaw `tts_polish` operator execution\\n- per-batch validation\\n- optional semantic-review escalation for ambiguous cases\\n- deterministic merge into canonical `tts_polished.json`\\n\\nThis module remains only as a transitional compatibility path.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZkSRh6v7awQahUgT535s4URI|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1571b92081938b605bab056bca42","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\README.md","content":"# runtime/s1\n\n## Status\n\nThis directory currently contains **two coexisting layers**:\n\n### 1. Canonical S1 architecture (target / active consolidation path)\n- `supervisor_skills/`\n- `screenplay_validator.py`\n- `polish_validator.py`\n- `scene_bible_builder.py`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\n- `checkpoint_writer.py`\n\nThis is the architecture aligned with:\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n- OpenClaw operators\n- explicit contracts in `docs/contracts/s1/`\n\n### 2. Legacy transitional compatibility path\n- `s1_start.py`\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\nThese files are still present because:\n- legacy tests depend on them\n- they provide a prototype linear execution path\n- they have not yet been fully retired from the repo\n\nThey should **not** be treated as the canonical long-term runtime design for S1.\n\n## Cleanup policy\n\n### Safe to keep\n- canonical supervisor skills\n- shared deterministic sector components\n- legacy transitional files only while imports/tests still depend on them\n\n### Safe to remove\n- `__pycache__/`\n\n### Do not remove yet without migration\n- `s1_start.py`\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\n\n## Direction of travel\n\nThe intended end state is:\n- OpenClaw supervisor as sector brain\n- OpenClaw operators as semantic specialists\n- deterministic Python substrate as support layer\n- legacy prototype path either removed or isolated only after dependency migration\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\README.md\",\"content\":\"# runtime/s1\\n\\n## Status\\n\\nThis directory currently contains **two coexisting layers**:\\n\\n### 1. Canonical S1 architecture (target / active consolidation path)\\n- `supervisor_skills/`\\n- `screenplay_validator.py`\\n- `polish_validator.py`\\n- `scene_bible_builder.py`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator.py`\\n- `checkpoint_writer.py`\\n\\nThis is the architecture aligned with:\\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\\n- OpenClaw operators\\n- explicit contracts in `docs/contracts/s1/`\\n\\n### 2. Legacy transitional compatibility path\\n- `s1_start.py`\\n- `scene_director_runner.py`\\n- `tts_polish_runner.py`\\n\\nThese files are still present because:\\n- legacy tests depend on them\\n- they provide a prototype linear execution path\\n- they have not yet been fully retired from the repo\\n\\nThey should **not** be treated as the canonical long-term runtime design for S1.\\n\\n## Cleanup policy\\n\\n### Safe to keep\\n- canonical supervisor skills\\n- shared deterministic sector components\\n- legacy transitional files only while imports/tests still depend on them\\n\\n### Safe to remove\\n- `__pycache__/`\\