{"type":"message","id":"02f09e1b","parentId":"979d1a57","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:56.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou destrinchar agora a última milha: como o `sm_s1_pre_production` vira runtime canónico efectivo e o que precisa existir no código para substituir o protagonismo do `s1_start.py`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc165f67108193b6e63b701b471154\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_boHYdoAjODLaUwBCsnrhfa7c|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b2081939f9bb3d93a142e73","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\s1_start.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\s1_start.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yp0CmrDltI6ainCfAtUG4XBe|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b388193ba4b2c6100f79681","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qxhXxDT33bdPck7HsTksjfN8|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b4881939076eed531674f9a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\operator_batch_scheduler.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\operator_batch_scheduler.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_YNkabrSKcfb4FQNwMu6sqLzf|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b548193b2aadf5e725461ea","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_director_io_adapter.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\scene_director_io_adapter.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rC6ZEx7CaDG3d4GsVL820Fdu|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b608193afd83481cdc2024e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":216,"output":282,"cacheRead":142080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":142578,"cost":{"input":0.00054,"output":0.00423,"cacheRead":0.035519999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.04028999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774982748805,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc165dc3448193b702a904861d68f1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7528b9b","parentId":"02f09e1b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:57.647Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_boHYdoAjODLaUwBCsnrhfa7c|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b2081939f9bb3d93a142e73","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S1 Pre-Production — LEGACY transitional entrypoint.\n\nLEGACY STATUS:\n- This module remains active for compatibility and legacy tests.\n- It is NOT the canonical runtime brain for S1.\n- Canonical architecture now expects the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`)\n  to own sector orchestration, with supervisor skills, operators, and deterministic\n  sector components separated explicitly.\n\nThis module still provides a prototype linear path:\nscene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder\n\nUse this only as a compatibility/transitional path while the canonical OpenClaw\nruntime path is being finalized.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_director_runner import run_scene_director, save_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.screenplay_validator import validate_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.tts_polish_runner import run_tts_polish, save_tts_polished\nfrom runtime.s1.polish_validator import validate_polish\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_builder import build_scene_bible, write_scene_bible\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_schema_validator import validate_scene_bible_schema\nfrom runtime.s1.checkpoint_writer import write_checkpoint\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\nMAX_RETRIES = 3\n\n\ndef start_s1(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: str | Path,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run S1 Pre-Production: script_raw -> scene_bible.json.\n\n    Args:\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n        video_root: Path to initialized run directory.\n        model: OpenAI model for LLM steps.\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result with success, paths, checkpoints, next_step.\n    \"\"\"\n    video_root = Path(video_root)\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    account = job.get(\"account\", \"\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"\")\n\n    # Load channel config\n    config = _load_config(account, language)\n\n    # Read script\n    script_path = video_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt not found\", \"missing_script\")\n    script_raw = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not script_raw.strip():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt is empty\", \"empty_script\")\n\n    checkpoints_written = []\n\n    # ===== STEP 1: Scene Director =====\n    try:\n        screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_failed\")\n\n    screenplay_path = save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step1_screenplay\", \"scene_director\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(screenplay), \"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 2: Screenplay Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        validation = validate_screenplay(script_raw, screenplay)\n\n        if validation[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            # Retry: re-run scene director\n            try:\n                screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n                save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Screenplay validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {validation['details']}\", \"screenplay_validation_failed\")\n\n    # Save validation result\n    val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay_validation.json\"\n    val_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated\", \"screenplay_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 3: TTS Polish =====\n    try:\n        polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_failed\")\n\n    polished_path = save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step3_tts_polished\", \"tts_polish\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\"],\n                     extra={\"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 4: Polish Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        polish_val = validate_polish(screenplay, polished)\n\n        if polish_val[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            try:\n                polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n                save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Polish validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {polish_val['details']}\", \"polish_validation_failed\")\n\n    polish_val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"polish_validation.json\"\n    polish_val_path.write_text(json.dumps(polish_val, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step4_polish_validated\", \"polish_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 5: Scene Bible Builder =====\n    bible = build_scene_bible(polished, job, screenplay)\n\n    # Schema validate\n    schema_val = validate_scene_bible_schema(bible)\n    if not schema_val[\"valid\"]:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene bible schema validation failed: {schema_val['errors']}\", \"scene_bible_schema_failed\")\n\n    bible_path = write_scene_bible(bible, video_root)\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step5_scene_bible\", \"scene_bible_builder\",\n                     [\"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"])})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 6: S1 Complete =====\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_complete\", \"s1_supervisor\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\",\n                      \"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\n                         \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n                         \"screenplay_validated\": True,\n                         \"polish_validated\": True,\n                         \"scene_bible_schema_valid\": True,\n                     })\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_complete.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_complete\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"b1_complete\",\n        \"screenplay_path\": screenplay_path,\n        \"tts_polished_path\": polished_path,\n        \"scene_bible_path\": bible_path,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": schema_val.get(\"warnings\", []),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict:\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\")\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n\n\ndef _error(job_id: str, message: str, code: str) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": code,\n        \"screenplay_path\": \"\",\n        \"tts_polished_path\": \"\",\n        \"scene_bible_path\": \"\",\n        \"checkpoints_written\": [],\n        \"scene_count\": 0,\n        \"next_step\": None,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982757527}}
{"type":"message","id":"e54fb2ff","parentId":"f7528b9b","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:57.758Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yp0CmrDltI6ainCfAtUG4XBe|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b388193ba4b2c6100f79681","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build `scene_director` payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule `scene_director` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n6. Invoke `scene_director` batches under supervisor control\n7. Validate each batch via `scene_director_output_validator`\n8. If needed, classify retry via `retry_planner`\n9. Merge approved scene batches via `screenplay_merger`\n10. Validate canonical screenplay via `screenplay_validator`\n11. If screenplay validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n12. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n13. Build `tts_polish` payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n14. Schedule `tts_polish` batches with controlled parallelism via `operator_batch_scheduler`\n15. Invoke `tts_polish` batches under supervisor control\n16. Validate each polish batch via `tts_polish_output_validator`\n17. Route only ambiguous cases to `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` when needed\n18. Merge approved polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n19. Validate canonical polish via `polish_validator`\n20. If polish validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n21. Build `scene_bible.json` via `scene_bible_builder`\n22. Validate scene bible schema via `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n23. Write/check checkpoints via `checkpoint_writer`\n24. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n25. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n- Do not allow unvalidated batch outputs into canonical merge artifacts\n- The supervisor remains the owner of sequencing and acceptance decisions\n- Semantic review is a narrow escalation lane, not a default second pass for all polish batches\n\n## Important current implementation note\n`operator_batch_scheduler` currently plans waves and summarizes execution.\nIt does **not** itself invoke OpenClaw operators.\nThe supervisor must still own the actual operator invocation/control loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982757648}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ee5394a","parentId":"e54fb2ff","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:57.875Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qxhXxDT33bdPck7HsTksjfN8|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b4881939076eed531674f9a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_batch_schedule(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if concurrency_cap < 1:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"operator\": operator_name,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"invalid_concurrency_cap\", \"message\": \"concurrency_cap must be >= 1\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for batch in batches:\n        normalized_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n                \"input_path\": batch.get(\"input_path\"),\n                \"output_path\": batch.get(\"output_path\"),\n                \"status\": batch.get(\"status\", \"queued\"),\n            }\n        )\n\n    waves: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for i in range(0, len(normalized_batches), concurrency_cap):\n        wave_batches = normalized_batches[i : i + concurrency_cap]\n        waves.append(\n            {\n                \"wave_index\": len(waves) + 1,\n                \"batch_ids\": [b.get(\"batch_id\") for b in wave_batches],\n                \"batch_count\": len(wave_batches),\n                \"batches\": wave_batches,\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(normalized_batches),\n        \"wave_count\": len(waves),\n        \"waves\": waves,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef summarize_batch_execution(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n    execution_results: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    completed_batches: list[str] = []\n    failed_batches: list[str] = []\n    pending_batches: list[str] = []\n    output_files: list[str] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    for result in execution_results:\n        batch_id = result.get(\"batch_id\")\n        status = result.get(\"status\", \"unknown\")\n\n        if status == \"completed\":\n            completed_batches.append(batch_id)\n            if result.get(\"output_path\"):\n                output_files.append(result[\"output_path\"])\n        elif status == \"failed\":\n            failed_batches.append(batch_id)\n        else:\n            pending_batches.append(batch_id)\n\n        for error in result.get(\"errors\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(error, dict):\n                errors.append(error)\n        for warning in result.get(\"warnings\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(warning, dict):\n                warnings.append(warning)\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(failed_batches) == 0,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(execution_results),\n        \"completed_batches\": completed_batches,\n        \"failed_batches\": failed_batches,\n        \"pending_batches\": pending_batches,\n        \"output_files\": output_files,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982757759}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc2233ca","parentId":"4ee5394a","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:57.991Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_YNkabrSKcfb4FQNwMu6sqLzf|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b548193b2aadf5e725461ea","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    account = job.get(\"account\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\")\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\")\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"start_word\": batch.get(\"start_word\"),\n            \"end_word\": batch.get(\"end_word\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n            \"text\": batch.get(\"text\"),\n        },\n        \"scene_words_range\": channel_config.get(\"scene_words_range\"),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Transform this script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes for screenplay generation.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve narrative meaning and order.\",\n                \"Return scene objects only for this batch.\",\n                \"Each scene must include scene_local_id, scene_title, scene_summary, narrative_function, narration_original, start_word, end_word, estimated_scene_word_count.\",\n                \"Use batch-relative word coordinates: the first word in this batch is word 1.\",\n                \"scene_local_id must be sequential within the batch (scene_01, scene_02, ...).\",\n                \"Do not generate global scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not rewrite the story beyond what is needed for clean scene segmentation.\",\n                \"Do not do visual planning, asset planning, prompt writing, or shot design in this step.\",\n                \"Do not polish for TTS in this step.\",\n                \"Do not leave gaps or overlaps between scene text spans.\",\n                \"narration_original must match the original source text assigned to each scene.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_scene_director_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982757875}}
{"type":"message","id":"b720a89d","parentId":"fc2233ca","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:45:58.109Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_rC6ZEx7CaDG3d4GsVL820Fdu|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16647b608193afd83481cdc2024e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    scene_ids = batch.get(\"scene_ids\", [])\n    scene_map = {\n        scene.get(\"scene_id\"): scene\n        for scene in screenplay.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n    }\n    scenes = [scene_map[scene_id] for scene_id in scene_ids if scene_id in scene_map]\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\"),\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"scene_ids\": scene_ids,\n            \"scene_count\": batch.get(\"scene_count\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n        },\n        \"tts_polish_rules\": channel_config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", []),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Polish the narration text for TTS without changing meaning.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve scene order and scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not remove the original narration layer.\",\n                \"Return narration_tts for each scene.\",\n                \"Keep meaning intact while improving speakability.\",\n                \"Return changes metadata for each scene when possible.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_tts_polish_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774982757992}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2c0667b","parentId":"b720a89d","timestamp":"2026-03-31T18:46:39.727Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. Agora dá para dizer com bastante precisão **o que precisa existir para o `sm_s1_pre_production` virar runtime canónico efectivo** e substituir o protagonismo do `s1_start.py`.\n\n# Diagnóstico central\nHoje o `s1_start.py` ainda concentra 4 coisas que o supervisor canónico deveria possuir:\n\n1. **sequencing runtime real**\n2. **operator invocation loop real**\n3. **retry loop real**\n4. **checkpoint/result completion loop real**\n\nA documentação do supervisor já define isso bem.  \nO que falta é a **camada executiva concreta**.\n\n---\n\n# O que o runtime canónico do supervisor precisa ser\n\n## Regra-mãe\nO `sm_s1_pre_production` não deve virar apenas “um prompt bonito”.\nEle precisa de operar como:\n\n- **LLM supervisor soberano**\n- apoiado por:\n  - supervisor skills determinísticas\n  - operators OpenClaw\n  - shared deterministic components\n  - persisted artifacts\n\nOu seja, o missing piece não é mais arquitectura.\nÉ **wiring operacional**.\n\n---\n\n# O loop canónico real que precisa existir\n\nVou te devolver isso em forma de execução concreta.\n\n---\n\n## Fase 0 — Entrada do supervisor\n### Input mínimo\nO supervisor deve receber:\n- `run_root`\n- ou contexto suficiente para resolver a run\n\n### Primeiros passos obrigatórios\n1. `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. `s1_paths_resolver`\n\nSe qualquer um falha:\n- fail fast\n- escreve erro claro\n- não improvisa\n\n---\n\n## Fase 1 — Loop real do `scene_director`\n### Passo 1\n`script_batch_planner`\n- gera `sd_###`\n\n### Passo 2\nPara cada batch:\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- escreve input payload\n- define output path\n\n### Passo 3\n`operator_batch_scheduler`\n- gera waves conforme cap\n\n### Passo 4 — aqui está a peça que falta hoje\nO supervisor precisa de um **operator invocation loop real**.\n\nIsto significa algo como:\n- pegar wave 1\n- para cada batch da wave\n  - chamar o operator `op_s1_scene_director`\n  - passando o payload certo\n- esperar outputs\n- recolher status por batch\n\n### Passo 5\nPara cada output batch:\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Passo 6\nSe houver falhas:\n- `retry_planner`\n- decidir:\n  - subset retry\n  - batch regen\n  - abort\n\n### Passo 7\nSó approved batches:\n- `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Passo 8\nWhole-artifact:\n- `screenplay_validator`\n\n### Passo 9\nSe falhou:\n- retry planner de novo\n- preferir subset retry quando possível\n\n### Passo 10\nEscrever:\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- checkpoint `b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- checkpoint `b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n\n---\n\n## Fase 2 — Loop real do `tts_polish`\nMesma lógica, mas com nuance maior.\n\n### Passo 1\n`tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Passo 2\nPara cada batch:\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Passo 3\n`operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Passo 4 — peça que falta hoje\nSupervisor faz **operator invocation loop real** para `op_s1_tts_polish`\n\n### Passo 5\nCada batch passa por:\n- `tts_polish_output_validator`\n\n### Passo 6\nSó batches ambíguos vão para:\n- `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### Passo 7\nSupervisor interpreta reviewer output:\n- approve\n- subset repair\n- regenerate\n- abort\n\n### Passo 8\nSó approved batches:\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Passo 9\nWhole-artifact:\n- `polish_validator`\n\n### Passo 10\nEscrever:\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- checkpoints:\n  - `b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n  - `b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n\n---\n\n## Fase 3 — Fecho do sector\n1. `scene_bible_builder`\n2. `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n3. `checkpoint_writer`\n4. `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nDepois:\n- `b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n# O que falta no código, concretamente\n\nAgora a parte mais útil: **quais peças concretas faltam**.\n\n## 1. Falta uma camada de “supervisor runtime executor”\nHoje temos:\n- skills\n- contracts\n- workspace\n- validators/mergers/builders\n\nMas não temos uma peça clara tipo:\n\n### exemplo de nome possível\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_runtime.py`\nou\n- `runtime/s1/sm_s1_runtime_executor.py`\n\nEssa peça seria a ponte entre:\n- supervisor canónico\n- skills determinísticas\n- operator invocation real\n- checkpoint/result writing\n\n### Papel dela\nNão ser o cérebro.\nSer o **executor substrate do cérebro**.\n\nOu seja:\n- o cérebro decide\n- esta peça operacionaliza\n\n---\n\n## 2. Falta uma abstração canónica de invocation de operator\nHoje o scheduler:\n- planeia\n- resume\n\nMas não invoca.\n\nEntão falta algo do tipo:\n\n### conceito\n`invoke_operator_batch(...)`\n\nPara:\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n### Esse invoker precisaria saber:\n- qual agent OpenClaw chamar\n- com que payload\n- onde esperar output\n- como devolver status estruturado ao supervisor\n\nEsta é provavelmente **a peça mais importante que ainda não existe claramente**.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Falta aterragem runtime explícita do `tts_polish_output_validator`\nHoje está muito bem no contrato.\nMas para a execução canónica ficar completa, essa peça precisa existir no mesmo nível prático do:\n- `scene_director_output_validator.py`\n\nOu seja:\n- runtime component real\n- integrado no loop do supervisor\n\n---\n\n## 4. Falta um supervisor-execution contract de facto\nJá temos contracts por componente.\nMas agora seria útil existir algo como:\n\n### documento novo possível\n- `s1_supervisor_runtime_execution_contract.md`\n\nQue diga explicitamente:\n- como a invocação de operators acontece\n- como batching waves são executadas\n- como outputs são recolhidos\n- quando um batch é “completed” vs “approved”\n- como o supervisor chama reviewer lane\n- como escreve checkpoints por stage\n\nIsto ajudaria a não deixar a última milha voltar a ficar implícita.\n\n---\n\n# O que o `s1_start.py` ainda faz que o supervisor runtime canónico precisa absorver\n## Hoje o `s1_start.py` ainda é dono de:\n- ler config\n- ler script\n- chamar scene_director\n- chamar validators\n- chamar polish\n- chamar scene_bible builder\n- escrever checkpoints\n- construir retorno final\n\n## No end-state\nEssas responsabilidades deveriam ficar repartidas assim:\n\n### Supervisor\n- decide ordem\n- decide retry\n- decide approve/reject/escalate\n- decide final completion\n\n### Runtime executor / substrate\n- chama skills\n- chama operators\n- recolhe outputs\n- persiste artefactos\n- escreve checkpoints quando o supervisor decide\n\n### Legacy `s1_start.py`\n- desaparece\nou\n- vira wrapper finíssimo que apenas delega para o executor canónico\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação concreta de implementação\nSe eu estivesse a fechar esta última milha contigo, eu faria nesta ordem:\n\n## Passo 1\nCriar a peça nova:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_runtime.py`\n\n### Objetivo\nconter funções como:\n- `run_s1_supervisor_runtime(...)`\n- `_run_scene_director_lane(...)`\n- `_run_tts_polish_lane(...)`\n- `_run_scene_bible_lane(...)`\n\nNão como cérebro LLM, mas como **substrate de execução canónica**.\n\n---\n\n## Passo 2\nCriar/definir uma função de invocação de operator\nAlgo tipo:\n- `_invoke_scene_director_batch(...)`\n- `_invoke_tts_polish_batch(...)`\n- `_invoke_tts_polish_reviewer(...)`\n\nMesmo que inicialmente usem uma bridge temporária, essa interface já deve nascer canónica.\n\n---\n\n## Passo 3\nImplementar o `tts_polish_output_validator` runtime real\nPara fechar simetricamente o lane do polish.\n\n---\n\n## Passo 4\nRebaixar `s1_start.py`\nDepois disso:\n- `s1_start.py` deixa de orquestrar tudo\n- passa só a chamar o runtime executor canónico\n- ou vira deprecated wrapper\n\n---\n\n# Decisão estratégica\nSe o teu objectivo é realmente:\n> “fazer o S1 funcionar da maneira mais perfeita possível com OpenClaw”\n\nentão o próximo passo certo já não é mais revisão.\nÉ:\n\n## **começar a construir a camada de execução canónica do supervisor**\n\nPorque agora:\n- a constituição já existe\n- os components já existem\n- os contracts já existem\n- o runtime velho já foi delimitado\n\nFalta só a peça que transforma tudo isso em **runtime soberano real**.\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação firme\nEu seguiria imediatamente assim:\n\n1. **criar `runtime/s1/supervisor_runtime.py`**\n2. desenhar nele o loop real do supervisor por lanes\n3. especificar a interface de invocation dos operators\n4. aterrar `tts_polish_output_validator`\n5. depois rebaixar `s1_start.py`\n\nSe quiser, eu posso começar já pela **primeira peça concreta**:\n> desenhar e escrever o esqueleto do `supervisor_runtime.py`\n\nEsse agora é o melhor próximo movimento.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc166ae700819395dfab93042fdd31\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":123179,"output":2089,"cacheRead":19968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145236,"cost":{"input":0.30794750000000004,"output":0.031335,"cacheRead":0.004992,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.34427450000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774982758715,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc16678388819387cba65f873c40c2"}}
