 cron will run at that time every single day. So those are two different things and the heartbeat good for one thing know crons are good for running a task and you know setting up automated tasks like you know go find me some leads go check the inbox go respond to all the emails like whatever the thing is you need it to do Crons are the way that you get your agent to run autonomously and work 24-7. So without crons, it's going to fall asleep and the heartbeats aren't really going to remember the tasks that it was doing or the heartbeats would just have it work on the task of which it's working on. And if it needs to switch task or switch project, then you can switch it based upon that and it can switch to the correct project and the correct thing that you're working on. So you can define the session and define what it is that it needs to be doing. And again, your agent can set these things up for you. So the delivery of outputs. Here's an example. channel WhatsApp to number. So WhatsApp is like that, telegrams like this, Slack is like this, Discord is like this, signals like that, iMessage is like that. So that's how you'll set up the updates if you want to get pinged on the update. So the gateway tool, this is the JSON. So again, you can load this into your agent and then your agent will automatically set up your cron ad in this situation or the recurring isolated where it spins up the sub agent, it'll run on that side. So it's totally up to you on how you want to set up your projects and test it out, see how it works and, you know, see what works best for you. So here's an example of some recipes that you can use. Morning brief, weather, calendar, emails, update, whatever it is that you want. Weekly review, give me a, you know, breakdown of everything. Use Opus to understand what it is that we're doing so you can define the model in the cron and then it'll use that model for that cron so opus for the most expensive sonnet for the second most expensive haiku for th