ry, you can read these. You see what I'm talking about. So some common issues that are having issues. You can read through these if you're hitting any of those blocks. It could be a wrong delivery target. That could be one of the issues. Job's getting delayed. Main session job is silent. Here's some best practices and so forth for setting up your crons. If you have any issues with this, definitely create a ticket in the, or just set up a message in troubleshooting and we can definitely work through those with you. Quick reference guide. And I think that's it. So just a little quick reference on, you know, how to double check to make sure your agent sets things up correctly. Sometimes it does. Sometimes it doesn't. So we always want to double check what our agent is up to. So, yeah, that wraps it up. We will see you on the next video. Thank you.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:14:This guide walks you through building a 12-agent autonomous video pipeline inside OpenClaw. Each step gives you the exact setup to perform in OpenClaw and the exact prompt to paste into each agent. Follow the steps in order. By the end, OpenClaw will run every morning, generate videos using your cloned voice and face, and post them while you sleep.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:121:OPENCLAW SETUP - CLONESETUPAGENT\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:124:In OpenClaw, create a new Agent with these settings:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:182:1. In OpenClaw, open Agents  CloneSetupAgent\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\De