{"type":"message","id":"8fe2ab35","parentId":"092ec4af","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:04:59.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Encontrei um sinal útil: há referência histórica a `openclaw agents run ...`, então vou preparar a ponte do hook como CLI-based transitional adapter explícito, sem fingir integração nativa onde ainda não vi substrate.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1ad32a2c8193a9a986feeb5ecdcc\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_IF0GXkYl1uSPbA5QmhRP2IC9|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1ad42ef08193a3a6b76bce79ff7d","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_runtime.py","oldText":"\"\"\"S1 Supervisor Runtime — canonical execution substrate for SM-S1.\n\nThis module is the execution substrate for the canonical S1 architecture.\nIt is intended to support the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`) as the\nruntime brain of the sector.\n\nIt is NOT the legacy linear prototype path from `runtime.s1.s1_start`.\n\nDesign goal:\n- supervisor owns sequencing / acceptance / retry / completion decisions\n- deterministic skills and shared components perform mechanical work\n- OpenClaw operators perform semantic work\n- persisted artifacts remain operational truth\n\nCurrent status:\n- scaffold / skeleton only\n- lane decomposition established\n- operator invocation hooks intentionally left explicit and narrow\n\"\"\"","newText":"\"\"\"S1 Supervisor Runtime — canonical execution substrate for SM-S1.\n\nThis module is the execution substrate for the canonical S1 architecture.\nIt is intended to support the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`) as the\nruntime brain of the sector.\n\nIt is NOT the legacy linear prototype path from `runtime.s1.s1_start`.\n\nDesign goal:\n- supervisor owns sequencing / acceptance / retry / completion decisions\n- deterministic skills and shared components perform mechanical work\n- OpenClaw operators perform semantic work\n- persisted artifacts remain operational truth\n\nInvocation strategy note:\n- canonical operator invocation should ultimately be performed through a real\n  OpenClaw runtime bridge\n- until a richer in-process bridge exists, this module may use an explicit\n  transitional adapter boundary for CLI/operator invocation\n- the adapter boundary is kept narrow on purpose so the architecture stays clear\n\nCurrent status:\n- scaffold / skeleton only\n- lane decomposition established\n- operator invocation hooks intentionally left explicit and narrow\n\"\"\""},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_runtime.py\",\"oldText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"S1 Supervisor Runtime — canonical execution substrate for SM-S1.\\n\\nThis module is the execution substrate for the canonical S1 architecture.\\nIt is intended to support the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`) as the\\nruntime brain of the sector.\\n\\nIt is NOT the legacy linear prototype path from `runtime.s1.s1_start`.\\n\\nDesign goal:\\n- supervisor owns sequencing / acceptance / retry / completion decisions\\n- deterministic skills and shared components perform mechanical work\\n- OpenClaw operators perform semantic work\\n- persisted artifacts remain operational truth\\n\\nCurrent status:\\n- scaffold / skeleton only\\n- lane decomposition established\\n- operator invocation hooks intentionally left explicit and narrow\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\",\"newText\":\"\\\"\\\"\\\"S1 Supervisor Runtime — canonical execution substrate for SM-S1.\\n\\nThis module is the execution substrate for the canonical S1 architecture.\\nIt is intended to support the OpenClaw supervisor (`sm_s1_pre_production`) as the\\nruntime brain of the sector.\\n\\nIt is NOT the legacy linear prototype path from `runtime.s1.s1_start`.\\n\\nDesign goal:\\n- supervisor owns sequencing / acceptance / retry / completion de