{"type":"message","id":"c1f186d3","parentId":"09a01fdd","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:14:26.100Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_SSsNZqAwI2e5e4j2Uk9Dfzo3|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1d111cfc81938919296494672e08","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"age|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-pine","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.28 (f9b1079)\n   I don't just autocomplete—I auto-commit (emotionally), then ask you to review (logically).\n\nUsage: openclaw agent [options]\n\nRun an agent turn via the Gateway (use --local for embedded)\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>               Agent id (overrides routing bindings)\n  --channel <channel>        Delivery channel:\n                             last|telegram|whatsapp|discord|irc|googlechat|slack|signal|imessage|line\n                             (omit to use the main session channel)\n  --deliver                  Send the agent's reply back to the selected channel\n                             (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --json                     Output result as JSON (default: false)\n  --local                    Run the embedded agent locally (requires model\n                             provider API keys in your shell) (default: false)\n  -m, --message <text>       Message body for the agent\n  --reply-account <id>       Delivery account id override\n  --reply-channel <channel>  Delivery channel override (separate from routing)\n  --reply-to <target>        Delivery target override (separate from session\n                             routing)\n  --session-id <id>          Use an explicit session id\n  -t, --to <number>          Recipient number in E.164 used to derive the\n                             session key\n  --thinking <level>         Thinking level: off | minimal | low | medium | high\n                             | xhigh\n  --timeout <seconds>        Override agent command timeout (seconds, default\n                             600 or config value)\n  --verbose <on|off>         Persist agent verbose level for the session\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\"\n    Start a new session.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\n    Use a specific agent.\n  openclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n    Target a session with explicit thinking level.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Trace logs\" --verbose on --json\n    Enable verbose logging and JSON output.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"Summon reply\" --deliver\n    Deliver reply.\n  openclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n    Send reply to a different channel/target.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/agent\n","name":"openclaw agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774984465964}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b6710ca","parentId":"c1f186d3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:14:38.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — **essas pesquisas não ficam automaticamente “na minha memória” de forma fiável**, a não ser que eu as escreva em ficheiros.\n\nOu seja:\n- os resultados dos subagentes existem nesta sessão/conversa\n- mas **se quisermos preservar mesmo** para depois, o certo é persistir no workspace\n\nE honestamente, faz sentido fazer isso agora, porque esta descoberta sobre:\n- `openclaw agent`\n- `agents` vs `agent`\n- superfície real de execução\n- implicação para o S1 runtime\n\né exactamente o tipo de contexto que não vale perder.\n\n## O que eu sugiro\nEu posso gravar isso já num ficheiro de research/decision no workspace, por exemplo:\n- `memory/2026-03-31.md`\nou\n- um ficheiro mais operacional tipo:\n  - `notes/s1-openclaw-runtime-research.md`\n  - ou dentro do próprio repo/docs se tu quiseres transformar isso em documentação do sistema\n\n### Minha recomendação\nComo isto é contexto de trabalho do S1, eu prefiro:\n- **guardar no workspace**\n- e depois, se fizer sentido, transformar parte disso em doc canónica do repo\n\n---\n\n## E quanto ao hook\nAcabei de confirmar também o help real de `openclaw agent`:\n- tem `--agent`\n- `--message`\n- `--json`\n- `--local`\n- `--session-id`\n- `--thinking`\n- `--timeout`\n- `--deliver`\n\nEntão agora o próximo passo técnico ficou ainda mais concreto:\n> ajustar o hook do `scene_director` para usar `openclaw agent`, não `agents`\n\nSe quiser, eu faço os dois agora:\n1. **persisto a pesquisa no workspace**\n2. **ajusto o hook do `scene_director` para a superfície `openclaw agent`**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc1d1594f88193825f502a7e00cd3d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":643,"output":395,"cacheRead":155520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalT