ser-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\zh-CN\\tools\\plugin.md:1297:`openUrl`?`oauth.createVpsAwareHandlers`?`secretInputMode` ?\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\zh-CN\\tools\\skills.md:265:- Token ?????????????? OpenAI ????? ~4 ??/token,??**?? Skills 97 ?? ~ 24 token** ???????????\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\zh-CN\\tools\\slash-commands.md:148:/model openai/gpt-5.2\r\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-breeze","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"bugging.md:154:PI_RAW_STREAM_PATH=~/.pi-mono/logs/raw-openai-completions.jsonl\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\debugging.md:159:`~/.pi-mono/logs/raw-openai-completions.jsonl`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\debugging.md:162:> `openai-completions` provider.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:11:Quick answers plus deeper troubleshooting for real-world setups (local dev, VPS, multi-agent, OAuth/API keys, model failover). For runtime diagnostics, see [Troubleshooting](/gateway/troubleshooting). For the full config reference, see [Configuration](/gateway/configuration).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:87:- **OpenAI Codex**: [https://openai.com/codex/](https://openai.com/codex/)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:522:- **Model/auth setup** (provider OAuth/setup-token flows and API keys supported, plus local model options such as LM Studio)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:533:<Accordion title=\"Do I need a Claude or OpenAI subscription to run this?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:534:No. You can run OpenClaw with **API keys** (Anthropic/OpenAI/others) or with\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:536:Pro/Max or OpenAI Codex) are optional ways to authenticate those providers.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:540:OpenAI Codex OAuth is explicitly supported for external tools like OpenClaw.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:542:Docs: [Anthropic](/providers/anthropic), [OpenAI](/providers/openai),\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:559:`claude setup-token` generates a **token string** via the Claude Code CLI (it is not available in the web console). You can run it on **any machine**. Choose **Anthropic token (paste setup-token)** in onboarding or paste it with `openclaw models auth paste-token --provider anthropic`. The token is stored as an auth profile for the **anthropic** provider and used like an API key (no auto-refresh). More detail: [OAuth](/concepts/oauth).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:579:Setup-token is still supported. Claude CLI migration is simpler when the gateway host already runs Claude Code. See [Anthropic](/providers/anthropic) and [OAuth](/concepts/oauth).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:601:See [Models](/cli/models), [OAuth](/concepts/oauth), and\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:607:Yes - via pi-ai's **Amazon Bedrock (Converse)** provider with **manual config**. You must supply AWS credentials/region on the gateway host and add a Bedrock provider entry in your models config. See [Amazon Bedrock](/providers/bedrock) and [Model providers](/providers/models). If you prefer a managed key flow, an OpenAI-compatible proxy in front of Bedrock is still a valid option.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:611:OpenClaw supports **OpenAI Code (Codex)** via OAuth (ChatGPT sign-in). Onboarding can run the OAuth flow and will set the default model to `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` when appropriate. See [Model providers](/concepts/model-providers) and [Onboarding (CLI)](/start/wizard).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:614:<Accordion title=\"Do you support OpenAI subscription auth (Codex OAuth)?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:615:Yes. OpenClaw fully supports **OpenAI Code (Codex) subscription OAuth**.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:616:OpenAI explicitly allows subscription OAuth usage in external tools/workflows\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:617:like OpenClaw. Onboarding can run the OAuth flow for you.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:619:See [OAuth](/concepts/oauth), [Model providers](/concepts/model-providers), and [Onboarding (CLI)](/start/wizard).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:623:<Accordion title=\"How do I set up Gemini CLI OAuth?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:631:This stores OAuth tokens in auth profiles on the gateway host. Details: [Model providers](/concepts/model-providers).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:640:Pick region-pinned endpoints. OpenRouter exposes US-hosted options for MiniMax, Kimi, and GLM; choose the US-hosted variant to keep data in-region. You can still list Anthropic/OpenAI alongside these by using `models.mode: \"merge\"` so fallbacks stay available while respecting the regioned provider you select.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:854:- **Model-agnostic:** use Anthropic, OpenAI, MiniMax, OpenRouter, etc., with per-agent routing\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1178:<Accordion title=\"Does semantic memory search require an OpenAI API key?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1179:Only if you use **OpenAI embeddings**. Codex OAuth covers chat/completions and\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1180:does **not** grant embeddings access, so **signing in with Codex (OAuth or the\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1181:Codex CLI login)** does not help for semantic memory search. OpenAI embeddings\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1182:still need a real API key (`OPENAI_API_KEY` or `models.providers.openai.apiKey`).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1186:It prefers OpenAI if an OpenAI key resolves, otherwise Gemini if a Gemini key\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1196:`memorySearch.remote.apiKey`). We support **OpenAI, Gemini, Voyage, Mistral, Ollama, or local** embedding\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1210:- **Remote by necessity:** messages you send to model providers (Anthropic/OpenAI/etc.) go to\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1226:| `$OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/credentials/oauth.json`                    | Legacy OAuth import (copied into auth profiles on first use)       |\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:1227:| `$OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json` | Auth profiles (OAuth, API keys, and optional `keyRef`/`tokenRef`)  |\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2111:Tip: `/model status` shows which agent is active, which `auth-profiles.json` file is being used, and which auth profile will be tried next.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2130:- **Quick switch (per session):** `/model gpt-5.2` for daily tasks, `/model openai-codex/gpt-5.4` for coding with Codex OAuth.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2131:- **Default + switch:** set `agents.defaults.model.primary` to `openai/gpt-5.2`, then switch to `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` when coding (or the other way around).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2174:<Accordion title=\"Can I use MiniMax as my default and OpenAI for complex tasks?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2182:env: { MINIMAX_API_KEY: \"sk-...\", OPENAI_API_KEY: \"sk-...\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2188:\"openai/gpt-5.2\": { alias: \"gpt\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2204:- Agent B default: OpenAI\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2207:Docs: [Models](/concepts/models), [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent), [MiniMax](/providers/minimax), [OpenAI](/providers/openai).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2216:- `gpt`  `openai/gpt-5.4`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2217:- `gpt-mini`  `openai/gpt-5-mini`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2285:~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2291:- Or copy `auth-profiles.json` from the main agent's `agentDir` into the new agent's `agentDir`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2317:- Current: `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2322:- Multi-agent setups mean there can be multiple `auth-profiles.json` files.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2364:Related: [/concepts/oauth](/concepts/oauth) (OAuth flows, token storage, multi-account patterns)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2368:An auth profile is a named credential record (OAuth or API key) tied to a provider. Profiles live in:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2371:~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/agent/auth-profiles.json\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2380:- `anthropic:<email>` for OAuth identities\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2390:You can also set a **per-agent** order override (stored in that agent's `auth-profiles.json`) via the CLI:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2414:<Accordion title=\"OAuth vs API key - what is the difference?\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2417:- **OAuth** often leverages subscription access (where applicable).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2420:The wizard explicitly supports Anthropic setup-token and OpenAI Codex OAuth and can store API keys for you.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\faq.md:2993:In OpenClaw, credentials and model selection are separate. Setting `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (or storing an Anthropic API key in auth profiles) enables authentication, but the actual default model is whatever you configure in `agents.defaults.model.primary` (for example, `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` or `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6`). If you see `No credentials found for profile \"anthropic:default\"`, it means the Gateway couldn't find Anthropic credentials in the expected `auth-profiles.json` for the agent that's running.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:158:- API key rotation (provider-specific): set `*_API_KEYS` with comma/semicolon format or `*_API_KEY_1`, `*_API_KEY_2` (for example `OPENAI_API_KEYS`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS`, `GEMINI_API_KEYS`) or per-live override via `OPENCLAW_LIVE_*_KEY`; tests retry on rate limit responses.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:210:- or `OPENCLAW_LIVE_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-5.2,anthropic/claude-opus-4-6,...\"` (comma allowlist)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:218:- Contains small, isolated regressions (example: OpenAI Responses/Codex Responses reasoning replay + tool-call flows)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:230:- OpenAI regression paths (tool-call-only  follow-up) keep working\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:243:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_PROVIDERS=\"google,google-antigravity,google-gemini-cli,openai,anthropic,zai,minimax\"` (comma allowlist)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:365:- It sources `~/.profile`, copies the matching CLI auth home (`~/.claude` or `~/.codex`) into the container, installs `acpx` into a writable npm prefix, then installs the requested live CLI (`@anthropic-ai/claude-code` or `@openai/codex`) if missing.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:373:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-5.2\" pnpm test:live src/agents/models.profiles.live.test.ts`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:376:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-5.2\" pnpm test:live src/gateway/gateway-models.profiles.live.test.ts`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:379:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-5.2,anthropic/claude-opus-4-6,google/gemini-3-flash-preview,zai/glm-4.7,minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\" pnpm test:live src/gateway/gateway-models.profiles.live.test.ts`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:383:- Antigravity (OAuth): `OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_MODELS=\"google-antigravity/claude-opus-4-6-thinking,google-antigravity/gemini-3-pro-high\" pnpm test:live src/gateway/gateway-models.profiles.live.test.ts`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:388:- `google-antigravity/...` uses the Antigravity OAuth bridge (Cloud Code Assist-style agent endpoint).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:402:- OpenAI (non-Codex): `openai/gpt-5.2` (optional: `openai/gpt-5.1`)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:403:- OpenAI Codex: `openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:411:`OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-5.2,openai-codex/gpt-5.4,anthropic/claude-opus-4-6,google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview,google/gemini-3-flash-preview,google-antigravity/claude-opus-4-6-thinking,google-antigravity/gemini-3-flash,zai/glm-4.7,minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\" pnpm test:live src/gateway/gateway-models.profiles.live.test.ts`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:417:- OpenAI: `openai/gpt-5.2` (or `openai/gpt-5-mini`)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:432:Include at least one image-capable model in `OPENCLAW_LIVE_GATEWAY_MODELS` (Claude/Gemini/OpenAI vision-capable variants, etc.) to exercise the image probe.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:443:- Built-in: `openai`, `openai-codex`, `anthropic`, `google`, `google-vertex`, `google-antigravity`, `google-gemini-cli`, `zai`, `openrouter`, `opencode`, `opencode-go`, `xai`, `groq`, `cerebras`, `mistral`, `github-copilot`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:444:- Via `models.providers` (custom endpoints): `minimax` (cloud/API), plus any OpenAI/Anthropic-compatible proxy (LM Studio, vLLM, LiteLLM, etc.)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:479:- Uses live/env API keys ahead of stored auth profiles by default, so stale test keys in `auth-profiles.json` do not mask real shell credentials\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:485:- `openai:default-generate`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:487:- `openai`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:490:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_IMAGE_GENERATION_PROVIDERS=\"openai,google\"`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:491:- `OPENCLAW_LIVE_IMAGE_GENERATION_MODELS=\"openai/gpt-image-1,google/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview\"`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:503:The live-model Docker runners also bind-mount only the needed CLI auth homes (or all supported ones when the run is not narrowed), then copy them into the container home before the run so external-CLI OAuth can refresh tokens without mutating the host auth store:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:524:OpenClaw gateway container with the OpenAI-compatible HTTP endpoints enabled,\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\help\\testing.md:574:- Gateway tool calling (mock OpenAI, real gateway + agent loop): `src/gateway/gateway.test.ts` (case: \"runs a mock OpenAI tool call end-to-end via gateway agent loop\")\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\docker-vm-runtime.md:124:| Model auth profiles | `/home/node/.openclaw/`           | Host volume mount      | OAuth tokens, API keys           |\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\docker.md:287:<Accordion title=\"OpenAI Codex OAuth (headless Docker)\">\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\docker.md:288:If you pick OpenAI Codex OAuth in the wizard, it opens a browser URL. In\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\fly.md:104:fly secrets set OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\fly.md:159:\"fallbacks\": [\"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\", \"openai/gpt-4o\"]\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\fly.md:173:\"openai:default\": { \"mode\": \"token\", \"provider\": \"openai\" }\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\gcp.md:64:- Gmail OAuth\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\install\\hetzner.md:71:- Gmail OAuth\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\doc