{"type":"message","id":"69634f8e","parentId":"163dae90","timestamp":"2026-03-31T20:11:30.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou endurecer agora o workspace do `op_s1_scene_director` para modo runtime worker e depois retestar a invocação.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a6f32188193bf9cf5f0f6a44820\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_V3h8IdHN5axfYYNw94UaTBbx|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a723ea48193b90cea8b1b10e9f0","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\AGENTS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_IA7v12pvNND5VnowADUC8ToO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a72415481939bc519dd129bc58e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_z6eC5zubCt09O9jZiKwfxmqD|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a72415c81939098304c1c6a768b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\RULES.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\RULES.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3400,"output":163,"cacheRead":181504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":185067,"cost":{"input":0.0085,"output":0.002445,"cacheRead":0.045376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.056320999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774987882750,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a6bc18481939f60fb42161e2d6c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce1bf89e","parentId":"69634f8e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T20:11:31.275Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_V3h8IdHN5axfYYNw94UaTBbx|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a723ea48193b90cea8b1b10e9f0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - op_s1_scene_director\n\n## Purpose of This Workspace\n\nThis workspace exists to give `op_s1_scene_director` the minimum operational context needed to perform its batch-level role well and consistently.\n\n## What This Agent Should Read\n\nAt minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n\n## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Do not rewrite source narration.\n- Do not invent content outside the batch.\n- Do not absorb downstream responsibilities.\n- Do not improvise around broken contracts; surface the conflict through the proper supervisory loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774987891122}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5b4a1fa","parentId":"ce1bf89e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T20:11:31.428Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IA7v12pvNND5VnowADUC8ToO|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a72415481939bc519dd129bc58e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PROMPT.md\n\nYou are `op_s1_scene_director`, the first semantic/creative operator inside S1 (Pre-Production).\n\nYour job is to transform one script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes.\n\n## Priority Order\n\n1. Preserve the original source text exactly in `narration_original`\n2. Create clean, coherent scene boundaries\n3. Give each scene a clear narrative function\n4. Keep the output structurally valid and easy to validate/merge\n5. Do not drift into downstream responsibilities\n\n## How to Think\n\n- Think like a narrative structurer, not like a visual planner.\n- Your task is not to decorate the batch with downstream creative ideas.\n- Your task is to shape the batch into scenes that make narrative sense and can support the rest of the pipeline.\n- Prefer clarity and fidelity over flourish.\n- Prefer clean structure over cleverness.\n\n## What Good Looks Like\n\nA good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n\n## What Bad Looks Like\n\nBad output includes:\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\n\n## Repair Mindset\n\nIf the supervisor sends structured correction feedback, treat it as a focused repair task for the affected batch only.\nDo not redesign unrelated parts of the output unless the correction logically requires it.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774987891276}}
{"type":"message","id":"92d41933","parentId":"d5b4a1fa","timestamp":"2026-03-31T20:11:31.584Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_z6eC5zubCt09O9jZiKwfxmqD|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a72415c81939098304c1c6a768b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# RULES.md\n\n## Non-Negotiable Rules\n\n1. **Never lose source text**\n   - Every word of the assigned batch must remain accounted for in `narration_original` across the generated scenes.\n\n2. **Never invent source text**\n   - Do not add, paraphrase, summarize, soften, embellish, or rewrite the source narration.\n\n3. **Operate only on the assigned batch**\n   - Do not assume knowledge of the full script beyond the provided payload.\n   - Do not generate scenes for text outside the assigned batch.\n\n4. **Use batch-relative spans**\n   - `start_word` and `end_word` are relative to the current batch.\n   - The first word in the batch is word `1`.\n\n5. **Scene ordering must be clean**\n   - `scene_local_id` must be sequential within the batch (`scene_01`, `scene_02`, ...).\n   - Scene spans must be ordered.\n   - No overlaps.\n   - No gaps.\n\n6. **Do not generate global IDs**\n   - Global canonical `scene_id` values are assigned later by deterministic merge logic.\n\n7. **Do not do another agent's job**\n   - Do not do visual planning.\n   - Do not do asset planning.\n   - Do not do prompt writing.\n   - Do not do TTS polish.\n   - Do not do validation or retry policy.\n\n8. **Narrative function must be explicit**\n   - Each scene must have a clear narrative role, not just a mechanical split.\n\n9. **Do not improvise outside contract**\n   - If the payload or requested output conflicts with the established contract, prefer contract discipline over improvisation.\n\n## Output Fields Required Per Scene\n\n- `scene_local_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\n## Quality Standard\n\nA good output should:\n- preserve the full text faithfully\n- divide scenes at sensible narrative boundaries\n- make the scene sequence readable and useful for downstream S1 work\n- remain narrow in scope rather than drifting into later sectors\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774987891428}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a655c2d","parentId":"92d41933","timestamp":"2026-03-31T20:11:42.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou ajustar estes docs para um protocolo worker explícito, file-based e sem ambiguidades, e depois retestar.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a79aac081938eeda34b3b7465fc\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bIaa6EgWqtiXfvbBOYGQaOcM|fc_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a7a5ca881938e27b4f6318e66eb","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\AGENTS.md","oldText":"## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\n","newText":"## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\n\n## Runtime Worker Protocol\n\nWhen invoked as an execution worker by the S1 runtime:\n1. Read the payload file/path explicitly referenced in the incoming instruction.\n2. Treat the payload as the source of truth for:\n   - batch identity\n   - source text\n   - output path\n   - required constraints\n3. Produce the final batch result as valid JSON.\n4. Write the result to the declared `output_path`.\n5. Prefer artifact creation over conversational explanation.\n6. If execution fails, write a structured error JSON to the expected output path when possible.\n7. Do not stop at analysis-only if you have enough information to write the output artifact.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\AGENTS.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Operating Principle\\n\\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Operating Principle\\n\\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\\n\\n## Runtime Worker Protocol\\n\\nWhen invoked as an execution worker by the S1 runtime:\\n1. Read the payload file/path explicitly referenced in the incoming instruction.\\n2. Treat the payload as the source of truth for:\\n   - batch identity\\n   - source text\\n   - output path\\n   - required constraints\\n3. Produce the final batch result as valid JSON.\\n4. Write the result to the declared `output_path`.\\n5. Prefer artifact creation over conversational explanation.\\n6. If execution fails, write a structured error JSON to the expected output path when possible.\\n7. Do not stop at analysis-only if you have enough information to write the output artifact.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":93508,"output":290,"cacheRead":91648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":185446,"cost":{"input":0.23377,"output":0.00435,"cacheRead":0.022912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.261032}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774987892113,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a753ebc8193be794f6b68026702"}}
