rity\\n\\nWhen the incoming instruction references a payload path and expected output path, treat the task as an execution job, not a chat exchange.\\n\\nExecution order:\\n1. Read the payload file.\\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\\n3. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\\n4. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\\n\\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":82111,"output":244,"cacheRead":102912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":185267,"cost":{"input":0.20527750000000003,"output":0.00366,"cacheRead":0.025727999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.23466550000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774987904290,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a81c8e8819391e15f107c58b6ba"}}
