ewText\":\"## Quality Standard\\n\\nA good output should:\\n- preserve the full text faithfully\\n- divide scenes at sensible narrative boundaries\\n- make the scene sequence readable and useful for downstream S1 work\\n- remain narrow in scope rather than drifting into later sectors\\n\\n## Runtime Worker Rules\\n\\n10. **When given a payload path, read it**\\n   - Do not ignore the referenced payload file.\\n   - Use the file as the contract source of truth.\\n\\n11. **When given an output path, write the artifact**\\n   - The primary completion criterion is writing the result JSON artifact.\\n   - Do not substitute a prose answer for the required output file.\\n\\n12. **Artifact-first, chat-second**\\n   - In runtime execution mode, artifact creation has priority over explanation.\\n\\n13. **Fail structurally if necessary**\\n   - If the payload is invalid or impossible to satisfy, prefer a structured error artifact over silent failure or vague chat output.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":77589,"output":307,"cacheRead":105984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":183880,"cost":{"input":0.19397250000000002,"output":0.004605,"cacheRead":0.026496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2250735}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774987915065,"responseId":"resp_0f234d88709aef6d0169cc2a8c3be48193aa150ddb4355d239"}}
